class.name: AnrFunctionEUtran
class.description: The parameters and constraints for LTE Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) functions.

attribute.name: anrFunctionEUtranId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: anrUesThreshInterFMax
attribute.description: This parameter defines the maximum target number of UEs in each cell, that are assigned ANR specific thresholds for EUTRAN inter-frequency neighbor cell reports. The actual number of UEs with these thresholds may deviate from the target.

attribute.name: anrUesThreshInterFMin
attribute.description: This parameter defines the minimum target number of UEs in each cell, that are assigned ANR specific thresholds for EUTRAN inter-frequency neighbor cell reports. The actual number of UEs with these thresholds may deviate from the target.

attribute.name: anrUesThreshInterFDecr
attribute.description: This parameter defines the decrease in the target number of UEs in each cell, that are assigned ANR specific thresholds for EUTRAN inter-frequency neighbor cell reports, every time a neighbor cell report is received with only known neighbor cells.

attribute.name: anrUesThreshInterFIncrHo
attribute.description: This parameter defines the increase in the target number of UEs in each cell, that are assigned ANR specific thresholds for EUTRAN inter-frequency neighbor cell reports, every time a neighbor cell report for HO is received with unknown neighbor cells.

attribute.name: anrUesThreshInterFIncrAnr
attribute.description: This parameter defines the increase in the target number of UEs in each cell, that are assigned ANR specific thresholds for EUTRAN inter-frequency neighbor cell reports, every time a neighbor cell report for ANR is received with unknown neighbor cells.

attribute.name: anrInterFreqState
attribute.description: Activates or deactivates the Automated Neighbor Relation (ANR) function support for Inter frequency LTE for one RBS. The value of the attribute is irrelevant when no valid license key is installed for the ANR feature.

attribute.name: anrIntraFreqState
attribute.description: Activates or deactivates the Automated Neighbor Relation (ANR) function support for Intra frequency LTE for one RBS. The value of the attribute is irrelevant when no valid license key is installed for the ANR feature.

attribute.name: anrUesEUtraIntraFDecr
attribute.description: This parameter defines the decrease in the target number of UEs in each cell, that are assigned ANR specific thresholds for EUTRAN intra-frequency neighbour cell reports, every time a neighbour cell report is received with only known neighbour cells.

attribute.name: cellAddRsrpThresholdEutran
attribute.description: Threshold value for reported power for a cell to be automatically added as neighbor.

attribute.name: anrUesEUtraIntraFIncrHo
attribute.description: This parameter defines the increase in the target number of UEs in each cell, that are assigned ANR specific thresholds for EUTRAN intra-frequency neighbour cell reports, every time a neighbour cell report for HO is received with unknown neighbour cells.

attribute.name: x2SetupPolicy
attribute.description: Indicates if X2 is to be set up when an ExternalENodeBFunction that is not in the x2BlackList is created by ANR (Automatic Neighbor Relations).

attribute.name: cellAddRsrqThresholdEutran
attribute.description: Threshold value for reported quality for a cell to be automatically added as neighbor.

attribute.name: anrUesEUtraIntraFMin
attribute.description: This parameter defines the minimum target number of UEs in each cell, that are assigned ANR specific thresholds for EUTRAN intra-frequency neighbour cell reports. The actual number of UEs with these thresholds may deviate from the target.

attribute.name: anrUesEUtraIntraFMax
attribute.description: This parameter defines the maximum target number of UEs in each cell, that are assigned ANR specific thresholds for EUTRAN intra-frequency neighbour cell reports. The actual number of UEs with these thresholds may deviate from the target.

attribute.name: hoAllowedEutranPolicy
attribute.description: Starting value of the parameter isHoAllowed when a EUtranCellRelation is created by ANR (Automatic Neighbor Relations) or X2.

attribute.name: anrUesEUtraIntraFIncrAnr
attribute.description: This parameter defines the increase in the target number of UEs in each cell, that are assigned ANR specific thresholds for EUTRAN intra-frequency neighbour cell reports, every time a neighbour cell report for ANR is received with unknown neighbour cells.

attribute.name: lbCellOffloadCapacityPolicy
attribute.description: This attribute indicates the starting value of the attribute lbEUtranCellOffloadCapacity when an ExternalEUtranCell is created by Automated Neighbour Relations (ANR).

attribute.name: eutranAnrAgQci1
attribute.description: Enables or disables eNodeB to order CGI measurement when LTE AG capable UE has QCI1.
attribute.statusInformation: Since L16B. Planned to be removed
attribute.dependencies: This attribute is effective only when ANR for LTE feature is activated.

attribute.name: anrEutranInterFMeasReportMax
attribute.description: Maximum target number of periodic measurement reports each hour for each EUtranFreqRelation. The number of measurement reports can deviate from the target. Note that the unit is decMeasurementReport. Thus, the given number of measurement reports is divided by 10.
attribute.dependencies: anrEutranInterFMeasReportMax > anrEutranInterFMeasReportMin

attribute.name: anrEutranInterFMeasReportMin
attribute.description: Minimum target number of periodic measurement reports each hour for each EUtranFreqRelation. The number of measurement reports can deviate from the target. Note that the unit is decMeasurementReport. Thus, the given number of measurement reports is divided by 10.
attribute.dependencies: anrEutranInterFMeasReportMin < anrEutranInterFMeasReportMax

attribute.name: anrEutranInterFMeasReportIncr
attribute.description: Increase in the target number of periodic measurement reports for each EUtranFreqRelation each time an ANR EUTRAN measurement report is received with unknown neighbor EUTRAN cells. Note that the unit is decMeasurementReport. Thus, the given number of measurement reports is divided by 10.

attribute.name: anrEutranInterFMeasReportDecr
attribute.description: Decrease in the target number of periodic measurement reports for each EUtranFreqRelation each time an ANR EUTRAN measurement report is received with only known neighbor cells. Note that the unit is decMeasurementReport. Thus, the given number of measurement reports is divided by 10.

class.name: AnrFunctionUtran
class.description: This managed object contains parameters and constraints for the UTRAN Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) functions.

attribute.name: anrStateUtran
attribute.description: Activates or deactivates the Automated Neighbor Relation (ANR) function support for Utran for one RBS. The value of the attribute is irrelevant when no valid license key is installed for the ANR feature.

attribute.name: anrFunctionUtranId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: anrUtranMeasReportMax
attribute.description: Defines the maximum target number of measurement reports per hour for each UtranFreqRelation/UtranTDDFreqRelation. The number of measurement reports may deviate from the target. Please note that the unit is decMeasurementReport. Thus, the given number of measurement reports will be divided by 10.

attribute.name: anrUtranMeasReportMin
attribute.description: Defines the minimum target number of measurement reports per hour for each UtranFreqRelation/UtranTDDFreqRelation. The number of measurement reports may deviate from the target. Please note that the unit is decMeasurementReport. Thus, the given number of measurement reports will be divided by 10.

attribute.name: anrUtranMeasReportDecr
attribute.description: Defines the decrease in the target number of measurement reports for each UtranFreqRelation/UtranTDDFreqRelation each time an Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) UTRAN measurement report is received with only known neighbor cells. Please note that the unit is decMeasurementReport. Thus, the given number of measurement reports will be divided by 10.

attribute.name: anrUtranMeasReportIncr
attribute.description: Defines the increase in the target number of measurement reports for each UtranFreqRelation/UtranTDDFreqRelation each time an Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) UTRAN measurement report is received with unknown neighbor UTRAN cells. Please note that the unit is decMeasurementReport. Thus, the given number of measurement reports will be divided by 10.

attribute.name: hoAllowedUtranPolicy
attribute.description: Starting value of the parameter isHoAllowed when a UtranCellRelation is created by ANR (Automatic Neighbor Relations)

attribute.name: anrUtranMeasReportAcIncr
attribute.description: Defines the increase in the target number of measurement reports for each UtranFreqRelation/UtranTDDFreqRelation each time a PCI measurement report is received with known cell but the corresponding LAC or RAC missing. Please note that the unit is decMeasurementReport. Thus, the given number of measurement reports will be divided by 10.

attribute.name: anrUtranAcMeasOn
attribute.description: Indicates whether more CGI measurements shall be initiated to find LAC and/or RAC for cells that were previously added by ANR with missing LAC or RAC.

attribute.name: rimIntegrationEnabled
attribute.description: This parameter indicates if ANR should be able to modify RIM associations to UTRAN cells.

attribute.name: cellAddRscpThresholdUtranDelta
attribute.description: This parameter together with b2Threshold2RscpUtra specifies "The Received Signal Code Power" (RSCP) threshold value for reported power for a cell to be automatically added as neighbor. The equation for calculating the RSCP threshold is b2Threshold2RscpUtra + cellAddRscpThresholdUtranDelta.

attribute.name: cellAddEcNoThresholdUtranDelta
attribute.description: This parameter together with b2Threshold2EcNoUtra specifies "Ratio of energy per modulation bit to noise spectral density" threshold value for reported EcNo for a cell to be automatically added as neighbor. The equation for calculating the EcNo threshold is b2Threshold2EcNoUtra + cellAddEcNoThresholdUtranDelta.

attribute.name: srvccPolicy
attribute.description: Starting value of the parameter srvccCapability when an ExternalUtranCellFDD/TDD is created by ANR (Automatic Neighbor Relations)

attribute.name: utranAnrAgQci1
attribute.description: Enables or disables eNodeB to order CGI measurement when UTRAN AG capable UE has QCI1.
attribute.statusInformation: Since L16B. Planned to be removed
attribute.dependencies: This attribute is effective only when ANR for UTRAN feature is activated.

class.name: AnrFunctionGeran
class.description: This managed object contains parameters and constraints for GERAN Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) functions.

attribute.name: anrStateGsm
attribute.description: Activates or deactivates the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function support for GSM for one RBS. The value of the attribute is irrelevant when no valid license key is installed for the ANR feature.

attribute.name: anrFunctionGeranId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: anrGeranMeasReportMax
attribute.description: The maximum target number of measurement reports per hour for each GeranFrequencyGroupRelation. The number of measurement reports may deviate from the target. Please note that the unit is decMeasurementReport. Thus, the given number of measurement reports will be divided by 10.

attribute.name: anrGeranMeasReportMin
attribute.description: The minimum target number of measurement reports per hour for each GeranFrequencyGroupRelation. The number of measurement reports may deviate from the target. Please note that the unit is decMeasurementReport. Thus, the given number of measurement reports will be divided by 10.

attribute.name: anrGeranMeasReportDecr
attribute.description: The decrease in the target number of measurement reports per GeranFrequencyGroupRelation each time an Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) GERAN measurement report is received with only known neighbor cells. Please note that the unit is decMeasurementReport. Thus, the given number of measurement reports will be divided by 10.

attribute.name: anrGeranMeasReportIncr
attribute.description: Defines the increase in the target number of measurement reports per GeranFrequencyGroupRelation each time an Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) GERAN measurement report is received with unknown neighbor GERAN cells or an unknown cell found in GERAN mobility report. Please note that the unit is decMeasurementReport. Thus, the given number of measurement reports will be divided by 10.

attribute.name: rimIntegrationEnabled
attribute.description: This parameter indicates if ANR should be able to modify RIM associations to GERAN cells

attribute.name: anrGeranMeasReportRacIncr
attribute.description: Defines the increase in the target number of measurement reports for each GeranFreqGroupRelation each time a PCI measurement report is received with known cell but the corresponding RAC missing. Please note that the unit is decMeasurementReport. Thus, the given number of measurement reports will be divided by 10.

attribute.name: anrGeranRacMeasOn
attribute.description: Indicates whether more CGI measurements shall be initiated to find RAC for cells that were previously added by ANR with missing RAC.

class.name: PlmnInfo
class.description: PLMN specific configuration parameters.

attribute.name: plmnInfoId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: plmnWhiteList
attribute.description: Lists all PLMN IDs that are available for outgoing handover toward EUTRAN, UTRAN or GERAN cell and X2 setup.

attribute.name: actualPlmn
attribute.description: PLMN that plmnWhiteList is applied to.

class.name: DataRadioBearer
class.description: Radio Bearer configuration.

attribute.name: dataRadioBearerId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: tPollRetransmitUl
attribute.description: Time lapsed before request for new poll if no STATUS report arrives for the Sequence Number that is contained in the UL RLC Data PDU where the poll bit is set.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause significantly higher drop rate.

attribute.name: tPollRetransmitDl
attribute.description: Time lapsed before request for new poll if no STATUS report arrives for the Sequence Number that is contained in the DL RLC Data PDU where the poll bit is set.

attribute.name: dlMaxRetxThreshold
attribute.description: Maximum number RLC re-transmissions in DL before stopping and indicating to RRC that the RLC threshold is reached.

attribute.name: ulMaxRetxThreshold
attribute.description: Maximum number RLC re-transmissions in UL before stopping and indicating to RRC that the RLC threshold is reached.
attribute.disturbances: Lowering the value of this attribute can cause significantly higher drop rate.

class.name: MACConfiguration
class.description:
MAC configuration.
The RDN of this MO is MACConfiguration=1.

attribute.name: dlMaxHARQTx
attribute.description: Maximum number of transmissions for one HARQ process in DL. Values higher than 7 will be treated as 7.

attribute.name: ulMaxHARQTx
attribute.description: Maximum number of transmissions for one HARQ process in UL.
attribute.dependencies: Overridden by ulTtiBundlingMaxHARQTx when UE is in TTI Bundling mode. TTI bundling mode occurs only when feature TTI Bundling is active.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: mACConfigurationId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: ulTtiBundlingMaxHARQTx
attribute.description: Maximum number of transmissions for one HARQ process in UL when UE is in TTI Bundling mode.
attribute.dependencies: Valid only when feature TTI Bundling is active. Overrides ulMaxHARQTx when UE is in TTI Bundling mode.

class.name: RadioBearerTable
class.description:
Contains Radio Bearer configurations.
The RDN for this MO type is "default".

attribute.name: radioBearerTableId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

class.name: SignalingRadioBearer
class.description: Signaling Radio Bearer configuration.

attribute.name: signalingRadioBearerId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: tReorderingUl
attribute.description: This timer is used by the receiving end of the Acknowledged Mode (AM) Radio Link Control (RLC) entity in eNB for SRB1 or SRB2, to detect loss of uplink RLC protocol data units at lower layers.
attribute.disturbances: Low values can cause high drop rate.

attribute.name: tPollRetransmitDl
attribute.description: Time lapsed before request for new poll if no STATUS report arrives for the Sequence Number that is contained in the DL RLC Data PDU where the poll bit is set.

attribute.name: dlMaxRetxThreshold
attribute.description: Maximum number RLC re-transmissions in DL before stopping and indicating to RRC that the RLC threshold is reached.

attribute.name: tPollRetransmitUl
attribute.description: Time lapsed before request for new poll if no STATUS report arrives for the Sequence Number that is contained in the UL RLC Data PDU where the poll bit is set.
attribute.disturbances: High values can cause high drop rate.

attribute.name: tReorderingDl
attribute.description: Time before sending STATUS report when a Sequence Number is outstanding.

attribute.name: ulMaxRetxThreshold
attribute.description: Maximum number RLC re-transmissions in UL before stopping and indicating to RRC that the RLC threshold is reached.
attribute.disturbances: Low values can cause high drop rate.

class.name: LogicalChannelGroup
class.description: Represents QoS configuration related to a Logical Channel group.

attribute.name: logicalChannelGroupId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN). Valid values for this MO type are: 0, 1, 2, or 3. The values correspond to logical channel group IDs in 3GPP TS 36.321.

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use.

attribute.name: reservedBy
attribute.description: Contains a list of QciProfile instances that reserve this MO instance.

class.name: QciProfilePredefined
class.description:
Contains bearer-level QoS configuration. It is not possible to create or remove instances of this MO. Each QciProfilePredefined instance corresponds to a standardized QCI as described in TS 23.203, except for a default QCI profile activated whenever a profile related to a specific QCI is not defined.
The RDNs for this MO type is "qci1", "qci2", .. "qci9", "default".

attribute.name: schedulingAlgorithm
attribute.description: Specifies which scheduling algorithm is to be used for a certain QCI.
attribute.dependencies: Only relevant if the license for QoS Aware Scheduler is present and the feature is active. The value DELAY_BASED can only be used if the attribute serviceType has value VOIP.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: qciProfilePredefinedId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use.

attribute.name: qci
attribute.description:
Quality of Service Class Indicator (QCI) as defined in 3GPP TS 23.203 (Release 8). Each instance of this MO has a unique value for the QCI.
Special value: 0 refers to a default QCI profile activated whenever a profile related to a specific QCI has not been defined.
attribute.dependencies: Each qci must be set to a unique value.

attribute.name: priority
attribute.description: Quality of Service Class Indicator (QCI)-related priority as defined in 3GPP TS 23.203 (Release 8).
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: pdb
attribute.description: The contribution from eNodeB to the Packet Delay Budget (PDB) for a QCI. Packet delays outside eNodeB e.g. in the transport network are excluded. For more information about PDB refer to TS 23.203.
attribute.dependencies: Only relevant if the license for QoS Aware Scheduler is present and active.

attribute.name: dscp
attribute.description: The Differentiated Services Code Point for a Quality of Service Class Indicator (QCI). This corresponds to mappings from RAN QoS to Transport Network QoS.

attribute.name: logicalChannelGroupRef
attribute.description: Refers to an instance of LogicalChannelGroup. Assigns a Logical Channel Group to a Quality of Service Class Indicator (QCI).

attribute.name: aqmMode
attribute.description: Active Queue Management (AQM) mode

attribute.name: pdbOffset
attribute.description: An offset to the PDB used by Active Queue Management (AQM).
attribute.dependencies: pdb + pdbOffset >= 0

attribute.name: dlMinBitRate
attribute.description: The scheduler will attempt to achieve minbitrate for all bearers before giving any user a higher rate. Value 0 means that the minRate scheduler is not used.
attribute.dependencies: This parameter will only be used if one of the following Proportional Fair scheduling algorithms, "maximum_C_over_I", "proportional_fair_low", "proportional_fair_medium", "proportional_fair_high" or "equal_rate", has been selected. Only relevant if the license for QoS Aware Scheduler is present and the feature is active.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: rlcSNLength
attribute.description: Radio Link Control (RLC) Sequence Number length in bits as specified in TS 36.322.
attribute.dependencies: RLC UM must be configured (rlcMode = UM) to set this attribute to 5. RLC AM must be configured (rlcMode = AM) to set this attribute to 16. 16-bit RLC SN is only applied if: - extendedRLC-SN-SO-Field-r13 is indicated by UE; and - 5CC DL Carrier Aggregation Extension license is enabled; and - UE is capable of at least 5CC DL Carrier Aggregation. Otherwise, default value of 10-bit RLC SN is applied for RLC AM bearers.

attribute.name: pdcpSNLength
attribute.description: Indicates the Packet Data Convergence Protocol (PDCP) Sequence Number length in bits as specified in TS 36.323.
attribute.dependencies: RLC UM must be configured (rlcMode = UM) to set this attribute to 7. RLC AM must be configured (rlcMode = AM) to set this attribute to 15. 15-bits PDCP SN is only applied if: - pdcp-SN-Extension capability is indicated by UE; And - UE is of category 11 or above; And - UE is capable of at least 3C Carrier Aggregation. Otherwise, default value of 12-bits PDCP SN is applied for RLC AM bearers.

attribute.name: tReorderingDl
attribute.description: This timer is used by the receiving end of Acknowledged Mode (AM) or Unacknowledged Mode (UM) Radio Link Control (RLC) entity in UE, to detect loss of downlink RLC protocol data units at lower layers.
attribute.dependencies: Not applicable for RLC TM. Only relevant when rlcMode is UM or AM

attribute.name: tReorderingUl
attribute.description: This timer is used by the receiving end of the Acknowledged Mode (AM) or Unacknowledged Mode (UM) Radio Link Control (RLC) entity in eNB, to detect loss of uplink RLC protocol data units at lower layers.
attribute.dependencies: Not applicable for RLC TM. Only relevant when rlcMode is UM or AM

attribute.name: rlcMode
attribute.description: RLC Mode
attribute.dependencies: Can only be set to AM if rlcSNLength is set to 10 or 16 and pdcpSNLength is set to 12 or 15. Must be set to UM if rlcSNLength is set to 5 or pdcpSNLength is set to 7.

attribute.name: resourceType
attribute.description: Indicates if the resource type of the Quality of Service Class Indicator (QCI) is Guaranteed Bit Rate (GBR) or non-GBR as defined in 3GPP TS 23.203.

attribute.name: dataFwdPerQciEnabled
attribute.description: Enables forwarding of data for this QCI.
attribute.dependencies: The parameter is only valid if the IntraLTEHODataFwd or S1HODataFwd licence is installed and active.

attribute.name: ulMinBitRate
attribute.description: The scheduler will attempt to achieve minbitrate for all bearers before giving any user a higher rate. Value 0 means that the minRate scheduler is not used.
attribute.dependencies:
This parameter will only be used if one of the following Proportional Fair scheduling algorithms, "maximum_C_over_I", "proportional_fair_low", "proportional_fair_medium", "proportional_fair_high" or "equal_rate", has been selected.
Only relevant if the license for QoS Aware Scheduler is present and the feature is active.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: absPrioOverride
attribute.description: Indicates if the data radio bearer is subject to Absolute Priority Override.
attribute.dependencies: Only relevant if the license for QoS Aware Scheduler is present and the feature is active.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: resourceAllocationStrategy
attribute.description: Defines the resource allocation strategy of the QoS Class Identifier (QCI).
attribute.dependencies: Only relevant if the licenses for Uplink Frequency Selective Scheduling and QoS Aware Scheduler are present and the features are active.

attribute.name: srsAllocationStrategy
attribute.description: If the parameter srsAllocationStrategy in the QoS configuration for a Data radio Bearer assigned to a UE is set to ACTIVATED, then an attempt is made to allocate sounding for a UE. If several Data Radio Bearers are setup towards the UE with different QoS configurations, and the QoS configurations has different QCI parameter, an algorithm using the priority parameter in the QoS configuration, will resolve which QoS configuration that will define sounding.
attribute.dependencies: Only relevant if the licenses for QoS Aware Scheduler and frequency selective scheduling are present and the features are active.

attribute.name: measReportConfigParams
attribute.description: Encapsulates the offset quantities of the mobility measurement thresholds. Only absolute mobility measurement thresholds are considered. The structure holds, for example, offsets for the thresholds a1ThresholdRsrpPrim, a2ThresholdRsrpPrim, and a5Threshold1Rsrp. The offsets are meant mainly to have values that differentiate the measurement thresholds between QCIs.

attribute.name: qciSubscriptionQuanta
attribute.description: Normalized subscription quantity associated with the specific the QCI. Specifies the subscription cost of a bearer with this predefined profile. The subscription cost is used for traffic load balancing purposes.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: qciACTuning
attribute.description: Tuning factor per QCI for admission control. Only valid for QCIs with resource type GBR.
attribute.dependencies: Only relevant if the license for Dynamic GBR admission control is present and the feature is active.
attribute.disturbances: Setting values below one means overbooking of GBR resources and thus a risk of letting in more GBR traffic than can be supported. Setting values above one means underbooking of GBR resources and thus a risk of underutilization of the resources.

attribute.name: dlResourceAllocationStrategy
attribute.description: Defines the downlink resource allocation strategy of the QoS Class Identifier (QCI).
attribute.dependencies: Changes to this parameter take effect only if the licenses for Downlink Frequency Selective Scheduling and QoS Aware Scheduler are present and the features are active.

attribute.name: relativePriority
attribute.description: The relative priority associated with a QCI.
attribute.dependencies: Changes to this parameter take effect only if the feature states of the QoS Aware Scheduler , Proportional Fair Scheduler, and the Rps are enabled.

attribute.name: rohcEnabled
attribute.description: Indicates if Robust Header Compression (ROHC) is enabled. Note: Enabling ROHC is only supported for a QCI that is intended to carry RTP/RTCP/UDP based VoIP traffic as for example the standardized QCI1 (3GPP TS 23.203) and not for any other type of traffic.

attribute.name: serviceType
attribute.description: Indicates the service that the bearer is used for.
attribute.dependencies: Changes to this parameter take effect only if the license for QoS Aware Scheduler is present and the feature is active.

attribute.name: drxProfileRef
attribute.description: Points out the DRX profile associated with this QCI. If not set the default reference will be to the DrxProfile instance corresponding to Local Distinguished Name (LDN) = ManagementElement=1, ENodeBFunction=1, DRxProfile=0.
attribute.dependencies: The DRX profile must exist, otherwise it will be interpreted as default DRX profile.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. Possible mismatch between DRX setting used by network and UE for ongoing connections.

attribute.name: drxPriority
attribute.description: The relative priority among the DRX profiles, i.e. if the bearer that is setup with this QCI has a higher DRX priority than any of the existing bearers, the DRX configuration will be set to those selected by the drxProfileId for this QCI. The drxPriority has to be unique across all the configured QciProfilePredefined and QciProfileOperatorDefined MOC instances except for instances where the drxProfileId is the same. That is, instances that share the same drxProfileId may have the same drxPriority value. Also note that larger drxPriority values indicate higher relative priority.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. Possible mismatch between DRX setting used by network and UE for ongoing connections.

attribute.name: counterActiveMode
attribute.description: Defines the interpretation of active for the QCI: FALSE (DEFAULT): Active time is measured in the case of: DRB: as the time when there is data in a buffer, DL and/or UL, with an added guard period of 100 ms thereafter UE: as the time when there is data in a buffer, DL and/or UL, with an added guard period of 100 ms thereafter in any of the DRBs connected to the UE The pmCounters for active E-RABs are stepped in case of data in a buffer, DL and/or UL. TRUE: Active time is measured in the case of: DRB: from the first data occurrence in a buffer to the last data occurrence in a buffer for that DRB UE: from the first data occurrence in a buffer to the last data occurrence in a buffer for any DRB associated with the UE The pmCounters for active E-RABs are always stepped since the DRB is considered always active

attribute.name: reservedBy
attribute.description: Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.

attribute.name: rlfProfileRef
attribute.description: Points out the RLF profile associated with this QCI. If not set the default reference will be to the RlfProfile instance corresponding to Local Distinguished Name (LDN) = ManagementElement=1, ENodeBFunction=1, RlfProfile=0.
attribute.dependencies: The RLF profile must exist, otherwise it will be interpreted as default RLF profile.

attribute.name: rlfPriority
attribute.description: The relative priority among the RLF (Radio Link Failure) profiles, i.e. if the bearer that is setup with this QCI has a higher RLF priority than any of the existing bearers, the RLF configuration will be set to those selected by the rlfProfileId for this QCI. If more than one QCI has been configured with the same and highest value of rlfPriority the RLF configuration will be set by the lowest QCI. The instances that share the same rlfProfileId may have the same rlfPriority value. Also note that larger rlfPriority values indicate higher relative priority.

attribute.name: inactivityTimerOffset
attribute.description: The offset time value that can be used to prolong the default inactivity timer.

attribute.name: dlMaxWaitingTime
attribute.description: The scheduler attempts to achieve dlMaxWaitingTime for DL bearers before giving any DL bearer a higher priority. Value 0 means that the higher priority is never applied. Must be set to a similar or slightly shorter value than the PDB. Setting too low a value can affect other services with higher priority. For more information about PDB refer to TS 23.203.
attribute.dependencies: Only used for Resource Fair Scheduling algorithm. Only relevant if the license for Advanced Differentiation for Resource Fair Scheduler is present and the feature is active.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect performance of all data bearers. A value that is set too low can affect other services with higher priority. A value that is set too high can cause Dynamic UE Admission Control to fail in keeping the cell stable at overload.

attribute.name: ulMaxWaitingTime
attribute.description: The scheduler attempts to achieve ulMaxWaitingTime for UL bearers before giving any UL bearer a higher priority. Value 0 means that the higher priority is never applied. Must be set to a similar or slightly shorter value than the PDB. Setting too low a value can affect other services with higher priority. For more information about PDB refer to TS 23.203.
attribute.dependencies: Only used for Resource Fair Scheduling algorithm. Only relevant if the license for Advanced Differentiation for Resource Fair Scheduler is present and the feature is active.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect performance of all data bearers. A value that is set too low can affect other services with higher priority. A value that is set too high can cause Dynamic UE Admission Control to fail in keeping the cell stable at overload.

attribute.name: timerProfileRef
attribute.description: Refers to the timer profile associated with this QCI.

attribute.name: timerPriority
attribute.description: Relative priority among the timer profiles. TimerProfile with highest priority can be applied for a new connection in case the bearer QCI has an associated TimerProfile. In case several bearers with different QCIs are established, the TimerProfile with highest relative priority is applied. The TimerProfile with lowest QCI number is applied, if TimerProfiles have the same priority, Larger timerPriority value indicates higher relative priority.

attribute.name: dlMaxHARQTxQci
attribute.description: Maximum number of transmissions for one HARQ process in DL when this QCI has the highest HARQ priority. Values higher than 7 will be treated as 7.

attribute.name: ulMaxHARQTxQci
attribute.description: Maximum number of transmissions for one HARQ process in UL when this QCI has the highest HARQ priority.

attribute.name: harqPriority
attribute.description: Relative HARQ priority of this QCI. If a bearer that is setup with this QCI has highest HARQ priority, HARQ transmission number is set to ulMaxHARQTxQci and dlMaxHARQTxQci. HARQ priority must be unique for all configured MOC instances for QciProfilePredefined and QciProfileOperatorDefined. Does not apply when ulMaxHARQTxQci and dlMaxHARQTxQci are same. Note that larger harqPriority values indicate higher relative priority.

attribute.name: lessMaxDelayThreshold
attribute.description: Time delay that scheduling stays on-hold for Low Energy Scheduler Solution. If 0, Low Energy Scheduler Solution is disabled.

class.name: QciTable
class.description:
Contains mapping from QCIs to parameters that has impact on QoS for DRBs.
The RDN for this MO type is "default".

attribute.name: qciTableId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: reservedBy
attribute.description: Contains a list of cells that reserves this MO instance.

class.name: QciProfileOperatorDefined
class.description: Contains bearer-level QoS configuration. Instances of this class are created on demand by the operator. Each QciProfileOperatorDefined instance corresponds to a unique operator defined QCI number within the range 10-255. The instances can be created and configured independent of the serviceStateOperatorDefinedQci. However the configured QCI profiles can not be used at bearer setup / modify unless the service state is OPERABLE.

attribute.name: absPrioOverride
attribute.description: Indicates if the data radio bearer is subject to Absolute Priority Override.
attribute.dependencies: Only relevant if the license for QoS Aware Scheduler is present and the feature is active.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: aqmMode
attribute.description: Active Queue Management (AQM) mode

attribute.name: dataFwdPerQciEnabled
attribute.description: Enables forwarding of data for this QCI.
attribute.dependencies: The parameter is only valid if the IntraLTEHODataFwd or S1HODataFwd licence is installed and active.

attribute.name: dlMinBitRate
attribute.description: The scheduler will attempt to achieve minbitrate for all bearers before giving any user a higher rate. Value 0 means that the minRate scheduler is not used.
attribute.dependencies:
This parameter will only be used if one of the following Proportional Fair scheduling algorithms, "maximum_C_over_I", "proportional_fair_low", "proportional_fair_medium", "proportional_fair_high" or "equal_rate", has been selected.
Only relevant if the license for QoS Aware Scheduler is present and the feature is active.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: dscp
attribute.description: The Differentiated Services Code Point for a Quality of Service Class Indicator (QCI). This corresponds to mappings from RAN QoS to Transport Network QoS.

attribute.name: logicalChannelGroupRef
attribute.description: Refers to an instance of LogicalChannelGroup. Assigns a Logical Channel Group to a Quality of Service Class Indicator (QCI).

attribute.name: measReportConfigParams
attribute.description: Encapsulates the offset quantities of the mobility measurement thresholds. Only absolute mobility measurement thresholds are considered. The structure holds, for example, offsets for the thresholds a1ThresholdRsrpPrim, a2ThresholdRsrpPrim, and a5Threshold1Rsrp. The offsets are meant mainly to have values that differentiate the measurement thresholds between QCIs.

attribute.name: pdb
attribute.description: The contribution from eNodeB to the Packet Delay Budget (PDB) for a QCI. Packet delays outside eNodeB e.g. in the transport network are excluded. For more information about PDB refer to TS 23.203
attribute.dependencies: Only relevant if the license for QoS Aware Scheduler is present and active.

attribute.name: pdbOffset
attribute.description: An offset to the PDB used by Active Queue Management (AQM).
attribute.dependencies: pdb + pdbOffset >= 0

attribute.name: pdcpSNLength
attribute.description: Indicates the Packet Data Convergence Protocol (PDCP) Sequence Number length in bits as specified in TS 36.323.
attribute.dependencies: RLC UM must be configured (rlcMode = UM) to set this attribute to 7. RLC AM must be configured (rlcMode = AM) to set this attribute to 15. 15-bits PDCP SN is only applied if: - pdcp-SN-Extension capability is indicated by UE; And - UE is of category 11 or above; And - UE is capable of at least 3C Carrier Aggregation. Otherwise, default value of 12-bits PDCP SN is applied for RLC AM bearers.

attribute.name: priority
attribute.description: Quality of Service Class Indicator (QCI)-related priority as defined in 3GPP TS 23.203 (Release 8).
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: qci
attribute.description: Quality of Service Class Indicator (QCI) as defined in 3GPP TS 23.203 (Release 8). Each instance of this MO has a unique value for the QCI.
attribute.dependencies: Each qci must be set to a unique value.

attribute.name: qciACTuning
attribute.description: Tuning factor per QCI for admission control. Only valid for QCIs with resource type GBR.
attribute.dependencies: Only relevant if the license for Dynamic GBR admission control is present and the feature is active.

attribute.name: qciProfileOperatorDefinedId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: qciSubscriptionQuanta
attribute.description: Normalized subscription quantity associated with the specific the QCI. Specifies the subscription cost of a bearer with this predefined profile. The subscription cost is used for traffic load balancing purposes.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: resourceAllocationStrategy
attribute.description: Defines the resource allocation strategy of the QoS Class Identifier (QCI).
attribute.dependencies: Only relevant if the license for QoS Aware Scheduler is present and the feature is active

attribute.name: resourceType
attribute.description: Indicates if the resource type of the Quality of Service Class Indicator (QCI) is Guaranteed Bit Rate (GBR) or non-GBR as defined in 3GPP TS 23.203.

attribute.name: rlcMode
attribute.description: RLC Mode
attribute.dependencies: Can only be set to AM if rlcSNLength is set to 10 or 16 and pdcpSNLength is set to 12 or 15. Must be set to UM if rlcSNLength is set to 5 or pdcpSNLength is set to 7.

attribute.name: rlcSNLength
attribute.description: Radio Link Control (RLC) Sequence Number length in bits as specified in TS 36.322.
attribute.dependencies: RLC UM must be configured (rlcMode = UM) to set this attribute to 5. RLC AM must be configured (rlcMode = AM) to set this attribute to 16. 16-bit RLC SN is only applied if: - extendedRLC-SN-SO-Field-r13 is indicated by UE; and - 5CC DL Carrier Aggregation Extension license is enabled; and - UE is capable of at least 5CC DL Carrier Aggregation. Otherwise, default value of 10-bit RLC SN is applied for RLC AM bearers.

attribute.name: schedulingAlgorithm
attribute.description: Specifies which scheduling algorithm is to be used for a certain QCI.
attribute.dependencies: Only relevant if the license for QoS Aware Scheduler is present and the feature is active. The value DELAY_BASED can only be used if the attribute serviceType has value VOIP.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: srsAllocationStrategy
attribute.description: If the parameter srsAllocationStrategy in the QoS configuration for a Data radio Bearer assigned to a UE is set to ACTIVATED, then an attempt is made to allocate sounding for a UE. If several Data Radio Bearers are setup towards the UE with different QoS configurations, and the QoS configurations has different QCI parameter, an algorithm using the priority parameter in the QoS configuration, will resolve which QoS configuration that will define sounding

attribute.name: tReorderingDl
attribute.description: This timer is used by the receiving end of Acknowledged Mode (AM) or Unacknowledged Mode (UM) Radio Link Control (RLC) entity in UE, to detect loss of downlink RLC protocol data units at lower layers.
attribute.dependencies: Not applicable for RLC TM. Only relevant when rlcMode is UM or AM

attribute.name: tReorderingUl
attribute.description: This timer is used by the receiving end of the Acknowledged Mode (AM) or Unacknowledged Mode (UM) Radio Link Control (RLC) entity in eNB, to detect loss of uplink RLC protocol data units at lower layers.
attribute.dependencies: Not applicable for RLC TM. Only relevant when rlcMode is UM or AM

attribute.name: ulMinBitRate
attribute.description: The scheduler will attempt to achieve minbitrate for all bearers before giving any user a higher rate. Value 0 means that the minRate scheduler is not used.
attribute.dependencies:
This parameter will only be used if one of the following Proportional Fair scheduling algorithms, "maximum_C_over_I", "proportional_fair_low", "proportional_fair_medium", "proportional_fair_high" or "equal_rate", has been selected.
Only relevant if the license for QoS Aware Scheduler is present and the feature is active.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use.

attribute.name: relativePriority
attribute.description: The relative priority associated with a QCI.
attribute.dependencies: Changes to this parameter take effect only if the feature states of the QoS Aware Scheduler , Proportional Fair Scheduler, and the Rps are enabled.

attribute.name: serviceType
attribute.description: Indicates the service that the bearer is used for.
attribute.dependencies: Changes to this parameter take effect only if the license for QoS Aware Scheduler is present and the feature is active.

attribute.name: drxProfileRef
attribute.description: Points out the DRX profile associated with this QCI. If not set the default reference will be to the DrxProfile instance corresponding to Local Distinguished Name (LDN) = ManagementElement=1, ENodeBFunction=1, DRxProfile=0.
attribute.dependencies: The DRX profile must exist, otherwise it will be interpreted as default DRX profile.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. Possible mismatch between DRX setting used by network and UE for ongoing connections.

attribute.name: drxPriority
attribute.description: The relative priority among the DRX profiles, i.e. if the bearer that is setup with this QCI has a higher DRX priority than any of the existing bearers, the DRX configuration will be set to those selected by the drxProfileId for this QCI. The drxPriority has to be unique across all the configured QciProfilePredefined and QciProfileOperatorDefined MOC instances except for instances where the drxProfileId is the same. That is, instances that share the same drxProfileId may have the same drxPriority value. Also note that larger drxPriority values indicate higher relative priority.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. Possible mismatch between DRX setting used by network and UE for ongoing connections.

attribute.name: counterActiveMode
attribute.description: Defines the interpretation of active for the QCI: FALSE (DEFAULT): Active time is measured in the case of: DRB: as the time when there is data in a buffer, DL and/or UL, with an added guard period of 100 ms thereafter UE: as the time when there is data in a buffer, DL and/or UL, with an added guard period of 100 ms thereafter in any of the DRBs connected to the UE The pmCounters for active E-RABs are stepped in case of data in a buffer, DL and/or UL. TRUE: Active time is measured in the case of: DRB: from the first data occurrence in a buffer to the last data occurrence in a buffer for that DRB UE: from the first data occurrence in a buffer to the last data occurrence in a buffer for any DRB associated with the UE The pmCounters for active E-RABs are always stepped since the DRB is considered always active

attribute.name: rohcEnabled
attribute.description: Indicates if Robust Header Compression (ROHC) is enabled. Note: Enabling ROHC is only supported for a QCI that is intended to carry RTP/RTCP/UDP based VoIP traffic as for example the standardized QCI1 (3GPP TS 23.203) and not for any other type of traffic.

attribute.name: dlResourceAllocationStrategy
attribute.description: Defines the downlink resource allocation strategy of the QoS Class Identifier (QCI).
attribute.dependencies: Changes to this parameter take effect only if the licenses for Downlink Frequency Selective Scheduling and QoS Aware Scheduler are present and the features are active.

attribute.name: reservedBy
attribute.description: Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.

attribute.name: rlfProfileRef
attribute.description: Points out the RLF profile associated with this QCI. If not set the default reference will be to the RlfProfile instance corresponding to Local Distinguished Name (LDN) = ManagementElement=1, ENodeBFunction=1, RlfProfile=0.
attribute.dependencies: The RLF profile must exist, otherwise it will be interpreted as default RLF profile.

attribute.name: rlfPriority
attribute.description: The relative priority among the RLF (Radio Link Failure) profiles, i.e. if the bearer that is setup with this QCI has a higher RLF priority than any of the existing bearers, the RLF configuration will be set to those selected by the rlfProfileId for this QCI. If more than one QCI has been configured with the same and highest value of rlfPriority the RLF configuration will be set by the lowest QCI. The instances that share the same rlfProfileId may have the same rlfPriority value. Also note that larger rlfPriority values indicate higher relative priority.

attribute.name: inactivityTimerOffset
attribute.description: The offset time value that can be used to prolong the default inactivity timer.

attribute.name: dlMaxWaitingTime
attribute.description: The scheduler attempts to achieve dlMaxWaitingTime for DL bearers before giving any DL bearer a higher priority. Value 0 means that the higher priority is never applied. Must be set to a similar or slightly shorter value than the PDB. Setting too low a value can affect other services with higher priority. For more information about PDB refer to TS 23.203.
attribute.dependencies: Only used for Resource Fair Scheduling algorithm. Only relevant if the license for Advanced Differentiation for Resource Fair Scheduler is present and the feature is active.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect performance of all data bearers. A value that is set too low can affect other services with higher priority. A value that is set too high can cause Dynamic UE Admission Control to fail in keeping the cell stable at overload.

attribute.name: ulMaxWaitingTime
attribute.description: The scheduler attempts to achieve ulMaxWaitingTime for UL bearers before giving any UL bearer a higher priority. Value 0 means that the higher priority is never applied. Must be set to a similar or slightly shorter value than the PDB. Setting too low a value can affect other services with higher priority. For more information about PDB refer to TS 23.203.
attribute.dependencies: Only used for Resource Fair Scheduling algorithm. Only relevant if the license for Advanced Differentiation for Resource Fair Scheduler is present and the feature is active.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect performance of all data bearers. A value that is set too low can affect other services with higher priority. A value that is set too high can cause Dynamic UE Admission Control to fail in keeping the cell stable at overload.

attribute.name: timerProfileRef
attribute.description: Refers to the timer profile associated with this QCI.

attribute.name: timerPriority
attribute.description: Relative priority among the timer profiles. TimerProfile with highest priority can be applied for a new connection in case the bearer QCI has an associated TimerProfile. In case several bearers with different QCIs are established, the TimerProfile with highest relative priority is applied. The TimerProfile with lowest QCI number is applied, if TimerProfiles have the same priority, Larger timerPriority value indicates higher relative priority.

attribute.name: dlMaxHARQTxQci
attribute.description: Maximum number of transmissions for one HARQ process in DL when this QCI has the highest HARQ priority. Values higher than 7 will be treated as 7.

attribute.name: ulMaxHARQTxQci
attribute.description: Maximum number of transmissions for one HARQ process in UL when this QCI has the highest HARQ priority.

attribute.name: harqPriority
attribute.description: Relative HARQ priority of this QCI. If a bearer that is setup with this QCI has highest HARQ priority, HARQ transmission number is set to ulMaxHARQTxQci and dlMaxHARQTxQci. HARQ priority must be unique for all configured MOC instances for QciProfilePredefined and QciProfileOperatorDefined. Does not apply when ulMaxHARQTxQci and dlMaxHARQTxQci are same. Note that larger harqPriority values indicate higher relative priority.

attribute.name: lessMaxDelayThreshold
attribute.description: Time delay that scheduling stays on-hold for Low Energy Scheduler Solution. If 0, Low Energy Scheduler Solution is disabled.

class.name: RlfProfile
class.description:
Contains RLF (Radio Link Failure) profiles, RLF parameters, to map towards the different QCIs. The first instance, RlfProfileId 0, is the default RLF profile.
The RDNs of this MO type are RlfProfile=0 to RlfProfile=18.
The timers and constants settings are provided to the UE by dedicated signaling.

attribute.name: n310
attribute.description: Maximum number of consecutive "out of sync" indications received from lower layers.
attribute.disturbances: Lowering the value can increase drop rate.

attribute.name: n311
attribute.description: Maximum number of consecutive "in-sync" indications received from lower layers.
attribute.disturbances: Increasing the value can increase drop rate.

attribute.name: t301
attribute.description: UE timer to supervise a response to RRC Connection Reestablishment Request (according to 3GPP TS 36.331), during a radio connection re-establishment procedure. The UE returns to Idle and optionally starts to reconnect over NAS when the timer expires.
attribute.disturbances: Lowering the value can increase drop rate.

attribute.name: t310
attribute.description: Waiting time for radio link failure. Used by the UE.
attribute.disturbances: Lowering the value can increase drop rate.

attribute.name: t311
attribute.description: UE timer triggered at radio link failure to supervise the period where the UE tries to re-establish the radio connection, either by performing RRC Connection Reestablishment (according to 3GPP TS 36.331), or by finding a suitable cell on another RAT. The UE returns to Idle and optionally starts to reconnect over NAS when the timer expires.
attribute.disturbances: Lowering the value can increase drop rate.

attribute.name: rlfProfileId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: reservedBy
attribute.description: Contains a list of QciProfile instances that reserve this MO instance.

class.name: TimerProfile
class.description: Contains internal eNodeB timer profiles to be mapped to different QCIs.

attribute.name: timerProfileId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: reservedBy
attribute.description: Contains a list of managed object instances that reserves this managed object instance.
attribute.dependencies: The MO cannot be deleted if it is reserved.

attribute.name: tWaitForRrcConnReest
attribute.description: Waiting time for the RRC message RRC Connection Reestablishment Request upon detecting Radio Link Failure. Used by the RBS.

attribute.name: tRrcConnectionReconfiguration
attribute.description: Waiting time for the RRC message RRC Connection Reconfiguration Complete. Used by the RBS.

attribute.name: tRrcConnReest
attribute.description: Waiting time for the RRC message RRC Connection Reestablishment Complete. Used by the RBS.

attribute.name: tRelocOverall
attribute.description: Supervision timer of the outgoing S1/X2/intra-eNodeB handover execution procedure according to 3GPP TS 36.413 and TS 36.423. If the feature Multi-Target RRC Connection Re-establishment is active this timer also supervises the Context Fetch procedure.
attribute.disturbances: Low values can stop outgoing HO.

class.name: ResourcePartitions
class.description:
Set of resource partitions defined for use in the node.
The RDN for this MO type is ResourcePartitions=1.

attribute.name: resourcePartitionsId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

class.name: ResourcePartition
class.description: A combination of attributes which specify the resource partition a given UE should be included in.

attribute.name: resourcePartitionId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: partitionName
attribute.description: The name of the resource partition.
attribute.statusInformation: Since L17A. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.

attribute.name: plmnList
attribute.description: Specifies which PLMNs shall be included in the resource partition.
attribute.dependencies: Can only be configured if spidList is empty.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: spidList
attribute.description: Specifies which SPID values shall be included in the resource partition. A partition with a spidList containing the value 0 will include UEs with no defined SPID value. A partition configured with an empty spidList will include all UE's with a spid value not appearing in any other partition in the ResourcePartitionGroup.
attribute.dependencies: Can only be configured if plmnList is empty.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: reservedBy
attribute.description: Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.
attribute.dependencies: The MO may not be deleted if it is reserved.

attribute.name: partitionId
attribute.description: Resource partition ID.
attribute.dependencies: Unique id among all ResourcePartition MOs.

class.name: ResourcePartitionGroup
class.description: Group of resource partitions used together in a cell. All partitions in a group must contain the same empty attribute (plmnList or spidList). Multiple partitions in the same group must not be applicable to the same UE.

attribute.name: resourcePartitionGroupId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: reservedBy
attribute.description: Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.
attribute.dependencies: The MO may not be deleted if it is reserved.

class.name: ResourcePartitionGroupMember
class.description: Specifies a resource partition configuration and the share of resources it should be granted in the cell.

attribute.name: resourcePartitionGroupMemberId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: resourcePartitionRef
attribute.description: Reference to an instance of ResourcePartition MO.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: resourcePartitionShare
attribute.description:
Share of scheduling resources available to a resource partition.
Partitions may use more than their share as long as there are free resources remaining in the cell but in a congested network the additional resources may instead be used to fulfill the shares of other partitions.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

class.name: FlexibleQoSFunction
class.description:
Contains eNB specific configuration used for feature Flexible QoS.
The RDN of this MO type is FlexibleQoSFunction=1.

attribute.name: flexibleQoSFunctionId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

class.name: FlexibleQoSGroup
class.description: Group of members to assign a bearer certain SCI profile. Multiple members in the same group must not be applicable to the same bearer.

attribute.name: flexibleQoSGroupId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: qciProfileRef
attribute.description: Reference to QCI profile MO, QciProfilePredefined or QciProfileOperatorDefined.
attribute.dependencies: Each qciProfileRef attribute in different FlexibleQoSGroup MOCs must be unique. Default QCI profiles cannot be used.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

class.name: FlexibleQoSGroupMember
class.description: Specifies a mapping configuration to decide what SciProfile should be assigned to a bearer.

attribute.name: flexibleQoSGroupMemberId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: userProfileRef
attribute.description: Reference to instance of UserProfile MO.
attribute.dependencies: Each FlexibleQoSGroupMember MO instance in same FlexibleQoSGroup MOC must have unique userProfileRef.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: sciProfileRef
attribute.description: Reference to instance of SciProfile MO.
attribute.dependencies: Default SCI profiles cannot be used.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

class.name: UserProfile
class.description: A combination of attributes specifies which SCI profile a given bearer should be assigned.

attribute.name: userProfileId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: userProfileName
attribute.description: Name of user profile.

attribute.name: spidList
attribute.description: Which SPID values are included in user profile. Empty list means all are included.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: plmnList
attribute.description: Which PLMNs are included in user profile. Empty list means all are included.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: arpList
attribute.description: Which ARP values are included in user profile. Empty list means all are included.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: reservedBy
attribute.description: List of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.
attribute.dependencies: MO can not be deleted if it is reserved.

class.name: SciProfile
class.description:
Contains bearer-level eNB specific QoS configuration used for feature FlexibleQoS. SCI profile can be used only when FlexibleQoS is activated.
The RDNs for this MO type are SciProfile=default, SciProfile=sci1, SciProfile=sci2,.. SciProfile=sci18.

attribute.name: absPrioOverride
attribute.description: Indicates if the data radio bearer is subject to Absolute Priority Override.
attribute.dependencies: Only relevant if the licenses for Flexible QoS and QoS Aware Scheduler are present and active.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: dlMaxWaitingTime
attribute.description: Scheduler attempts to achieve dlMaxWaitingTime for DL bearers before giving any DL bearer a higher priority. Value 0 means that the higher priority is never applied. Must be set to similar or slightly shorter value than PDB. If value set too low, higher priority services can be affected. For more information about PDB refer to TS23.203.
attribute.dependencies: Only used for Resource Fair Scheduling algorithm. Only relevant if licenses for Flexible QoS and Advanced Differentiation for Resource Fair Scheduling are present and active.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect performance of all data bearers. A value that is set too low can affect other services with higher priority. A value that is set too high can cause Dynamic UE Admission Control to fail in keeping the cell stable at overload.

attribute.name: dlMinBitRate
attribute.description: Scheduler attempts to achieve minbitrate for all bearers before giving any user a higher rate. Value 0 means that minRate scheduler is not used.
attribute.dependencies: Parameter is used only if one of the following Proportional Fair scheduling algorithms is selected: "maximum_C_over_I", "proportional_fair_low", "proportional_fair_medium", "proportional_fair_high" or "equal_rate". Only relevant if the licenses for Flexible QoS and QoS Aware Scheduler are present and active.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: dlResourceAllocationStrategy
attribute.description: Defines downlink resource allocation strategy of SCI.
attribute.dependencies: Parameter changes take effect only if the licenses are present and active for the following: Flexible QoS, Downlink Frequency Selective Scheduling and QoS Aware Scheduler.

attribute.name: logicalChannelGroupRef
attribute.description: Refers to an instance of LCG. Assigns LCG to SCI.
attribute.dependencies: Only relevant if the license for Flexible QoS is present and active.

attribute.name: pdb
attribute.description: Contribution from eNodeB to PDB for SCI. Packet delays outside eNodeB are excluded, for example in the transport network. For more information about PDB refer to TS23.203.
attribute.dependencies: Only relevant if the licenses for Flexible QoS and QoS Aware Scheduler are present and active.

attribute.name: priority
attribute.description: SCI-related bearer priority. Refer to priority defined in 3GPP TS 23.203.
attribute.dependencies: Only relevant if the license for Flexible QoS is present and active.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: sci
attribute.description: SCI specifies eNodeB configuration that controls packet-forwarding treatment for bearers. Each MO instance has unique SCI value. Special value: 0 activates default SCI profile. Used for specific bearer with no defined profile.
attribute.dependencies: Each SCI must be unique.

attribute.name: sciProfileId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: dlRelativePriority
attribute.description: The relative priority for DL associated with an SCI.
attribute.dependencies: Changes to this parameter take effect only if the licenses are present and active for: Flexible QoS, QoS Aware Scheduler, Proportional Fair Scheduler, and the Rps.

attribute.name: reservedBy
attribute.description: List of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.
attribute.dependencies: MO can not be deleted if it is reserved.

attribute.name: ulResourceAllocationStrategy
attribute.description: Defines uplink resource allocation strategy of SCI.
attribute.dependencies: Only relevant if the licenses are present and active for: Flexible QoS, Uplink Frequency Selective Scheduling and QoS Aware Scheduler.

attribute.name: schedulingAlgorithm
attribute.description: Scheduling algorithm used for certain SCI.
attribute.dependencies: Only relevant if the licenses for Flexible QoS and QoS Aware Scheduler are present and active. Value DELAY_BASED can only be used if attribute serviceType for a bearer has value VOIP.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: srsAllocationStrategy
attribute.description: If parameter srsAllocationStrategy in QoS configuration for UE DRB is ACTIVATED, then an attempt is made to allocate UE sounding. Algorithm uses priority parameter in QoS configuration to resolve which QoS configuration defines sounding, if several DRBs are setup to UE with different QoS configurations.
attribute.dependencies: Only relevant if the licenses are present and active for: Flexible QoS, QoS Aware Scheduler and frequency selective scheduling.

attribute.name: ulMaxWaitingTime
attribute.description: Scheduler attempts to achieve ulMaxWaitingTime for UL bearers before giving any UL bearer a higher priority. Value 0 means that the higher priority is never applied. Must be set to similar or slightly shorter value than PDB. If value set too low, higher priority services can be affected. For more information about PDB refer to TS23.203.
attribute.dependencies: Only used for Resource Fair Scheduling algorithm. Only relevant if licenses for Flexible QoS and Advanced Differentiation for Resource Fair Scheduler are present and active.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect performance of all data bearers. A value that is set too low can affect other services with higher priority. A value that is set too high can cause Dynamic UE Admission Control to fail in keeping the cell stable at overload.

attribute.name: ulMinBitRate
attribute.description: Scheduler attempts to achieve minbitrate for all bearers before giving any user a higher rate. Value 0 means that minRate scheduler is not used.
attribute.dependencies: Parameter is used only if one of the following Proportional Fair scheduling algorithms is selected: "maximum_C_over_I", "proportional_fair_low", "proportional_fair_medium", "proportional_fair_high" or "equal_rate". Only relevant if licenses for Flexible QoS and QoS Aware Scheduler are present and active.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: ulRelativePriority
attribute.description: The relative priority for UL associated with an SCI.
attribute.dependencies: Parameter changes take effect only if the licenses are present and active for: Flexible QoS, QoS Aware Scheduler, Proportional Fair Scheduler, and RPS.

attribute.name: lessMaxDelayThreshold

attribute.name: spidTriggerList

Multiple values indicates UE must fulfill at least one of them for the trigger to evaluate to TRUE. The value 0 matches all UEs without any assigned SPID. Note: For a UE to be part of this subscriber group, it must be evaluated to true in these trigger lists: spidTriggerList, bearerTriggerList and customTriggerList. If all three arrays are empty, all UEs match. If all lists are not empty, UE must match at least one value in each list.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: bearerTriggerList
attribute.description: Bearer parameters included in subscriber profile. Evaluated for a UE when a bearer is added, modified or released. If empty, all bearers are included. One element indicates that only that set of bearer parameters makes the trigger evaluate to TRUE. Multiple elements indicate a bearer needs to fulfill at least one of them for the trigger to evaluate to TRUE. For a UE to be part of this subscriber group, it must be evaluated to true in these trigger lists: spidTriggerList, bearerTriggerList and customTriggerList. If all three arrays are empty, all UEs match. If all lists are not empty, UE must match at least one value in each list.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: customTriggerList

class.name: PmEventService
class.description: This MO contains the parameters for Performance Monitoring (PM) event handling functions.

attribute.name: cellTraceHighPrioReserve
attribute.description:
The percentage of total cell trace storage (totalCellTraceStorageSize) reserved for high-priority scanners.
This means that no events from low-priority scanners are stored in the file when the storage limit is reached for the sum of the low-priority scanners:
totalCellTraceStorageSize - (cellTraceHighPrioReserv / 100) * totalCellTraceStorageSize.
High-priority scanner files are not limited to the reserved area for high priority scanners. These files can also be stored in the non-reserved area together with the low-priority scanner files. When the default value of zero is set, the high- and low-priority share the totalCellTraceStorageSize for storing cell trace events.

attribute.name: totalCellTraceStorageSize
attribute.description: Total available storage for the cell trace recording files. The actual limit may be slightly offset from this value due to the fact that the compressed file size is approximated by the system.
attribute.dependencies: totalCellTraceStorageSize >= cellTraceFileSize AND totalCellTraceStorageSize <= totalEventStorageSize

attribute.name: cellTraceFileSize
attribute.description:
cellTraceFileSize is calculated basing on compression factor equal to 8. In some outstanding conditions it is possible that the maximum size could exceed definition in MOM attribute, depending of content of ROP file.
If the cellTraceFileSize is reached within a specific Reporting Output Period (ROP), cell trace recording stops until the next ROP begins.
attribute.dependencies: cellTraceFileSize <= totalCellTraceStorageSize

attribute.name: totalEventStorageSize
attribute.description: The total storage that the observability mechanisms can use to store information about the collected event data. This means that the total size of the cell trace and UE trace files stored should be less than the value of this attribute. The actual limit may be slightly offset from this value due to the fact that the compressed file size is approximated by the system.
attribute.dependencies: totalEventStorageSize >= totalCellTraceStorageSize + totalUeTraceStorageSize

attribute.name: ueTraceFileSize
attribute.description:
ueTraceFileSize is calculated basing on compression factor equal to 8. In some outstanding conditions it is possible that the maximum size could exceed definition in MOM attribute, depending of content of ROP file.
If ueTraceFileSize is reached during ROP, UE trace recording stops until next ROP.
attribute.dependencies: ueTraceFileSize <= totalUeTraceStorageSize

attribute.name: pmEventServiceId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: totalUeTraceStorageSize
attribute.description: Total available storage for UE trace recording files. Actual limit can differ slightly from value because system approximates compressed file size.
attribute.dependencies: totalUeTraceStorageSize >= ueTraceFileSize AND totalUeTraceStorageSize <= totalEventStorageSize.

attribute.name: hysteresisPm
attribute.description: The hysteresis value for the condition triggering the entering and leaving measurement report for PM-Initiated UE Measurements. Used only when measSelectionEUtraPm is set to EVENT_A1, EVENT_A2, EVENT_A3, EVENT_A4 or EVENT_A5.

attribute.name: timeToTriggerPm
attribute.description: Time during which specific event criteria must be met to trigger a measurement report for PM-Initiated UE Measurements. Used only when measSelectionEUtraPm is set to EVENT_A1, EVENT_A2, EVENT_A3, EVENT_A4 or EVENT_A5.

attribute.name: reportQuantityPm
attribute.description:
The quantities to include in the measurement report for PM-Initiated UE Measurements.
The value 0, sameAsTriggerQuantity, means that the same quantity as triggerQuantityPm is included in the measurement report.
The value 1, both, means that both Reference Signal Received Power (RSRP) and Reference Signal Received Quality (RSRQ) quantities are included in the measurement report.

attribute.name: maxReportCellsPm
attribute.description: Maximum number of cells to include in the measurement report for the PM Initiated UE Measurements.

attribute.name: reportIntervalPm
attribute.description: The interval for event-triggered periodical reporting for PM-Initiated UE Measurements.

attribute.name: reportAmountPm
attribute.description: The number of periodical reports for PM-Initiated UE Measurements. Value 0 means that reports are sent as long as the event is fulfilled.

attribute.name: reservedBy
attribute.description: Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.
attribute.dependencies: The managed object cannot be deleted if it is reserved.

attribute.name: reportConfigEUtraIntraFreqPmId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

class.name: UeMeasControl
class.description: Models the manageable characteristics for UE measurements.

attribute.name: ueMeasControlId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: sMeasure
attribute.description:
Primary cell (PCell) quality threshold controlling whether or not the UE is required to perform measurements of intra-frequency, inter-frequency and inter-RAT neighboring cells.
Value "0" indicates to disable s-Measure.
Corresponds to s-Measure in TS 36.331.
attribute.disturbances: High values can stop outgoing HO.

attribute.name: filterCoefficientEUtraRsrp
attribute.description: The filtering coefficient for E-UTRA using the measured quantity Reference Signal Received Power (RSRP). The coefficient filters measurements before event evaluation.

attribute.name: filterCoefficientEUtraRsrq
attribute.description: The filtering coefficient for E-UTRA using the measured quantity Reference Signal Received Quality (RSRQ). The coefficient filters measurements before event evaluation.

attribute.name: ueMeasurementsActive
attribute.description: Activates or deactivates A3/A5/B2 measurements on EUTRAN inter-frequencies and on GERAN, UTRAN, CDMA2000 HRPD and CDMA2000 1xRtt frequencies for mobility purposes. This attribute also activates or deactivates A4/B1 measurements on EUTRAN inter-frequencies, GERAN and UTRAN frequencies for soft lock of cell purposes. Note that this parameter has no effect when feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage is enabled.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute to false can cause loss of traffic. Blocks outgoing measurement-based IF and IRAT mobility.

attribute.name: a5B2MobilityTimer
attribute.description: Length of time the eNodeB waits for reports from A3/A5/B2 measurements configured in UE for mobility reasons. If 0, timer is not started. If ULTRIG is enabled, timer is also applicable for UL-triggered measurements.

attribute.name: maxMeasInterFreqEUtra
attribute.description: The number of measurements that can be concurrently performed by the UE on E-UTRA frequencies other than the serving cell frequency.

attribute.name: maxMeasEUtraOther
attribute.description: The number of measurements that can be concurrently performed by the UE on E-UTRA frequencies of a type (FDD - TDD) other than the serving cell frequency.

attribute.name: maxMeasGeran
attribute.description: The number of measurements that can be concurrently performed by the UE on GERAN measurement objects.

attribute.name: maxMeasUtraFdd
attribute.description: The number of measurements that can be concurrently performed by the UE on UTRA FDD measurement objects.

attribute.name: maxMeasCdma2000eHrpd
attribute.description: The number of measurements that can be concurrently performed by the UE on CDMA2000 eHRPD measurement objects.

attribute.name: measQuantityUtraFDD
attribute.description: Measurement quantity used for all types of UTRA FDD measurements.
