attribute.name: maxMeasUtraTdd
attribute.description: The number of measurements that can be concurrently performed by the UE on UTRA TDD measurement objects.

attribute.name: maxUtranCellsToMeasure
attribute.description: Defines the maximal number of UTRAN cells to perform mobility measurements upon.

attribute.name: csfbHoTargetSearchTimer
attribute.description: Length of time the eNodeB waits for reports from B1 and B2 measurements configured in the UE for CS Fallback reasons.

attribute.name: maxMeasCdma20001xRtt
attribute.description: Number of measurements that can be concurrently performed by the UE on CDMA2000 1xRTT measurement objects

attribute.name: ueMeasurementsActiveIF
attribute.description: Activates or deactivates EUTRAN inter-frequency measurements for mobility and soft lock of cells purposes when feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage is enabled.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute to false can cause loss of traffic. Blocks measurement based IF mobility.

attribute.name: ueMeasurementsActiveUTRAN
attribute.description: Activates or deactivates UTRAN measurements for mobility and soft lock of cells purposes when feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage is enabled.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute to false can cause loss of traffic. Blocks measurement based mobility to UTRAN.

attribute.name: ueMeasurementsActiveGERAN
attribute.description: Activates or deactivates GERAN measurements for mobility and soft lock of cells purposes when feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage is enabled.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute to false can cause loss of traffic. Blocks measurement based mobility to GERAN.

attribute.name: ueMeasurementsActiveCDMA2000
attribute.description: Activates or deactivates CDMA2000 measurements for mobility purposes when Mobility Control at Poor Coverage feature is enabled.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute to false can cause loss of traffic. Blocks measurement based mobility to CDMA2000.

attribute.name: allowReleaseQci1
attribute.description: This attribute specifies whether or not blind and measurement-based Release of a User Equipment (UE) with a QCI1 bearer is allowed.

attribute.name: searchEffortTime
attribute.description: Time used in feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage to determine if measured frequencies must be excluded for mobility action at critical threshold. Special value: 0 means infinity. If ULTRIG is enabled, timer is also applicable for UL-triggered measurements.

attribute.name: ueMeasurementsActiveCDMA20001xRtt
attribute.description: Activates or deactivates CDMA 1xRtt measurements for mobility purposes when Mobility Control at Poor Coverage feature is enabled.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute to false can cause loss of traffic. Blocks measurement based mobility to CDMA 1xRtt.

attribute.name: servOrPrioIFHoTimer
attribute.description: The length of time the eNodeB waits for measurement reports from the UE in the feature Service or Priority-triggered inter-freq Handover.

attribute.name: inhibitB2RsrqConfig
attribute.description: Disables or enables configuration of B2-RSRQ if event A2Search-RSRQ is triggered when the UE enters the search zone.
attribute.dependencies: This attribute is only effective when feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage is activated.

attribute.name: lowPrioMeasThresh
attribute.description: Frequency priority threshold to specify the low priority measurement group from connectedModeMobilityPrio or voicePrio in search zone. Those less than this threshold are put in low priority measurement group and can be configured after event A2OuterSearch is triggered from UE.
attribute.dependencies: Feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage must be active.

attribute.name: excludeInterFreqAtCritical
attribute.description: If set, E-UTRA Inter-frequencies must be excluded when eNodeB selects the highest priority frequency at A2Critical.
attribute.dependencies: Feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage must be active.

attribute.name: bothA5RsrpRsrqCheck
attribute.description: This attribute is used to turn on/off the functionality for checking the second value - RSRP or RSRQ - in an A5 Target Good Enough measurement report triggered by RSRQ or RSRP respectively.
attribute.dependencies: Feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage must be active.

attribute.name: filterCoefficientEUtraUlSinrMax
attribute.description: Filtering coefficient for the UE UL-normalized Signal-to-Noise-Max measurements in eNodeB. The coefficient filters measurements before event evaluation.

attribute.name: maxNoMeasReportsInact
attribute.description: Maximal value of reports that any UE must provide any system functions, based on periodical measurements, that are used to measure on EUtran, Utran and Geran neighbors. Special Value: 0 means infinity.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect UE battery consumption and user throughput.

attribute.name: filterCoefficientEUtraNI
attribute.description: Filtering coefficient for noise and interference value measure in eNodeB and used in calculation of uplink SINR. Coefficient filters noise and interference samples used to compare uplink quality in source and potential target cell. The filter coefficient assumes a sample period of 200ms.

attribute.name: targetA2UlSearchOffset
attribute.description: Offset value above a1a2UlSearchThreshold that UL SINR in target cell must reach for handover to be allowed. Used when feature Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is enabled. Configured in target cell.

attribute.name: ulSinrOffset
attribute.description: Offset value above UL SINR in source cell that estimated UL SINR in target cell must reach for handover to be allowed. Used when feature UL-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is enabled. Configured in source cell.

attribute.name: a3SuspendCsgTimer
attribute.description: The length of time the eNodeB discards A3 measurement report for CSG or Hybrid CSG cells from UE. If 0, timer is not started.

class.name: UtraNetwork
class.description: This managed object represents a Utra network.

attribute.name: utraNetworkId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use.

class.name: UtranFreqRelation
class.description:
This Managed Object represents a UTRAN FDD mobility relation between a EUtranCellFDD or EUtranCellTDD and an UtranFrequency. It contains parameters that are specific for this relation.
Deleting this MO while the parent EUtranCellFDD/EUtranCellTDD has operationalState set to ENABLED is not recommended as it may affect traffic.

action.name: setMaxNrUtranCellRelations
action.description: This MO action is used for setting the maximum number of UtranCellRelations per UtranFreqRelation. This action will remove UtranCellRelations so the number of relations goes down to the value of MaxNrUtranCellRelation. Relations that were latest used are kept.

parameter.name: maxNrUtranCellRelations
parameter.description: This specifies the maximum number of UtranCellRelations.

action.disturbances: Executing this action can cause loss of traffic. Lowering the value can remove relations.

attribute.name: anrMeasOn
attribute.description: ANR performs measurement on the referenced frequency if this parameter is set to true. Otherwise, ANR does not perform any measurements on this frequency.

attribute.name: utranFreqRelationId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use.

attribute.name: utranFrequencyRef
attribute.description: Reference to the UTRAN frequency MO, UtranFreq.

attribute.name: threshXHigh
attribute.description: The threshold used by the UE when reselecting towards a higher priority frequency from the current serving frequency. Each UTRAN frequency may have a specific threshold. The threshold is specified as parameter Thresx,high in 3GPP TS 36.304.

attribute.name: threshXLow
attribute.description: The threshold used in reselection towards a lower frequency priority from a higher priority frequency. Each frequency of UTRAN may have a specific threshold. The threshold is specified as parameter Thresx,low in 3GPP TS 36.304.

attribute.name: qRxLevMin
attribute.description: The required minimum received Rx level in the UTRAN frequency used in cell reselection. Corresponds to parameter Qrxlevmin in 3GPP TS 36.304.

attribute.name: pMaxUtra
attribute.description: Used to calculate the parameter Pcompensation (defined in 3GPP TS 36.304) at cell reselection to a UTRAN cell.

attribute.name: qQualMin
attribute.description: Minimum required quality level in the cell (dB). Corresponds to parameter Qqualmin in 3GPP TS 25.304

attribute.name: cellReselectionPriority
attribute.description:
The absolute priority of the carrier frequency used by the cell reselection procedure. Corresponds to parameter priority in 3GPP TS 36.304.
Value 0 means lowest priority. The UE behavior when the field is empty if applicable, is specified in 3GPP TS 36.304.
attribute.dependencies: The value must be unique and not already used by other RAT, i.e. equal priorities between RATs are not supported.

attribute.name: allowedPlmnList
attribute.description:
List of all Public Land Mobile Network (PLMN) IDs allowed for this frequency relation.
A UE that does not support one of the IDs included in the allowedPlmnList does not measure on this frequency, according to the UE Handover Restriction List.
No values in allowedPlmnList imply that the frequency has no restrictions for PLMN.
The PLMN ID contains the following parts: 1. MobileCountryCode, MCC, 3 digits 2. MobileNetworkCode, MNC, 2 or 3 digits (the correct number of digits is set in the mncLength member of this Struct)
For example, if MCC=125 and MNC=46, then plmnId=12546.

attribute.name: csFallbackPrio
attribute.description: Prioritizes UTRAN frequencies among all frequencies related to the cell for UEs in connected mode. Sets the priority to which frequency/frequency group to make CS Fallback to. The value -1 means the frequency is excluded. The value 0 means the lowest priority. The value 7 means the highest priority.

attribute.name: connectedModeMobilityPrio
attribute.description: Prioritizes UTRA frequencies among all frequencies related to the cell for UEs in connected mode. (0 means the lowest priority. -1 means the frequency is excluded.)

attribute.name: qOffsetFreq
attribute.description: Indicates a frequency-specific offset to apply when evaluating triggering conditions for measurement reporting.

attribute.name: csFallbackPrioEC
attribute.description: Prioritizes UTRAN frequencies for emergency calls among all frequencies/frequency groups related to the cell for UEs in connected mode. Sets the priority to which frequency to make emergency call CS Fallback to. The value -1 means the frequency is excluded. The value 0 means the lowest priority. The value 7 means the highest priority.

attribute.name: mobilityAction
attribute.description: The preferred way to transfer a UE in connected mode to a UTRAN FDD frequency in case of coverage triggered mobility.

attribute.name: mobilityActionCsfb
attribute.description: The preferred way to transfer a UE in connected mode to a UTRAN FDD frequency in case of CS Fallback.

attribute.name: threshXHighQ
attribute.description:
Specifies the quality level threshold used by the UE when reselecting towards a higher priority UTRA frequency than the current serving frequency.
Corresponds to ThreshX, HighQ in 3GPP TS 36.304
attribute.dependencies: This parameter is included in SIB6 if the threshServingLowQ in SIB3 is included in systemInformationBlockType3.

attribute.name: threshXLowQ
attribute.description:
Specifies the quality level threshold used by the UE when reselecting towards a lower priority UTRA frequency than the current serving frequency.
Corresponds to ThreshX, LowQ in 3GPP TS 36.304
attribute.dependencies: This parameter is included in SIB6 if the threshServingLowQ in SIB3 is included in systemInformationBlockType3.

attribute.name: voicePrio
attribute.description: Prioritizes UTRAN frequencies among all frequencies related to the cell for UEs in connected mode. Sets the priority to which frequency to perform mobility to for a voice session. The value -1 means the frequency is excluded. The value 0 means the lowest priority. The value 7 means the highest priority.

attribute.name: utranFreqToQciProfileRelation
attribute.description: QCI profile relation The attribute encapsulates parameters for service specific load management for specific QCI profiles.

attribute.name: lbBnrPolicy
attribute.description: Specifies the policy for updating the loadBalancing attribute by the feature Best Neighbor Relations for WCDMA IRAT Offload. The policy is valid for all cell relations corresponding to this UtranFreqRelation.

attribute.name: maxNrUtranCellRelations
attribute.description: This parameter specifies the maximum number of UtranCellRelations per UtranFreqRelation. The value is set by the action with name SetMaxNrUtranCellRelations.

attribute.name: altCsfbTargetPrio
attribute.description: Prioritizes UTRAN frequencies among all frequencies related to the cell for UEs in connected mode. Sets the priority to the alternative target frequency/frequency group to which to make release with redirect when measurement or handover to selected target fails. Value -1 means the frequency is excluded. Value 0 means the lowest priority. Value 7 means the highest priority.

attribute.name: altCsfbTargetPrioEc
attribute.description: Prioritizes UTRAN frequencies for emergency calls among all frequencies related to the cell for UEs in connected mode. Sets the priority to the alternative target frequency/frequency group to which to make release with redirect when measurement or handover to selected target fails for emergency calls. Value -1 means the frequency is excluded. Value 0 means the lowest priority. Value 7 means the highest priority.

attribute.name: b2Thr1RsrpUtraFreqOffset
attribute.description: The frequency-relation specific offset for the absolute threshold b2Threshold1Rsrp, RSRP threshold1 for event B2, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility.

attribute.name: b2Thr1RsrqUtraFreqOffset
attribute.description: The frequency-relation specific offset for the absolute threshold b2Threshold1Rsrq, RSRQ threshold1 for event B2, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility.

attribute.name: b2Thr2EcNoUtraFreqOffset
attribute.description: The frequency-relation specific offset for the absolute threshold b2Threshold2EcNo, Ratio of energy for each modulation bit to noise spectral density in the ThresholdUTRA for event B2, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility.

attribute.name: b2Thr2RscpUtraFreqOffset
attribute.description: The frequency-relation specific offset for the absolute threshold b2Threshold2Rscp, RSCP in the ThresholdUTRA for event B2, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility.

attribute.name: atoAllowed
attribute.description: Specifies whether Admission-triggered offload (ATO) is activated from the current cell towards a certain UTRAN frequency.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: b2UtranOffsetPerPC
attribute.description: The frequency-relation specific offset for the absolute threshold, RSRP threshold1 for event B2, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility and High Power UE.

class.name: UtranFrequency
class.description: This Managed Object contains information of a specific Utran frequency.

attribute.name: utranFrequencyId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: reservedBy
attribute.description: Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use.

attribute.name: arfcnValueUtranDl
attribute.description: Indicates the ARFCN applicable for a downlink UTRA carrier frequency, as defined in 3GPP TS 25.331. Allowed ARFCN values are specified in 3GPP TS 25.101 (UTRAN FDD) and 3GPP TS 25.102 (UTRAN TDD).

class.name: Paging
class.description: Contains the configuration parameters for the Paging function in the RBS and applies to all the cells.

attribute.name: pagingId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: maxNoOfPagingRecords
attribute.description: The maximum allowed number of paging records included in one Radio Resource Control (RRC) paging message. It is the allowed maximum number of UE that can be paged per paging occasion.
attribute.takesEffect: After all the cells in the RBS have been locked, and subsequently been unlocked.

attribute.name: defaultPagingCycle
attribute.description: Paging cycle (T). Used by RBS and broadcast in system information type 2. UE-specific DRX cycle overrides defaultPagingCycle if UE-specific DRX cycle is provided in S1AP paging. If extended Idle Mode DRX feature is active, paging cycle can be extended up to 262144 radio frames.
attribute.dependencies: Parameter modificationPeriodCoeff * defaultPagingCycle must be equal or less than 1024 radio frames.
attribute.takesEffect: After all the cells in the RBS have been locked, and subsequently been unlocked.

attribute.name: nB
attribute.description:
Used to calculate the number and position of Paging Occasions (PO) and Paging Frames (PF).
The numerical value of nB depends on the value of the defaultPagingCycle (T) and can be set to one of the following values: 4T, 2T, T, T/2, T/4, T/8, T/16, T/32.
When nB is set to T, 2T or 4T, it determines the number of POs per PF, and the PO position in PF.
When nB is set to a value smaller than T, it affects the System Frame Number of the PF, the position of PO in the PF, and also distribution of UE into groups with the same PF.
When nB is set to smaller value, amount of groups is smaller, but amount of UEs inside each groups is larger. When nB is set to a larger value, amount of groups is larger but amount of UEs inside each groups is smaller.
If categoryMAccess is enabled and nBBr is set to the default value (NOT_PRESENT) then further restrictions apply. If highestSupportedCeLevelBr = 0 then nB should be selected from the following available options (T, T/2, T/4, T/8, T/16, T/32) due to the half duplex nature of Cat-M devices. If highestSupportedCeLevelBr = 1 then nB should be selected from the following available options (T/8, T/16, T/32) due to repetitions.
attribute.dependencies: nB=T4 can not be used in combination with specialSubframePattern = 5 on MO EUtranCellTDD, see 3GPP TS 36.213.
attribute.takesEffect: After all the cells in the RBS have been locked, and subsequently been unlocked.

attribute.name: pagingDiscardTimer
attribute.description: The length of time a received paging is retained or queued in the RBS before it is discarded. The timer should be set to the same (or smaller) value as the paging resend timer in MME (T3413). This setting prevents the RBS from retaining or sending an old paging after the re-sent copy is received from the MME.
attribute.statusInformation: Since 17.Q4. Replaced by pagingDiscardTimerDrx. Planned to be removed.
attribute.takesEffect: After all the cells in the RBS have been locked, and subsequently been unlocked.

attribute.name: noOfDefPagCyclPrim
attribute.description: Number of consecutive "DefaultPagingCycles" in which paging for Earthquake and Tsunami Warning System (ETWS) Primary Notification shall be transmitted in the RBS.

attribute.name: nBBr
attribute.description:
Used to calculate the number and position of Paging Occasions (PO) and Paging Frames (PF) for Bandwidth reduced (Br) UEs.
The numerical value of nBBr depends on the value of the defaultPagingCycle (T) and can be set to one of the following values: T/64, T/128, T/256 and NOT_PRESENT.
The value of nBBr affects the System Frame Number of the PF, the position of PO in the PF, and also distribution of UE into groups with the same PF.
When nBBr is set to smaller value, amount of groups is smaller, but amount of UEs inside each group is larger. When nBBr is set to a larger value, amount of groups is larger but amount of UEs inside each group is smaller. nBBr should have such value that it is always >=1 , i.e. if T=128 then nBBr >= T/128, meaning that there should be at least 1 paging group (TS 36.304).
When nBBr is set to NOT_PRESENT the attribute is not used and instead nB value is used to calculate PF and PO for the CAT-M1 users.
nBBr values T, T/2, T/4, T/8, T/16, T/32 are not allowed.
attribute.disturbances: Setting unallowed value, described as "Undefined value" in enumeration NBValueBr, can cause loss of all traffic in the eNodeB.

attribute.name: defaultPagingCycleNbIot
attribute.description: NB IoT paging cycle (also called T) used by RBS and broadcast in NB-SIB2. For defaultPagingCycle 128, numRepetitionsPaging must not exceed 512. For defaultPagingCycle 256, numRepetitionsPaging must not exceed 1024.
attribute.takesEffect: After all the cells in the RBS have been locked, and subsequently been unlocked

attribute.name: nBNbIot
attribute.description: Used to calculate number and position of NB IoT PO and NB IoT PF. When nBNbIot is set to T, it determines PO number for each PF, and PO position in PF. When nBNbIot is smaller than T, it affects System Frame Number of PF, PO position in PF, and UE distribution into groups with same PF. nBNbIot values of T2 and T4 are not allowed, as they result in grouping issues for paging occasions. T2 and T4 are converted to T.

attribute.name: numRepetitionsPagingNbIot
attribute.description: Maximum number of repetitions for NPDCCH common search space (CSS) for paging. Provided in NB-SIB2.
attribute.statusInformation: Since 17.Q4. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.

attribute.name: pagingDiscardTimerNb
attribute.description: The time a received paging for NB-IoT is retained or queued in the RBS before it is discarded. Set to the same (or smaller) value as the paging resend timer in MME to prevent the RBS from retaining or sending an old paging after the re-sent copy is received from the MME.
attribute.statusInformation: Since 17.Q4. Replaced by pagingDiscardTimerDrxNb. Planned to be removed.
attribute.takesEffect: After all the cells in the RBS have been locked, and subsequently been unlocked.

attribute.name: maxNoOfPagingRecordsNb
attribute.description: The maximum allowed number of NB-IoT paging records included in one Radio Resource Control (RRC) paging message. It is the allowed maximum number of UE that can be paged per paging occasion.
attribute.takesEffect: After all the cells in the RBS have been locked, and subsequently been unlocked.

attribute.name: pagingDiscardTimerDrx
attribute.description: The length of time a received paging is retained or queued in the RBS before it is discarded. The timer should be set to the same (or smaller) value as the paging resend timer in MME (T3413). This setting prevents the RBS from retaining or sending an old paging after the re-sent copy is received from the MME.
attribute.takesEffect: After all the cells in the RBS have been locked, and subsequently been unlocked.

attribute.name: pagingDiscardTimerDrxNb
attribute.description: The length of time a received NB-IoT paging is retained or queued in the RBS before it is discarded. The timer should be set to the same (or smaller) value as the NB-IoT paging resend timer in MME (T3413). This setting prevents the RBS from retaining or sending an old paging after the re-sent copy is received from the MME.

attribute.name: pagingDiscardTimerEdrxNb
attribute.description: The time a received eDRX paging for NB-IoT is retained or queued in the RBS before it is discarded. Set to the same (or smaller) value as the paging resend timer in MME to prevent the RBS from retaining or sending an old paging after the re-sent copy is received from the MME.
attribute.takesEffect: After all the cells in the RBS have been locked, and subsequently been unlocked.

attribute.name: pagingDiscardTimerEdrx
attribute.description: The time a received eDRX paging is retained or queued in the RBS before it is discarded. Set to the same (or smaller) value as the paging resend timer in MME to prevent the RBS from retaining or sending an old paging after the re-sent copy is received from the MME.
attribute.takesEffect: After all the cells in the RBS have been locked, and subsequently been unlocked.

class.name: Rcs
class.description: This MO models the manageable characteristics of the Radio Connection Supervision functionality.

attribute.name: rcsId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: tInactivityTimer
attribute.description:
The time a UE can be inactive before it is released.
86400s = 24 hours
Special values: 0 is used to turn off the use of this timer. This means that a UE will not be released due to inactivity.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: rlcDlDeliveryFailureAction
attribute.description: Attribute controls the action when there is an RLC DL Delivery failure on a DRB in a connection. The action can be set to: - always make an UE Context release - resume the connection if higher ARP prioritized DRBs exist to get better retainability If there is RLC Delivery failure on SRB or on the DRB used for IMS Signaling (indicated by ServiceType in QciProfileOperatorDefined/QciProfilePredefined), the design base behavior applies. In this case, eNodeB triggers a UE Context Release regardless of the value of attribute rlcDlDeliveryFailureAction.
attribute.dependencies: If this attribute is not set to UE_CONTEXT_RELEASE, the behavior depends on: - ARP priority - ServiceType attribute
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic if the value is not set to make a UE context release. When there is a RLC DL Delivery failure on one of several DRBs of a UE, the DRB may be marked as failed and the other DRBs are then retained. The marked DRB cannot be used after the failure until a handover or an RRC Connection Re-establishment initiated by the UE is successful.

attribute.name: tInactivityTimerBr
attribute.description:
Time a Bandwidth reduced UE can be inactive before it is released.
86400s = 24 hours. Special values: 0 turns timer off. If so, UEs are not released due to inactivity.

class.name: SecurityHandling
class.description: Models the manageable characteristics of the security handling except security handling during X2 handover and S1 handover. These characteristics are then used by all instances of the RRC dedicated protocol.

attribute.name: securityHandlingId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: countWrapSupervisionActive
attribute.description: Parameter for controlling whether or not to supervise if COUNT-C is about to wrap.

attribute.name: rbIdSupervisionActive
attribute.description: Controls supervision when the same radio bearer ID with the same set of parameters occurs in the ciphering algorithm.

attribute.name: cipheringAlgoPrio
attribute.description: An array specifying the ciphering algorithms that should be allowed and their priority order. The array has a maximum length of 4 and a minimum length of 1. The algorithm in index zero has the highest priority. Each algorithm shall be written only once in the array.

attribute.name: integrityProtectAlgoPrio
attribute.description: An array specifying the integrity protection algorithms that should be allowed and their priority order. The array has a maximum length of 3 and a minimum length of 1. The algorithm in index zero has the highest priority. Each algorithm shall be written only once in the array.

class.name: GeraNetwork
class.description: This managed object represents a Gera network.

attribute.name: geraNetworkId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use.

class.name: GeranFreqGroup
class.description: This managed object contains information about a set of Geran ARFCN values, which represent a group of Geran frequencies. It is not possible to include Geran frequencies from both band 1800 and 1900 within the same GeranFreqGroup.

attribute.name: geranFreqGroupId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use.

attribute.name: reservedBy
attribute.description: Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.
attribute.dependencies: The MO may not be deleted if it is reserved.

attribute.name: frequencyGroupId
attribute.description: This ID identifies the GeranFreqGroup in the network.

class.name: GeranFreqGroupRelation
class.description:
This Managed Object represents a mobility relation between an EUtranCellFDD or an EUtranCellTDD and a GeranFreqGroup. It contains parameters that are specific for this relation.
Deleting this MO while the parent EUtranCellFDD/EUtranCellTDD has operationalState set to ENABLED is not recommended as it may affect traffic.

attribute.name: geranFreqGroupRelationId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use.

attribute.name: geranFreqGroupRef
attribute.description: Reference to the GERAN frequency group MO, GeranFreqGroup.

attribute.name: qRxLevMin
attribute.description: The required minimum received Rx level in the GERAN frequency used in cell reselection. Corresponds to parameter Qrxlevmin in 3GPP TS 36.304.

attribute.name: pMaxGeran
attribute.description: Calculates the parameter Pcompensation (defined in 3GPP TS 36.304) at cell reselection to a GERAN cell. Value 1000 means the parameter is not included in system information.

attribute.name: threshXHigh
attribute.description: The threshold used by the UE when reselecting towards a higher priority frequency from the current serving frequency. Each frequency of GERAN may have a specific threshold. Corresponds to parameter Thresx,high in 3GPP TS 36.304.

attribute.name: threshXLow
attribute.description: The threshold used by UE when reselecting towards a lower priority frequency from the current serving frequency. Corresponds to parameter Thresx,low in 3GPP TS 36.304.

attribute.name: nccPermitted
attribute.description:
Field encoded as a bit map.
Bit N is set to 0 if a BCCH carrier with NCC = N-1 is not permitted for monitoring.
Bit N is set to 1 if the BCCH carrier with NCC = N-1 is permitted for monitoring.
Bit N = 1 to 8; bit 1 of the bitmap is the leading bit of the bit string.

attribute.name: cellReselectionPriority
attribute.description: Absolute priority of the radio access technology. 0 means lowest priority. Corresponds to parameter priority in 3GPP TS 36.304.
attribute.dependencies: The value must be unique and not already used by other RAT, i.e. equal priorities between RATs are not supported.

attribute.name: allowedPlmnList
attribute.description:
Lists all Public Land Mobile Network (PLMN) IDs allowed for this frequency relation.
A UE that does not support one of the IDs included in allowedPlmnList does not measure on this frequency, according to the UE Handover Restriction List.
No values in the list imply that the frequency has no restrictions for PLMN.
The PLMN identity contains the following parts: 1. MobileCountryCode, MCC, 3 digits 2. MobileNetworkCode, MNC, 2 or 3 digits (the correct number of digits is set in the mncLength member of this Struct)
For example, if MCC=125 and MNC=46, then plmnId=12546.

attribute.name: csFallbackPrio
attribute.description: Prioritizes GERAN Frequency group among all frequencies related to the cell for UEs in connected mode. Sets the priority to which frequency/frequency group to make CS Fallback to. The value -1 means the frequency is excluded. The value 0 means the lowest priority. The value 7 means the highest priority.

attribute.name: connectedModeMobilityPrio
attribute.description: Prioritizes GERAN frequencies among all frequencies related to the cell for UEs in connected mode. (0 means the lowest priority. -1 means the frequency is excluded.)

attribute.name: qOffsetFreq
attribute.description: Indicates a frequency-specific offset to apply when evaluating triggering conditions for measurement reporting.

attribute.name: csFallbackPrioEC
attribute.description: Prioritizes GERAN Frequency group among all frequencies/frequency groups for emergency calls related to the cell for UEs in connected mode. Sets the priority to which frequency group to make emergency call CS Fallback to. The value -1 means the frequency is excluded. The value 0 means the lowest priority. The value 7 means the highest priority.

attribute.name: mobilityActionCsfb
attribute.description: The preferred way to transfer a UE in connected mode to a GERAN frequency group in case of CS Fallback.

attribute.name: mobilityAction
attribute.description: The preferred way to transfer a UE in connected mode to a GERAN frequency group in case of coverage triggered mobility.

attribute.name: anrMeasOn
attribute.description: ANR performs measurement on the referenced frequency if this parameter is set to true. Otherwise, ANR does not perform any measurements on this frequency.

attribute.name: voicePrio
attribute.description: This attribute prioritizes GERAN frequencies among all frequencies related to the cell for User Equipments (UEs) in connected mode. It sets the priority for which frequency to perform mobility to for a voice session. The value -1 means the frequency is excluded. The value 0 means the lowest priority. The value 7 means the highest priority.

attribute.name: altCsfbTargetPrio
attribute.description: Prioritizes the GERAN frequency group among all frequencies related to the cell for UEs in connected mode. Sets the priority to the alternative target frequency/frequency group to which to make release with redirect, when measurement or handover to selected target fails. Value -1 means the frequency is excluded. Value 0 means the lowest priority. Value 7 means the highest priority.

attribute.name: altCsfbTargetPrioEc
attribute.description: Prioritizes the GERAN frequency group for emergency calls among all frequencies related to the cell for UEs in connected mode. Sets the priority to the alternative target frequency/frequency group to which to make release with redirect to, when measurement or handover to selected target fails for emergency calls. Value -1 means the frequency is excluded. Value 0 means the lowest priority. Value 7 means the highest priority.

attribute.name: b2Thr1RsrpGeranFreqOffset
attribute.description: The frequency group relation specific offset for the absolute threshold b2Threshold1Rsrp, RSRP threshold1 value for event B2, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility.

attribute.name: b2Thr1RsrqGeranFreqOffset
attribute.description: The frequency group relation specific offset for the absolute threshold b2Threshold1Rsrq, RSRQ threshold1 value for event B2, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility.

attribute.name: b2Thr2GeranFreqOffset
attribute.description: The frequency group relation specific offset for the absolute threshold b2Threshold2Geran, Signal quality in the ThresholdGERAN for event B2, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility.

attribute.name: qciB2ThrOffsets
attribute.description: Parameters for adding QCI profile and frequency relation specific offsets to B2 threshold values used for mobility decisions. Applicable if Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility (MLSTM) is active.

attribute.name: b2GeranOffsetPerPC
attribute.description: The frequency group relation specific offset for the absolute threshold, RSRP/RSRQ threshold1 value for event B2, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility and High Power UE.

class.name: GeranFrequency
class.description: This Managed Object contains information of a specific Geran frequency.

attribute.name: geranFrequencyId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use.

attribute.name: bandIndicator
attribute.description:
Indicates how to interpret an associated GERAN carrier ARFCN.
The parameter indicates the GERAN frequency band when the ARFCN value is either a DCS 1800 or a PCS 1900 carrier frequency. For ARFCN values not associated with one of these bands, the indicator has no meaning.

attribute.name: arfcnValueGeranDl
attribute.description: The GERAN BCCH carrier frequency. Applicable ARFCN for DL GERAN carrier frequency, as defined in 3GPP TS 45.005.

attribute.name: geranFreqGroupRef
attribute.description: A list of references to instances of GeranFreqGroup.

attribute.name: reservedBy
attribute.description: A list of references to instances of ExternalGeranCell.

class.name: ExternalCdma2000Cell
class.description: The MO represents a CDMA2000 HRPD cell.

attribute.name: externalCdma2000CellId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: pnOffset
attribute.description: The CDMA physical cell identity.

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use.

attribute.name: cellGlobalIdHrpd
attribute.description:
The IPv6 address for a CDMA2000 HRPD cell. The input format is eight groups of four digits and characters each, separated by colons.
Ex. 2001:0db8:0000:0000:0000:0000:1428:07ab

attribute.name: reservedBy
attribute.description: Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.
attribute.dependencies: The MO may not be deleted if it is reserved.

class.name: ExternalEUtranCellFDD
class.description: This managed object represents a neighbor EUTRAN cell (FDD) in another ENodeB in any MME pool.

parameter.name: earfcn
parameter.description: Changes the frequency of the external cell. If not already existing an instance of EUtranFrequency with corresponding EUtranFreqRelation is created. For all EUtranCells within the eNB with existing cell relations to the updated external cell, new EUtranCellRelation instances are created.

attribute.name: externalEUtranCellFDDId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: localCellId
attribute.description: RBS internal ID attribute for the ExternalEUtranCellFDD. Must be unique in the RBS. Together with the Node ID and Public Land Mobile Network (PLMN) ID this is a globally unique eUTRAN Cell ID (ECGI).

attribute.name: physicalLayerCellIdGroup
attribute.description: The physical-layer cell-identity group. Physical-layer cell IDs are grouped into 168 unique physical-layer cell-identity groups, each group containing 3 unique subidentities.

attribute.name: physicalLayerSubCellId
attribute.description: The unique subidentity within a group. Physical-layer cell identities are grouped into 168 unique physical-layer cell-identity groups, each group containing 3 unique subidentities.

attribute.name: reservedBy
attribute.description: Lists EUtranCellRelation managed object instances that reserve this managed object instance.
attribute.dependencies: The managed object cannot be deleted if it is reserved.

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: User-defined alphanumeric label, maximum 128 characters including spaces.

attribute.name: tac
attribute.description: The Tracking Area Code of an external cell.

attribute.name: dlChannelBandwidth
attribute.description: The downlink channel bandwidth in a cell that is served by a neighboring RBS. The parameter is set by the RBS at X2 SETUP procedure. The value 0 means there is no valid value available.

attribute.name: isRemoveAllowed
attribute.description: Indicates if the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function is allowed to remove this object. The setting does not restrict operator removal of the object. Objects created by ANR have this attribute set to true initially.

attribute.name: masterEUtranCellFDDId
attribute.description: The identity of the EUtranCellFDD represented by this MO, for managed objects automatically created by ExternalEUtranCellFDD.

attribute.name: ulChannelBandwidth
attribute.description: The uplink channel bandwidth in a cell that is served by a neighboring RBS. The attribute is set by the RBS at X2 SETUP procedure. The value 0 means there is no valid value available.

attribute.name: eutranFrequencyRef
attribute.description: Reference to the EUTRAN frequency MO, EUtranFrequency. Cannot be changed as long as this MO is referred to by a EUtranCellRelation MO.

attribute.name: activePlmnList
attribute.description: Lists the PLMN IDs in the external E-UTRAN cell. The list may include up to 6 PLMN IDs. The list tracks the activePlmnList in the corresponding instance of EUtranCellFDD/TDD in another RBS. It is configured by ANR when ANR feature creates the MO and then set to the PLMN Id from the CGI report. The list is updated via X2 or OSS-RC, or manually.

attribute.name: createdBy
attribute.description: Indicates whether the MO has been created by the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function or operator or X2

attribute.name: timeOfCreation
attribute.description: Indicates the time and date when the MO was created. Format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS

attribute.name: lastModification
attribute.description: Indicates whether the MO was last modified by the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function or operator or X2 and if the MO is to be deleted who triggered the deletion

attribute.name: timeOfLastModification
attribute.description: Indicates the time and date when the MO was last modified. Format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS

attribute.name: pciConflict
attribute.description: A PCI confusion exists if a source cell has relations to two neighbor cells where both neighbor cells have the same PCI and frequency. A PCI collision exists if a source cell has a relation to a neighbor cell where both the source cell and neighbor cell have the same PCI and frequency.

attribute.name: pciConflictCell
attribute.description: Indicates the CGI of the other cell that is involved in the PCI collision/confusion. This value is only valid if the attribute pciConflict is "YES" or "YES_CONFLICTING_CELL".

attribute.name: csgPhysCellId
attribute.description: Physical Cell Identity for the CSG (Closed Subscriber Group). It is the start physical cell ID in the SIB4. If value is equal to 1000, it means that csg-PhysCellIdRange IE is not presented in SIB4.
attribute.statusInformation: Since L16B. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.
attribute.dependencies: This attribute has a dependency to csgPhysCellIdRange.

attribute.name: csgPhysCellIdRange
attribute.description: It is the range of Physical Cell Identity for the CSG (Closed Subscriber Group). The information is broadcasted in SIB4.
attribute.statusInformation: Since L16B. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.
attribute.dependencies: If csgPhyscellId != 1000, csgPhysCellId + csgPhysCellIdRange <= 504

attribute.name: pciDetectingCell
attribute.description: Indicates the CGI of the cell that detected the PCI collision/confusion. This value is only valid if the corresponding attribute pciConflict is "YES" or "YES_CONFLICTING_CELL". The first cell in the pciDetectingCell list corresponds to the first cell in the pciConflictCell list and the first value of pciConflict. The second cell in the pciDetectingCell list corresponds to the second cell in the pciConflictCell list and the first value of pciConflict.

attribute.name: activeServiceAreaId
attribute.description: The active MBMS Service Area Identity of an external cell.

attribute.name: lbEUtranCellOffloadCapacity
attribute.description: This attribute indicates the offload subscription capacity associated with the EUTRAN target cell. The value is used to moderate the offload rate to the EUTRAN target cell.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: additionalFreqBandList
attribute.description: A list of additional frequency bands the cell belongs to, not including the frequency band indicated by the EARFCN value of the cell (primary frequency band). The list is automatically set by the eNB.

attribute.name: freqBand
attribute.description: The primary frequency band the cell belongs to according to its defined EARFCN. This frequency band indicator is broadcasted to the UEs in SystemInformationBlockType1.

attribute.name: noOfTxAntennas
attribute.description: Number of antennas that can be used for DL transmission.

attribute.name: mbsfnSubframeAlloc
attribute.description: Shows the subframes that are reserved for MBSFN in DL.
attribute.statusInformation: Since 17.Q2. Replaced by commonSFAllocList. Planned to be removed.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic. Any UEs using this cell as an external SCell will have this SCell deactivated. New connections that take place after the attribute change will use the new value.

attribute.name: remoteCellState

action.name: updateMMEConnection
action.description:
This action shall make it possible to order the RBS to make a new DNS lookup to get possible new MME Pool addresses. The orderCode has two different options:
- Retain: This option will retain all connections that were included in DNS response and the connections that were not included in the response will be removed. For the IP addresses that were unknown for the RBS, the RBS will establish connections to those MMEs.
- Renew All existing: The RBS performs a DNS lookup. Release all S1 connections to the MMEs and connect to the MMEs that are included in the DNS response.
This action should be used only when dnsLookupOnTai has the value ON. The action is rejected if dnsLookupState has the value OFF.

action.name: collectDynamicCellStatus
action.description: Returns a snapshot of the traffic status of the node divided per cell, in the form; number of attached UEs and set up radio bearers.

parameter.name: dynamicCellStatusOutput
parameter.description: Specifies the format of the returned information. It can be either of: - Unformatted text, suitable for on-screen reading. - Formatted text, suitable for automated interpretation, currently JSON (JavaScript Object Notation).

attribute.name: timeAndPhaseSynchCritical
attribute.description: If set to true, the cell will be disabled if the time and phase synchronization accuracy of the eNodeB is not fulfilled.

attribute.name: eNodeBFunctionId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use.

attribute.name: sctpRef
attribute.description: Refers to SCTP instance used to configure SCTP host for S1 and X2 connections unless specified by sctpX2Ref.

attribute.name: dnsLookupOnTai
attribute.description:
Controls if the Tracking Area Identity (TAI) is used to get IP addresses of MME nodes from the Domain Name System (DNS).
The RBS uses TAI to automatically obtain all MME IP addresses from the DNS when dnsLookupOnTai is switched on, or at RBS start or restart.
The MME IP address list is refreshed periodically and MME connections released and setup according to the new list. The MME IP address list can also be refreshed from OSS-RC.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: dnsLookupTimer
attribute.description: The interval to perform DNS Lookup to get potential new IP addresses of MME nodes. DNS lookup is performed for the TAI domain name. If the value is set to zero, then no periodic DNS Lookup is done.

attribute.name: dscpLabel
attribute.description: Static mapping of DiffServ label for control messages, Performance Management (PM), and Non-Access Stratum (NAS).
attribute.dependencies: Will only be used then dscpUsage is active.

attribute.name: eNBId
attribute.description: The ENodeB ID that forms part of the Cell Global Identity, and is also used to identify the node over the S1 interface.

attribute.name: eNodeBPlmnId
attribute.description: The ENodeB Public Land Mobile Network (PLMN) ID that forms part of the ENodeB Global ID used to identify the node over the S1 interface. Note: The value (MCC=001, MNC=01) indicates that the PLMN is not initiated. The value can not be used as a valid PLMN Identity.

attribute.name: x2BlackList
attribute.description: A list of blacklisted RBS IDs. X2 may not be set up to any neighbor RBS in the blacklist.
attribute.disturbances: If an eNB is added to the list, any termPointToEnb for this external eNB is removed.

attribute.name: x2retryTimerMaxAuto
attribute.description: See attribute x2RetryTimerStart.

attribute.name: x2retryTimerStart
attribute.description:
After failed X2 setup and after X2 link break the x2RetryTimer is used to control the time till next retry. x2RetryTimer is used for DNS, SCTP, X2AP retries and x2IpAddrViaS1.
After first failed setup or missing IP address from DNS, x2RetryTimer = max(x2RetryTimerStart,W), where W is the timeToWait received in x2SetupFail. If W is not received, W=0.
After link break, x2RetryTimer = random(0,x2RetryTimerStart). If the first setup after link break fails, the timer values according to the above and below paragraphs shall apply as for failed initial setup.
After 2nd and following fails, if the X2 connection is not being setup by ANR in the S-RBS, x2RetryTimer = max(x2RetryTimerStart,W).
After 2nd and following fails, if the X2 connection is being setup by ANR in the S-RBS, x2RetryTimer = max(min[2^(n-2)*x2RetryTimerStart, x2retryTimerMaxAuto], W), where n is failure number.
Each W is only used in the first retry after it is received.

attribute.name: x2WhiteList
attribute.description: The list of whitelisted RBS IDs. Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) is not allowed to disconnect X2 for any neighbor RBS in the whitelist.

attribute.name: s1RetryTimer
attribute.description: Defines the frequency to perform re-establishment of SCTP and S1-AP connection, when the connection to a MME is lost.

attribute.name: ulSchedulerDynamicBWAllocationEnabled
attribute.description: Specifies if the advanced UL scheduler is enabled

attribute.name: x2IpAddrViaS1Active
attribute.description: Indicates if the function X2 IP addresses over S1 is active in the RBS.

attribute.name: nnsfMode
attribute.description:
The mode used by the RBS for the non-access stratum node selection.
Regardless of the mode used, the function attempts to:
- Reconnect every UE to its registered MME in any of the tracking areas of the cell.
- Distribute the UEs that are not reconnected among MMEs that serve the Public Land Mobile Network selected by each UE.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: rrcConnReestActive
attribute.description: Indicates if the feature RRC Connection Reestablishment is ACTIVATED or DEACTIVATED.

attribute.name: x2SetupTwoWayRelations
attribute.description: This parameter indicates if two way relations shall be setup during X2 setup and eNB configuration. The RBS creates a two-way relation for each entry in the received neighbour information that contains a relation to a source cell. Neighbour information is sent in X2 setup and eNB configuration. Neighbour information is eUtranCellRelations per source cell from the sending node.

attribute.name: minRandc

attribute.dependencies: minRandc < maxRandc

attribute.name: maxRandc
attribute.description: Rand range datatype is the eight most significant bits (MSB) of the Rand used for authentication. This attribute controls the maximum random number value that can be generated. Typically a range of random numbers is allocated to each system using this attribute.
attribute.dependencies: maxRandc > minRandc

attribute.name: randUpdateInterval
attribute.description: Random number update interval This attribute specifies the time interval in minutes between random number generation. When this interval expires, the eNodeB generates a new random number between MinRandc and MaxRandc.

attribute.name: biasThpWifiMobility
attribute.description: In order to send a UE to WiFi, a throughput comparison is made between WiFi and LTE. For comparisons made in eNodeB, a UE is admitted to WiFi if, WiFi throughput > biasThpWifiMobility * LTE throughput.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic

attribute.name: tS1HoCancelTimer
attribute.description: The timeout time for receiving HANDOVER CANCEL ACKNOWLEDGE after RBS sent HO CANCEL message to MME. Value specifies supervision time of outgoing S1 HO Cancellation according to procedure described in 3GPP TS 36.413 section 8.4.5.

attribute.name: dnsSelectionS1X2Ref
attribute.description:
Controls DNS selection for S1 and X2 lookups. If not set, DNS server on OAM network is used.
For DU Radio Node it can be set to reference a DnsResolver, and DNS queries are resolved using referenced DnsResolver (typically using DNS server on transport network).
For Baseband Radio Node it can be set to reference a DnsClient, and DNS queries are resolved using referenced DnsClient (typically using DNS server on transport network).
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
attribute.precondition: To enable this attribute DNS servers must support EDNS0.

attribute.name: releaseInactiveUesEnable
attribute.description: Controls if the release of inactive UEs at handover shall be enabled.
attribute.statusInformation: Since L16A. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.

attribute.name: releaseInactiveUesInactTime
attribute.description: Inactivity time value to be used to decide release of inactive UEs at handover.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: releaseInactiveUesMpLoadLevel
attribute.description: Minimum MP load level at which inactive UEs are released at handover.

attribute.name: combCellSectorSelectThreshTx
attribute.description: Used for PDSCH and PHICH sector selection in combined Cell. For each UE, all sectors received power are compared against the primary sector. Sectors that are below the threshold will be selected.
attribute.disturbances: Changes may affect Sector Selection.

attribute.name: combCellSectorSelectThreshRx
attribute.description: Used for PUSCH sector selection in combined Cell. For each UE, all sectors received power are compared against the primary sector. Only the primary and the best sector that is below the threshold will be selected.
attribute.disturbances: Changes may affect Sector Selection.

attribute.name: timePhaseMaxDeviationSib16
attribute.description: The maximum allowed time and phase deviation for time and phase synchronization of the eNodeB. It is the deviation that is allowed for SIB16 Time Information Broadcast feature to function. When the limit is exceeded, the feature is deactivated.
attribute.disturbances: Traffic can be affected if this attribute is changed. It can cause malfunction of the SIB16 Time Information Broadcast due to the time and phase deviation for time and phase synchronization of the eNodeB.

attribute.name: timePhaseMaxDeviationMbms
attribute.description: The maximum allowed time and phase deviation for time and phase synchronization of the eNodeB. It is the deviation that is allowed for Multimedia Broadcast Multicast Service (MBMS) to function. When the limit is exceeded, the service is deactivated.
attribute.disturbances: Traffic can be affected if this attribute is changed. It can cause malfunction of the Multimedia Broadcast Multicast Service (MBMS) due to the time and phase deviation for time and phase synchronization of the eNodeB.

attribute.name: timePhaseMaxDeviationOtdoa
attribute.description: The maximum allowed time and phase deviation for time and phase synchronization of the eNodeB. It is the deviation that is allowed for Observed Time Difference of Arrival (OTDOA) Support to function. When the limit is exceeded, the service is deactivated.
attribute.disturbances: Traffic can be affected if this attribute is changed. It can cause malfunction of the Observed Time Difference of Arrival (OTDOA) Support feature due to the time and phase deviation for time and phase synchronization of the eNodeB.

attribute.name: timePhaseMaxDeviationCdma2000
attribute.description: The maximum allowed time and phase deviation for time and phase synchronization of the eNodeB. It is the deviation that is allowed for features related to CDMA2000 fallback and handover to function. When the limit is exceeded, some of the functionality is deactivated.
attribute.disturbances: Traffic can be affected if this attribute is changed. It can cause malfunction of the features related to CDMA2000 due to the time and phase deviation for time and phase synchronization of the eNodeB.

attribute.name: timePhaseMaxDeviationTdd
attribute.description: Max allowed deviation for time and phase synchronization of eNodeB for TDD cells. If exceeded, TDD cells that use this limit are disabled.
attribute.dependencies: timeAndPhaseSynchAlignment must be true.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: timePhaseSynchStateSib16
attribute.description: Set to false when the SIB16 Time Information Broadcast feature is degraded due to time and phase synchronization accuracy requirements not fulfilled, otherwise it is set to true.

attribute.name: timePhaseSynchStateMbms
attribute.description: Set to false when the Multimedia Broadcast Multicast Service (MBMS) feature is degraded due to time and phase synchronization accuracy requirements not fulfilled, otherwise it is set to true.

attribute.name: timePhaseSynchStateOtdoa
attribute.description: Set to false when the Observed Time Difference of Arrival (OTDOA) feature is degraded due to time and phase synchronization accuracy requirements not fulfilled, otherwise it is set to true.

attribute.name: timePhaseSynchStateCdma2000
attribute.description: Set to false when the features related to CDMA2000 are degraded due to time and phase synchronization accuracy requirements not fulfilled, otherwise it is set to true.

attribute.name: timeAndPhaseSynchAlignment
attribute.description: If set to true, any time and phase synchronization accuracy-dependent feature is deactivated or degraded if its time and phase synchronization accuracy is not fulfilled.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: licConnectedUsersPercentileConf
attribute.description: The percentile to use for the counter pmLicConnectedUsersActual.

attribute.name: licDlBbPercentileConf
attribute.description: The percentile to use for the counter BbProcessingResource::pmLicDlCapActual.

attribute.name: licUlBbPercentileConf
attribute.description: The percentile to use for the counter BbProcessingResource::pmLicUlCapActual.

attribute.name: licDlPrbPercentileConf
attribute.description: The percentile to use for the counter BbProcessingResource::pmLicDlPrbCapActual.

attribute.name: licUlPrbPercentileConf
attribute.description: The percentile to use for the counter BbProcessingResource::pmLicUlPrbCapActual.

attribute.name: mtRreWithoutNeighborActive
attribute.description: Enables or disables the RRC Connection Reestablishment in source cell when there is no target neighbor cell information.
attribute.dependencies: This attribute is only effective when feature Multi-Target RRC Connection Reestablishment is activated.

attribute.name: csmMinHighHitThreshold
attribute.description: Minimum required hit rate to qualify a related cell as high hit rate coverage cell by feature Cell Sleep Mode.

attribute.name: checkEmergencySoftLock
attribute.description: Used to turn on and off the function for checking existence of emergency calls.

attribute.name: softLockRwRWaitTimerInternal
attribute.description: Length of waiting time before soft-lock of cell starts to release all ongoing calls with Release with Redirect (RwR), when eNodeB internally triggers soft-lock of cell.

attribute.name: softLockRwRWaitTimerOperator
attribute.description: Length of waiting time before soft-lock of cell starts to release all ongoing calls with Release with Redirect (RwR), when operator triggers soft-lock of cell.

attribute.name: mfbiSupportPolicy
attribute.description: A policy parameter that sets the start value of the attribute mfbiSupport when an ExternalENodeBFunction is automatically created by the eNodeB.

attribute.name: tddVoipDrxProfileId
attribute.description: DrxProfile ID used for TDD VOIP bearers on a mixed FDD/TDD eNodeB. The default value results in TDD using the same DrxProfile as FDD for VOIP bearers.

attribute.name: measuringEcgiWithAgActive
attribute.description: Configures use of autonomous gap as method of CGI measurement. If enabled, capable UEs are configured to use autonomous gap for CGI measurement to target LTE or UTRAN cell.
attribute.dependencies: This attribute is effective only when ANR for LTE or UTRAN feature is activated.

attribute.name: enabledUlTrigMeas
attribute.description: Enables or disables the UL SINR max measurements and event triggers for the UL quality. Only has effect if license for Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is not installed.

attribute.name: adaptiveRlcRetxDl
attribute.description: Shows if Adaptive RLC Retransmission in DL is active or not.
attribute.statusInformation: Since L16B. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.

attribute.name: ulMaxWaitingTimeGlobal
attribute.description: The targeted maximum allowed time between scheduling occasions of an UL bearer. A bearer that is not scheduled within the specified time is given higher priority. Value 0 means that the higher priority is never applied. It is recommended to set the value =< than the PDB. A value that is set too low can affect other services with higher priority.
attribute.dependencies: Only used for Resource Fair Scheduling algorithm. Only relevant if the license for Dynamic UE Admission Control is present and the feature is active.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect performance of all data bearers. A value that is set too low can affect other services with higher priority. A value that is set too high can cause Dynamic UE Admission Control to fail in keeping the cell stable at overload.

attribute.name: dlMaxWaitingTimeGlobal
attribute.description: The targeted maximum allowed time between scheduling occasions of a DL bearer. A bearer that is not scheduled within the specified time is given higher priority. Value 0 means that the higher priority is never applied. It is recommended to set the value =< than the PDB. A value that is set too low can affect other services with higher priority.
attribute.dependencies: Only used for Resource Fair Scheduling algorithm. Only relevant if the license for Dynamic UE Admission Control is present and the feature is active.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect performance of all data bearers. A value that is set too low can affect other services with higher priority. A value that is set too high can cause Dynamic UE Admission Control to fail in keeping the cell stable at overload.

attribute.name: tRelocOverall
attribute.description: Supervision timer of the outgoing S1/X2/intra-eNodeB handover execution procedure according to 3GPP TS 36.413 and TS 36.423. If the feature Multi-Target RRC Connection Re-establishment is active this timer also supervises the Context Fetch procedure.
attribute.disturbances: Low values can stop outgoing HO.

attribute.name: alignTtiBundWUlTrigSinr
attribute.description: Configures UL quality measure type utilized for decisions on when to configure and de-configure TTI Bundling. If setting is 'ULTRIG' uplink SINR value from 'Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility' is used for TTI Bundling.

attribute.name: s1GtpuEchoEnable
attribute.description: If the node monitors and measures delay for all S1-U termination points or not.
attribute.dependencies:
For DU Radio Node: If feature Transport Path Characteristics Monitoring is activated, and peer node supports delay measurements, delay measurements are performed and monitoring interval is 5 seconds. If feature Transport Path Characteristics Monitoring is activated, and peer node does not support delay measurements, delay measurements are not performed and monitoring interval is 60 seconds. If feature Transport Path Characteristics Monitoring is not activated, monitoring is not enabled.
For Baseband Radio Node: If feature Transport Path Characteristics Monitoring is activated, and peer node supports delay measurements, delay measurements are performed and monitoring interval is determined by s1GtpuEchoInterval. If feature Transport Path Characteristics Monitoring is not activated, or peer node does not support delay measurements, delay measurements are not performed and monitoring interval is 60 seconds.

attribute.name: x2GtpuEchoEnable
attribute.description: If the node monitors and measures delay for all X2-U termination points or not.
attribute.dependencies:
For DU Radio Node: If feature Transport Path Characteristics Monitoring is activated, and peer node supports delay measurements, delay measurements are performed and monitoring interval is 1 second. If feature Transport Path Characteristics Monitoring is activated, and peer node does not support delay measurements, delay measurements are not performed and monitoring interval is 60 seconds. If feature Transport Path Characteristics Monitoring is not activated, monitoring is not enabled.
For Baseband Radio Node: If feature Transport Path Characteristics Monitoring is activated, and peer node supports delay measurements, delay measurements are performed and monitoring interval is 1 second. If feature Transport Path Characteristics Monitoring is not activated, or peer node does not support delay measurements, delay measurements are not performed and monitoring interval is 60 seconds.

attribute.name: s1GtpuEchoDscp
attribute.description: DSCP value used for outgoing GTP-U echo request packets on S1-U.

attribute.name: x2GtpuEchoDscp
attribute.description: DSCP value used for outgoing GTP-U echo request packets on X2-U.

attribute.name: gtpuErrorIndicationDscp
attribute.description: DSCP value used for outgoing GTP-U error indication messages.

attribute.name: s1GtpuEchoFailureAction
attribute.description: S1-U failure action.

attribute.precondition: Requires support for the feature Multiple Frequency Band Indicators in the eNB.

attribute.name: prioritizeAdditionalBands
attribute.description: When enabled, additional frequency bands have higher priority than primary frequency band when considering whether intra-cell handover will improve secondary cell availability.

attribute.name: useBandPrioritiesInSCellEval
attribute.description: When enabled, secondary cell evaluation for CA aware Intra-Cell Handover to Additional Band is done according to priorities in prioritizeAdditionalBands and EUtranCellFDD/EUtranCellTDD::prioAdditionalFreqBandList.

attribute.name: useBandPrioritiesInSib1
attribute.description: When enabled, prioritized additional frequency band list is broadcasted in SIB1 according to priorities in EUtranCellFDD/EUtranCellTDD::prioAdditionalFreqBandList.
attribute.statusInformation: Since 18.Q2. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed

attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic. A node restart is required.

attribute.name: interEnbCaTunnelDscp
attribute.description: DSCP value used for outgoing inter-eNB CA packets on X2. It is recommended to set this to the same value as "QCI9 - Non-GBR TCP Default Bearer", as inter-eNB CA benefits should be treated as opportunistic and not allowed to interfere with baseline LTE performance.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can also affect other X2 traffic than CA packets.

attribute.name: timePhaseMaxDeviationIeNbCa
attribute.description: The maximum allowed time and phase deviation for time and phase synchronization of the eNodeB. It is the maximum deviation that is allowed for Carrier Aggregation to function. When the limit is exceeded, inter-eNB CA or eRAN CA is deactivated. Takes effect immediately.
attribute.dependencies: Only effective if timeAndPhaseSynchAlignment is true.
attribute.disturbances: Traffic can be affected if this attribute is changed. It can cause malfunction of the inter-eNB CA or eRAN CA feature due to the time and phase deviation for time and phase synchronization between two eNodeBs.

attribute.name: ulBbCapacityNet
attribute.description: Granted UL baseband capacity. Available capacity of corresponding Baseband HWAC property for all enabled Baseband HW.

attribute.name: ulBbCapacityMaxLimit
attribute.description: Max UL baseband capacity available on unlocked Baseband hardware. Maximum limit of UL capacity that can be granted by baseband HWAC. This level sets the limit at emergency unlock.

attribute.name: dlBbCapacityNet
attribute.description: Granted DL baseband capacity. Available capacity of corresponding Baseband HWAC property for all enabled Baseband HW.

attribute.name: dlBbCapacityMaxLimit
attribute.description: Max DL baseband capacity available on unlocked Baseband hardware. Maximum limit of DL capacity that can be granted by baseband HWAC. This level sets the limit at emergency unlock.

attribute.name: altNasBackTo
