attribute.name: timePhaseMaxDevIeNBUlComp
attribute.description: Max deviation for time and phase synchronization of eNodeB allowed for inter-eNodeB UL CoMP to function. If exceeded, service for inter-eNodeB UL CoMP is deactivated.
attribute.dependencies: timeAndPhaseSynchAlignment must be true.
attribute.disturbances: Traffic can be affected if this attribute is changed. It can cause malfunction of inter-eNodeB UL CoMP feature due to time and phase deviation for time and phase synchronization between two eNodeBs.

attribute.name: timePhaseSyncStateIeNBUlComp
attribute.description: Set to false when inter-eNodeB UL CoMP feature is degraded due to time and phase synchronization accuracy requirements not fulfilled, otherwise it is set to true.

attribute.name: interEnbUlCompTunnelDscp
attribute.description: DSCP value used for outgoing inter-eNodeB UL CoMP packets on X2. Set to same value as "QCI9 - Non-GBR TCP Default Bearer". Treat inter-eNodeB UL CoMP benefits as opportunistic and do not allow it to interfere with baseline LTE performance.

attribute.name: maxNrOfInterEnbUlCompLbm
attribute.description: Max number of inter-eNodeB UL CoMP candidate LBMs for each serving or cooperating LBM.

attribute.name: extendedWaitTimeNb
attribute.description: Wait time. Used for Narrow Band IoT RRC Connection Reject. If 0, value range is random.

attribute.name: inactivitySupervisionTimerNb
attribute.description:
Inactivity supervision timer for NbIot cells in relation to estimated MCL for the UEs.
InactivitySupervisionTimerNb[0] is used for UEs estimated to be in MCL less or equal to 144dB. InactivitySupervisionTimerNb[1] is used for UEs estimated to be in MCL greater than 144dB and less or equal to 154dB. InactivitySupervisionTimerNb[2] is used for UEs estimated to be in MCL greater than 154dB.
Value 0 in an array entry means disable the timer for UEs in corresponding MCL.

attribute.name: zzzTemporary55
attribute.description: Temporary attributes are intended as temporary solutions. Their usage can vary depending on the installed software. It is strongly recommended to only set the attributes that correspond to a desired functionality and leave all other temporary attributes set to default value. Information in the descriptions about what attributes are in use can be overridden by the information in CPI documents. Note that a later release can use another attribute to control functionality previously provided by a temporary attribute, or can remove functionality altogether. In these cases, the change is documented in the NIR.

attribute.name: zzzTemporary56
attribute.description: Temporary attribute intended for temporary solution. Usage depends on the installed software. Only set this attribute when it corresponds to a desired functionality and leave all other temporary attributes set to default values. Information in the descriptions about the used attributes can be overridden by information in CPI documents. Note that a later release can use another attribute or completely remove the functionality. Changes are documented in the NIR.

attribute.name: zzzTemporary57
attribute.description: Temporary attribute intended for temporary solution. Usage depends on the installed software. Only set this attribute when it corresponds to a desired functionality and leave all other temporary attributes set to default values. Information in the descriptions about the used attributes can be overridden by information in CPI documents. Note that a later release can use another attribute or completely remove the functionality. Changes are documented in the NIR.

attribute.name: zzzTemporary58
attribute.description: Temporary attribute intended for temporary solution. Usage depends on the installed software. Only set this attribute when it corresponds to a desired functionality and leave all other temporary attributes set to default values. Information in the descriptions about the used attributes can be overridden by information in CPI documents. Note that a later release can use another attribute or completely remove the functionality. Changes are documented in the NIR.

attribute.name: intraRanIpAddressRef
attribute.description: Reference to an AddressIPv4/AddressIPv6 instance. Used to configure IP address for intra RAN control, and user plane connections unless specified by rpUpIpAddressRef.

attribute.name: rpUpIpAddressRef
attribute.description: Reference to an AddressIPv4/AddressIPv6 instance. Used to configure IP address for intra RAN user plane connections.

attribute.name: zzzTemporary59
attribute.description: Temporary attribute intended for temporary solution. Usage depends on the installed software. Only set this attribute when it corresponds to a desired functionality and leave all other temporary attributes set to default values. Information in the descriptions about the used attributes can be overridden by information in CPI documents. Note that a later release can use another attribute or completely remove the functionality. Changes are documented in the NIR.

attribute.name: maxNrOfEnbPartnersEranUlComp
attribute.description: Max number of Elastic RAN UL CoMP candidate partners. Currently only 0..6 is supported and 7..20 will be considered as 6.

attribute.name: eranUlCompReSelectLinkTime
attribute.description: The maximum time that the serving eNodeB can reselect Inter ME Link for Elastic RAN UL CoMP towards a new neighbor eNodeB.

attribute.name: eranUlCompVlanPortRef
attribute.description: VlanPort instance that can be used to set up EranInterMeLinks and BbLinks for Elastic RAN UL CoMP. Used as default when no value is specified for ExternalENodeBFunction::eranUlCompVlanPortRef.

attribute.name: zzzTemporary60
attribute.description: Temporary attributes are intended as temporary solutions. Their usage can vary depending on the installed software. It is strongly recommended to only set the attributes that correspond to a desired functionality and leave all other temporary attributes set to default value. Information in the descriptions about what attributes are in use can be overridden by the information in CPI documents. Note that a later release can use another attribute to control functionality previously provided by a temporary attribute, or can remove functionality altogether. In these cases, the change is documented in the NIR.

attribute.name: zzzTemporary61
attribute.description: Temporary attributes are intended as temporary solutions. Their usage can vary depending on the installed software. It is strongly recommended to only set the attributes that correspond to a desired functionality and leave all other temporary attributes set to default value. Information in the descriptions about what attributes are in use can be overridden by the information in CPI documents. Note that a later release can use another attribute to control functionality previously provided by a temporary attribute, or can remove functionality altogether. In these cases, the change is documented in the NIR.

attribute.name: elasticRanUlCompSupport
attribute.description: Whether eNodeB supports Elastic RAN UL CoMP feature.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect in Baseband Radio Node.

attribute.name: iuaMaxResourcePerBbm
attribute.description: Maximum percentage of UL PRBs and SEs that are used by IUA at BBM level.

attribute.name: s1GtpuEchoInterval
attribute.description: Monitoring interval for delay measurements for all S1-U termination points.
attribute.dependencies: Only applicable for Baseband Radio Node. Takes effect if license and feature Transport Path Characteristics Monitoring is activated, s1GtpuEchoEnable = PERIODIC, and peer node supports delay measurements.

attribute.name: interNodalProtVersions
attribute.description: Protocol versions for inter-nodal features.

attribute.name: release
attribute.description: The product release of the ManagedFunction. It commonly contains the Managed Function release, for example L12.0, 13A, R1A

class.name: EUtranCellFDD
class.description: This MO represents a Cell and contains parameters needed by the cell. It also contains parameters for the mandatory common channels.

action.name: changeFrequency
action.description:
Changes the frequency of the cell. The attribute earfcndl is changed. This MO action includes the following steps:
- An instance of EUtranFrequency with correct frequency is created (if not already existing).
- For neigbouring cells with existing cell relations to the cell, create new EUtranFreqRelation instances (if not already existing) and new EUtranCellRelation instances (with the same attribute values as the existing EUtranFreqRelation and EUtranCellRelation MOs).
- For the changed cell an instance of EUtranFreqRelation with reference to the correct instance of EUtranFrequency is created, if not already existing (with the same attribute values as the existing EUtranFreqRelation MO).
Note that changing frequency of a EUtranCellFDD will imply that all other eNBs that have this cell configured as an ExternaEUtranCellFDD will be updated with the new frequency. This means that new EUtranFreqRelation and corresponding EUtranFrequency MOs might be created.

parameter.name: earfcn
parameter.description: The new DL frequency for this cell.

action.disturbances: Changes may affect traffic. The cell will be automatic locked/unlocked if needed.

action.name: stopAilg
action.description: Stops execution of the optional feature Air Interface Load Generator.

action.name: startAilg
action.description: Starts execution of the optional feature Air Interface Load Generator.
action.disturbances: Executing this action can cause loss of traffic if high priority load is configured.

attribute.name: eUtranCellFDDId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: earfcndl
attribute.description: The channel number for the central downlink frequency. The mapping from channel number to physical frequency for specified EUTRA bands is described in 3GPP TS 36.104. The values that can be used depend on national, operator-specific frequency allocation as well as on the supported frequency bands in the RBS. Note: Use the MO action changeFrequency if the DL frequency must be changed after the cell is initially setup.
attribute.dependencies: This attribute is dependent on and set together with earfcnul. The earfcnul and earfcndl values are dependent and relate according to default EUTRA TX channel to RX channel separation as specified in 3GPP TS 36.101 for the EUTRA operating band and channel bandwidth of the cell.
attribute.disturbances: Changes may affect traffic.

attribute.name: earfcnul
attribute.description: Channel number for the central UL frequency. The mapping from channel number to physical frequency for specified EUTRA bands is described in 3GPP TS 36.104. Values that can be used depend on national, operator-specific frequency allocation, as well as on the supported frequency bands of the RBS. Value 0 means that the UL channel number is N/A for the DL-only bands.
attribute.dependencies: This attribute is dependent on and set together with earfcndl. The earfcnul and earfcndl values are dependent and relate according to default EUTRA TX channel to RX channel separation as specified in 3GPP TS 36.101 for the EUTRA operating band and channel bandwidth of the cell.
attribute.disturbances: Changes may affect traffic.

attribute.name: frameStartOffset
attribute.description: The frame start offset of the cell.
attribute.disturbances: Changes may affect traffic.

attribute.name: noOfPucchCqiUsers
attribute.description: The number of Channel Quality Indicator (CQI) resources available on the PUCCH channel. For 1.4 MHz system bandwidth the recommended value is 50.
attribute.disturbances: Cell runs new set-up procedure. All cell-connected UEs are released and connected again.

attribute.name: noOfPucchSrUsers
attribute.description: The number of Scheduling Request (SR) resources available on the PUCCH channel. For 1.4 MHz system bandwidth the recommended value is 50.
attribute.disturbances: Cell runs new set-up procedure. All cell-connected UEs are released and connected again.

attribute.name: dlChannelBandwidth
attribute.description:
The downlink channel bandwidth in the cell.
Valid values: 1400, 3000, 5000, 10000, 15000, 20000
attribute.dependencies: This attribute is dependent on and shall be set to the same as ulChannelBandwidth.
attribute.disturbances: Changes may affect traffic.

attribute.name: ulChannelBandwidth
attribute.description:
The uplink channel bandwidth in the cell.
Valid values: 1400, 3000, 5000, 10000, 15000, 20000
attribute.dependencies: This attribute is dependent on and shall be set to the same as dlChannelBandwidth.
attribute.disturbances: Changes may affect traffic.

attribute.name: cellRange
attribute.description: Defines the maximum distance from the base station where a connection to a UE can be setup and/or maintained.
attribute.disturbances: Changes may affect traffic.

attribute.name: commonSrPeriodicity
attribute.description: Common SR periodicity, used for all UEs.
attribute.dependencies: For 1.4 MHz: Only valid inputs are 10 and 20.

attribute.name: transmissionMode
attribute.description: Defines the Transmission Mode (e.g. Transmit Diversity and Closed-Loop Spatial Multiplexing) that shall be used for the UEs that are connected to the cell. See 3GPP TS 36.213 table 7.1-5 for a definition of Transmission Mode.

attribute.name: isDlOnly
attribute.description: Indicates if the cell is operated with downlink only and with no uplink.
attribute.disturbances: Changes may affect traffic.

attribute.name: noOfChannelSelectionSets
attribute.description: The number of channel selection PUCCH resource sets (CS sets) to reserve in each cell for secondary cell HARQ feedback. To conserve PUCCH resource, this attribute can be set to 0 if the cell is not used as PCell for Carrier Aggregation.

attribute.name: channelSelectionSetSize
attribute.description:
Determines the number of Channel Selection (CS) PUCCH resources in a CS set.
Set to 1 when all SCell candidates are configured with transmission mode 1 or 2. Set to 2 when at least one SCell candidate is configured with transmission mode 3 or higher.
attribute.dependencies:
Applicable only when attribute noOfChannelSelectionSets > 0.
Only SCell candidates with TM mode resource requirements that match the CS set size are considered for carrier aggregation.

attribute.name: csiRsConfigType8TxFDD
attribute.description: This attribute specifies configuration type of CSI-RS (Channel State Information Reference Signal) for FDD 8Tx.

attribute.name: maxSentCrsAssistCells
attribute.description: Maximum number of neighbor cells whose CRS Assistance Information is sent to UE.

attribute.name: dlInternalChannelBandwidth
attribute.description: Internal DL channel bandwidth in the cell with reduced channel bandwidth. Reduced bandwidth for an LTE carrier creates free space for carriers of other radio technologies to use within a standard spectrum 5 MHz or 10 MHz. Other spectrum will generate the undefined value 0. Reduced channel bandwidth is only supported on RRUS14 and RRUS04.
attribute.dependencies: Dependent on, and to be set to, the same value as ulInternalChannelBandwidth. dlInternalChannelBandwidth values 4600 and 4800 are only allowed when dlChannelBandwidth is 5000. dlInternalChannelBandwidth value 9000 is only allowed when dlChannelBandwidth is 10000.
attribute.disturbances: Changes may affect traffic

attribute.name: ulInternalChannelBandwidth
attribute.description: Internal UL channel bandwidth in the cell with reduced channel bandwidth. Reduced bandwidth for an LTE carrier creates free space for carriers of other radio technologies to use within a standard spectrum 5 MHz or 10 MHz. Other spectrum will generate the undefined value 0. Reduced channel bandwidth is only supported on RRUS14 and RRUS04.
attribute.dependencies: Dependent on, and to be set to, the same value as dlInternalChannelBandwidth. ulInternalChannelBandwidth values 4600 and 4800 are only allowed when ulChannelBandwidth is 5000. ulInternalChannelBandwidth value 9000 is only allowed when ulChannelBandwidth is 10000.
attribute.disturbances: Changes may affect traffic

attribute.name: ttiBundlingSwitchThres
attribute.description: SINR threshold for triggering a switch to TTI bundling.

attribute.name: ttiBundlingSwitchThresHyst
attribute.description: Hysteresis of SINR threshold for triggering a switch to TTI bundling.

attribute.name: ttiBundlingAfterHo
attribute.description: Controls if UE remains in TTI bundling mode after handover.

attribute.name: ttiBundlingAfterReest
attribute.description: Controls if UE remains in TTI bundling mode after reestablishment.

attribute.name: noOfPucchFormat3PrbPairs
attribute.description: Number of PUCCH Format 3 PRB pairs.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect when 3CC Carrier aggregation Extension Feature (FAJ 121 3084) is enabled.

attribute.name: siPeriodicityBr
attribute.description: SI message periodicity for Bandwidth reduced UEs. If SIB is not mapped to SI message, SI message is not transmitted.

attribute.name: maxValidSubframeDlBr
attribute.description: Upper limit of valid subframes for DL transmission of BR traffic.

attribute.name: highestSupportedCeLevelBr
attribute.description: Max CE level for BR low-complexity UEs. 0 enables CE level 0. 1 enables CE levels 0 and 1.

attribute.name: catm1SupportEnabled
attribute.description:
Whether or not support for Category M device is enabled in the cell.
Note: Feature is optional and under license control.

attribute.name: beamWeightSet16Tr
attribute.description: Specifies the index representing the beam weight vector to be applied for beam forming using the 16TR feature. If the value is equal to 0, the feature is not active.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic. A cell lock/unlock is required.

attribute.name: beamWeightSet16TrTm9
attribute.description: Index that represents beam weight vector applied for beam forming when 16TR TM9 feature is used. If value is 0, feature is not active.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic. A cell lock/unlock is required.

attribute.name: csiRsConfigType
attribute.description: Configuration type of 8 port CSI-RS (Channel State Information Reference Signal).

attribute.name: schedulingInfoSib1BrMod
attribute.description: Whether or not to modify the transmission of IE SchedulingInfoSIB1-BR-r13 in the MIB to improve accessibility of faulty legacy LTE UEs (not compliant with Release 13 of 3GPP). If modification is on, also UEs which require zero schedulingInfoSIB1-BR-r13 are supported.
attribute.dependencies: Only valid if catm1SupportEnabled = true.

attribute.name: tm9Tm4ModeSwitchingEnabled
attribute.description: Enables dynamic switching between TM9 and TM4.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect if radio equipment supports AAS functionality.

attribute.name: ailgRef
attribute.description: Refers to an instance of AirIfLoadProfile. Assigns a AirIfLoadProfile to a cell.

attribute.name: ailgActive
attribute.description: The state of the feature Air Interface Load Generator. Indicates if it is running or stopped.

attribute.name: changeNotification
attribute.description: For each System Information Block (SIB), indicates when the SIB content is changed, if system information change notification is broadcast prior to broadcast of updated system information.

attribute.name: mappingInfo
attribute.description:
The System Information (SI) message to which each System Information Block (SIB) is mapped.
Note: SIB2 is always mapped to the SI message 1 according to 3GPP TS 36.331.

attribute.name: modificationPeriodCoeff
attribute.description: The modification period, expressed in number of radio frames = modificationPeriodCoeff * defaultPagingCycle. See MO Paging for information about defaultPagingCycle.
attribute.dependencies: modificationPeriodCoeff * defaultPagingCycle must be equal or less than 1024 radio frames. See MO Paging for information about defaultPagingCycle.

attribute.name: siPeriodicity
attribute.description: The periodicity of System Information (SI) messages. If a System Information Block (SIB) is not mapped to a SI message, the SI message is not transmitted.

attribute.name: siWindowLength
attribute.description:
Length of the System Information (SI) window within which each SI message is transmitted. Applies to all SI messages.
Note: An SI window of 1 ms may be configured only when a maximum of 5 SI messages is configured for broadcast by attribute mappingInfo, to avoid collision with SIB1 transmission in subframe #5.
attribute.dependencies: siWindowLength must be 10 ms or above in case PWS SI messages are broadcasted.

attribute.name: qRxLevMin
attribute.description: The required minimum received Reference Symbol Received Power (RSRP) level in the E-UTRA frequency for cell reselection. Corresponds to parameter Qrxlevmin in 3GPP TS 36.304. This attribute is broadcast in SIB1.

attribute.name: minBestCellHoAttempts
attribute.description: Number of attempts for handover to a cell better than the serving cell, before handover is attempted to the next best cell. If there is no next best cell in the UE report, handover to the best cell is attempted repeatedly.

attribute.name: systemInformationBlock6
attribute.description: Contains cell re-selection information common for cell re-selection towards UTRAN.

attribute.name: systemInformationBlock7
attribute.description: Contains cell re-selection information common for cell re-selection towards GERAN.

attribute.name: systemInformationBlock8
attribute.description: Contains cell re-selection information common for cell re-selection towards CDMA2000. This is controlled by the licensing MO Cdma2000SessionContinuity. The SIB8 distribution and information are also controlled by other licenses.

attribute.name: reservedBy
attribute.description: Contains a list of managed object instances that reserves this managed object instance.
attribute.dependencies: The managed object cannot be deleted if it is reserved.

attribute.name: systemInformationBlock3
attribute.description: Contains cell re-selection information common for intra-frequency, inter-frequency and/ or inter-RAT cell re-selection.

attribute.name: ulInterferenceManagementActive
attribute.description: Specifies if uplink interference management is enabled or disabled.

attribute.name: cellBarred
attribute.description: Indicates if the cell is barred and should not be accessible to random UEs.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute to BARRED blocks all traffic in the cell.

attribute.name: dlInterferenceManagementActive
attribute.description: Specifies if the downlink interference management is enabled or disabled.

attribute.name: pMaxServingCell
attribute.description:
Limits UE uplink transmission power in the serving cell and calculates the parameter Pcompensation (defined in 3GPP TS 36.304) for cell selection. The attribute is broadcast in SIB1.
Value 1000 means the parameter is not included in system information.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: pZeroNominalPucch
attribute.description: The nominal component of the UE transmit power for Physical Uplink Control Channel (PUCCH).
attribute.disturbances: Changes may affect traffic.

attribute.name: pZeroNominalPusch
attribute.description: The nominal component of the UE transmit power for Physical Uplink Shared Channel (PUSCH).
attribute.dependencies: Changing the value of pZeroNominalPusch, might have impact on the setting of puschPwrOffset64Qam. See puschPwrOffset64Qam for how that attribute depends on pZeroNominalPusch.
attribute.disturbances: Changes may affect traffic.

attribute.name: qciTableRef
attribute.description:
Refers to an instance of QciTable and assigns a QciTable to a cell. The QciTable defines Quality of Service Class Indicator (QCI) to use in the cell.
Refers to the QciTable instance corresponding to Local Distinguished Name (LDN) = ManagementElement=1, ENodeBFunction=1, QciTable=default
attribute.dependencies: It is assumed that the QciTable MO has been created.

attribute.name: rachRootSequence
attribute.description:
The first root sequence number for Random Access Channel (RACH) preamble generation. RACH root sequence is broadcast as a part of system information distribution and used for preamble detection. See definition for logical root sequence number in 3GPP TS 36.211.
If feature Automated Rach Root Sequence Allocation is not activated a parameter change triggers automatic cell lock/unlock. If feature Automated Rach Root Sequence Allocation is activated the parameter is changed without the need to lock/unlock the cell.
attribute.disturbances: Changes may affect traffic.

attribute.name: availabilityStatus
attribute.description: The availability status. It contains details about operationalState. This attribute is set by the application in the RBS.

attribute.name: operationalState
attribute.description: The operational state. This attribute is set by the application in the RBS.

attribute.name: administrativeState
attribute.description: The administrative state.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute to LOCKED or SHUTTINGDOWN causes loss of traffic.

attribute.name: cellId
attribute.description:
RBS internal ID attribute for EUtranCell. Must be unique in the RBS. Together with the Node ID and Public Land Mobile Network (PLMN) this is a universally unique cell ID.
Range 0-255.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: physicalLayerCellIdGroup
attribute.description:
The physical layer cell ID group. Physical-layer cell IDs are grouped into 168 unique physical-layer cell-identity groups, each group containing 3 unique subidentities.
This attribute together with physicalLayerSubCellId is used to calculate physical layer cell ID (see 3GPP TS 36.211) that is sent as part of the system information (see 3GPP TS 36.331).
attribute.disturbances: Changes may affect traffic

attribute.name: physicalLayerSubCellId
attribute.description:
The subidentity within the physical layer cell ID group. Physical-layer cell IDs are grouped into 168 unique physical-layer cell-identity groups, each group containing 3 unique subidentities.
This attribute together with physicalLayerCellIdGroup is used to calculate physical layer cell identity (see 3GPP TS 36.211) which is sent as part of the system information (see 3GPP TS 36.331).
attribute.disturbances: Changes may affect traffic

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use.

attribute.name: tac
attribute.description: Tracking Area Code for the EUtran Cell.
attribute.disturbances: Changes may affect traffic

attribute.name: drxActive
attribute.description: Indicates if the DRX function in the cell is activated.

attribute.name: networkSignallingValue
attribute.description: Enables additional spectrum emission requirements according to 3GPP TS 36.101, table 6.2.4-1.

attribute.name: initCdma2000SysTimeType
attribute.description: Intended type of CDMA2000 system time to broadcast in SIB8, if applicable.

attribute.name: bcCdma2000SysTimeType
attribute.description: The actual type of CDMA2000 system time that is broadcast in SIB8.

attribute.name: pucchOverdimensioning
attribute.description:
Number of resource blocks outside each Physical Uplink Control Channel (PUCCH) region that are available for scheduling Physical Uplink Shared Channel (PUSCH).
Note: Both the value of this attribute and the amount of resources allocated for PUCCH impacts where the resource allocation of the PRACH starts.

attribute.name: qRxLevMinOffset
attribute.description: The offset applied to the signaled Qrxlevmin. Corresponds to parameter Qrxlevminoffset in 3GPP TS 36.304. Value 1000 means it is not sent and the UE sets Qrxlevminoffset=0dB.

attribute.name: otdoaSuplActive
attribute.description: Indicates if the feature OTDOA Support in SUPL Environment is ACTIVATED or DEACTIVATED in the cell.

attribute.name: prsConfigIndex
attribute.description: The Positioning Reference Signal (PRS) index value for the cell defines the periodicity of the PRS occasions and the PRS subframe offset, as defined in 3GPP TS 36.211. The value -1 (default) means that this parameter will not be used for setting the PRS period and prsSubframeOffset. Instead the parameter prsPeriod shall be used to directly set the PRS period while prsSubframeOffset will be set by the system to guarantee non collision with SIB1.

attribute.name: noConsecutiveSubframes
attribute.description: The number of consecutive downlink sub-frames with positioning reference signals as defined in 3GPP TS 36.211. Values define 1, 2, 4, or 6 consecutive sub-frames.
attribute.dependencies: None

attribute.name: latitude
attribute.description: The degree of latitude of the transmitter antenna position. In case of Combined Cell (multi-sector cell): For indoor system, antenna of any sector. For outdoor system,antenna of macro sector.

attribute.name: longitude
attribute.description: The degree of longitude of the transmitter antenna position. In case of Combined Cell (multi-sector cell): For indoor system, antenna of any sector. For outdoor system,antenna of macro sector.

attribute.name: altitude
attribute.description: The altitude of the transmitter antenna in meters. Use +/- values to denote height/depth. In case of Combined Cell (multi-sector cell): For indoor system, antenna of any sector. For outdoor system,antenna of macro sector.

attribute.name: uncertSemiMajor
attribute.description:
Semi-major axis of uncertainty. The uncertainty (r) is derived from the uncertainty code (k) by:
r = 10 * ((1.1^k) - 1).

attribute.name: uncertSemiMinor
attribute.description:
Semi-minor axis of uncertainty. The uncertainty (r) is derived from the uncertainty code (k) by:
r = 10 * ((1.1^k) - 1).

attribute.name: orientMajorAxis
attribute.description:
Orientation of the major axis of uncertainty, in degrees clockwise from north. Orientation value (N) is derived by the formula:
N <= X < (N + 1)
where X is the orientation in degrees (0 - 180).
attribute.dependencies: None

attribute.name: uncertAltitude
attribute.description: The uncertainty altitude (h) expressed in meters is derived from the uncertainty altitude (k) by h = 45*((1.025)^k - 1).

attribute.name: confidence
attribute.description: Percentage of confidence that the target device is within the ellipsoid defined by the three axes of uncertainty: semi-major, semi-minor, and altitude.
attribute.dependencies: None

attribute.name: gpsTimeSFN0DecimalSecond
attribute.description:
The decimal part of the GPS time for the most recent occurrence of System Frame Number (SFN)=0 in the cell.
Unit: 2^(-32) second

attribute.name: primaryPlmnReserved
attribute.description: Indicates if the primary PLMN ID in the cell is reserved for operator use. The primary PLMN ID is reserved if this attribute is set to true.
attribute.dependencies: the attribute eNodeBPlmnId in the parent ENodeBFunction will hold the value of the primary PLMN ID.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can block traffic in the cell.

attribute.name: additionalPlmnReservedList
attribute.description: For the list of PLMN IDs in the cell, indicates if they are reserved for operator use. The list must have the same number of entries as additonalPlmnList. The PLMN ID appearing in additionalPlmnList[x] is reserved when additionalPlmnListReserved[x] is set to true.
attribute.dependencies: The length of this list must be the same as the list in addtionalPlmnList.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: additionalPlmnList
attribute.description:
Lists additional PLMN IDs supported in the cell.
The list may include up to 5 PLMNs, and they must be the same in all EUtranCells in the node.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: activePlmnList
attribute.description: Lists the PLMN IDs served by at least one MME. The PLMN ID is defined in the attribute eNodeBPlmnId in the parent ENodeBFunction. PLMN IDs from additionalPlmnList also appear in this list. The list may include up to 6 PLMNs.

attribute.name: gpsTimeSFN0Seconds
attribute.description: The integer part of the GPS time for the most recent occurrence of SFN=0 in the cell.

attribute.name: prsPeriod
attribute.description:
The period of Positioning Reference Signal (PRS) occasions. Valid periods include 160 ms, 320 ms, 640 ms and 1280 ms.
prsPeriod is used to calculate the prsConfigIndex to avoid PRS sub-frame collisions with SIB1 sub-frames.

attribute.name: covTriggerdBlindHoAllowed
attribute.description: Says whether a blind Handover from this cell can be initiated when a UE reports bad coverage, or not. Note that even if the value is True, the eNB will only initiate a blind handover if it finds a suitable cell.

attribute.name: dlConfigurableFrequencyStart
attribute.description: Specifies the start frequency offset for the allocation of resources when the downlink interference management is disabled expressed as a percentage of the configured bandwidth.
attribute.dependencies: dlInterferenceManagementActive shall be disabled before this parameter takes effect.

attribute.name: ulConfigurableFrequencyStart
attribute.description: Specifies the start frequency offset for the allocation of resources when the uplink interference management is disabled expressed as a percentage of the configured bandwidth.
attribute.dependencies: ulInterferenceManagementActive shall be disabled before this parameter takes effect.

attribute.name: dlFrequencyAllocationProportion
attribute.description: Specifies the amount of frequency resources that is allocated in DL expressed as a percentage of the configured bandwidth.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: ulFrequencyAllocationProportion
attribute.description: Specifies the amount of frequency resources that is allocated in UL expressed as a percentage of the configured bandwidth.

attribute.name: eutranCellPolygon
attribute.description: Models the manageable characteristics for the cell polygon used for UE positioning. Each polygon corner is described by a latitude and longitude pair. Each polygon corner is represented with one position in the sequence. The other configured polygon corners follow in sequence. There must at least be three corners configured in a polygon when the function is active/used. The points shall be connected in the order that they are given. The last point is connected to the first point.

attribute.name: prsConfigIndexMapped
attribute.description: This parameter holds the resulting prsConfigIndex value. If prsPeriod is used by the operator then prsConfigIndexMapped will be set by the system. If prsConfigIndex is used by the operator then prsConfigIndexMapped will be a copy of the entered value.

attribute.name: eutranCellCoverage
attribute.description:
Models the cell coverage area used for UE positioning. The cell coverage area is defined by the cell bearing, cell opening angle and cell radius.
This attribute has no operational impact.

attribute.name: qQualMin
attribute.description:
Specifies the minimum required quality level (RSRQ) in the cell in dB.
Corresponds to Qqualmin in TS 36.304, sent in SIB1. Value 0 means that it is not sent and UE applies in such case the (default) value of negative infinity for Qqualmin.
attribute.dependencies: The field is mandatory present if the Struct Member threshServingLowQ in SIB3 is used in systemInformationBlockType3.

attribute.name: qQualMinOffset
attribute.description:
The offset applied to the signaled qQualMin.
Corresponds to Qqualminoffset in TS 36.304.
Value 0 means that it is not sent in SIB1 and UE applies in such case the (default) value of 0 dB for Qqualminoffset.
attribute.dependencies: If the value of qQualMin is set to 0 the parameter qQualMinOffset will not be broadcasted.

attribute.name: pdcchCfiMode
attribute.description: Controls the CFI (Control Format Indicator) used for the control region. cfiMode maps to CFI as described under enumerations. For DL BW of 1400 kHz, values of CFI = 1, 2 and 3 map to 2, 3, and 4 control region symbols respectively. Other BW, CFI maps directly to number of control region symbols.
attribute.dependencies: pdcchCfiMode cannot equal CFI_STATIC_1 while dlChannelBandwidth = 1400, 3000, or 5000 kHz since there would be insufficient CCEs to transmit a PDCCH for common channel messages such as SIB1 or SI. Certain values of pdcchCfiMode that allow high CFI values may be disallowed when the combination of attributes pdcchCfiMode, dlChannelBandwidth, noOfPucchCqiUsers, and noOfPucchSrUsers require too many corresponding PUCCH HARQ-ARQ resources.

attribute.name: ulSrsEnable
attribute.description: Controls whether sounding shall be enabled or not for the functionality that supports sounding.

attribute.name: rateShapingActive
attribute.description: Indicates if End-user bitrate shaping functionality is activated in this cell.
attribute.dependencies: Only relevant if the license for End-user bitrate shaping is present and the feature is active.

attribute.name: cellSubscriptionCapacity
attribute.description: Normalized subscription capacity of the cell. The value represents the total capacity of the cell used for traffic load balancing purposes.
attribute.disturbances: Low values reduce cell capacity.

attribute.name: threshServingLow
attribute.description: Specifies the threshold that the signal strength of the serving cell must be below for cell reselection towards a lower priority Inter-Frequency or Inter-RAT frequency. Corresponds to ThreshServingLowP in TS 36.304.

attribute.name: pciConflict
attribute.description: A PCI confusion exists if a source cell has relations to two neighbor cells where both neighbor cells have the same PCI and frequency. A PCI collision exists if a source cell has a relation to a neighbor cell where both the source cell and neighbor cell have the same PCI and frequency.

attribute.name: lastModification
attribute.description: Indicates whether the MO was last modified by the operator or if the MO has been modified by the PCI conflict detection application.

attribute.name: pciConflictCell
attribute.description: Indicates the CGI of the other cell that is involved in the PCI collision/confusion. This value is only valid if the attribute pciConflict is "YES" or "YES_CONFLICTING_CELL".

attribute.name: timeOfLastModification
attribute.description: Indicates the time and date when the MO was last modified. Format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS

attribute.name: cfraEnable
attribute.description: This parameter controls if Contention Free Random Access (CFRA, known as non-contention based random access in 3GPP term) shall be enabled or not. When enabled, a portion of random access preambles should be allocated for CFRA and CFRA can be used for incoming HO and PDCCH ordered uplink re-sync.

attribute.name: acBarringInfoPresent
attribute.description: Specifies presence of Information Element ac-BarringInfo in SIB2.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: acBarringForMoSignalling
attribute.description: Access class barring parameters for mobile originating signalling. The information in broadcasted in SIB2.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can block originating traffic.

attribute.name: acBarringForMoData
attribute.description: Access class barring parameters for mobile originating calls. The information in broadcasted in SIB2.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can block data calls.

attribute.name: ssacBarringForMMTELVoicePresent
attribute.description: Specifies presence of Information Element ssac-BarringForMMTEL-Voice-r9 in SIB2.
attribute.statusInformation: Since 17.Q3. Replaced by AcBarringPresence.acBarringForMmtelVoicePresence in EUtranCellFDD/EUtranCellTDD::acBarringPresence. Planned to be removed.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can block VoLTE calls in the cell.

attribute.name: ssacBarringForMMTELVideoPresent
attribute.description: Specifies presence of Information Element ssac-BarringForMMTEL-Video-r9 in SIB2.
attribute.statusInformation: Since 17.Q3. Replaced by AcBarringPresence.acBarringForMmtelVideoPresence in EUtranCellFDD/EUtranCellTDD::acBarringPresence. Planned to be removed.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can block video calls in the cell.

attribute.name: ssacBarringForMMTELVoice
attribute.description: Service specific access class barring parameters for MMTEL voice originating calls. The information in broadcasted in SIB2.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can block VoLTE calls in the cell.

attribute.name: ssacBarringForMMTELVideo
attribute.description: Service specific access class barring parameters for MMTEL video originating calls. The information in broadcasted in SIB2.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can block video calls in the cell.

attribute.name: acBarringForEmergency
attribute.description: Access class barring for Emergency, which corresponds to access class 10.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can block emergency calls.

attribute.name: pciDetectingCell
attribute.description: Indicates the CGI of the cell that detected the PCI collision/confusion. This value is only valid if the corresponding attribute pciConflict is "YES" or "YES_CONFLICTING_CELL". The first cell in the pciDetectingCell list corresponds to the first cell in the pciConflictCell list and the first value of pciConflict. The second cell in the pciDetectingCell list corresponds to the second cell in the pciConflictCell list and the first value of pciConflict.

attribute.name: emergencyAreaId
attribute.description: A cell that supports broadcast of warning messages can belong to one to 15 Emergency Areas, identified by an Emergency Area Id, set by the operator. Value -1 means identity not set.

attribute.name: hostingDigitalUnit
attribute.description: Shows the DU or Baseband on which baseband processing for the cell is located

attribute.name: highSpeedUEActive
attribute.description: Indicates if the feature High Speed UE is activated in the cell

attribute.name: advCellSupSensitivity
attribute.description: Indicates the sensitivity of the Advanced Cell Supervision function. A higher value will make ACS detect a sleeping cell faster, but with higher risk for false detection. A lower value will make ACS detect a sleeping cell slower, but with lower risk for false detection.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: advCellSupAction
attribute.description: Controls which recovery actions to be performed when ACS detects a sleeping cell.

attribute.name: hoOptStatTime
attribute.description: The operational cycle of the handover optimization function.

attribute.name: hoOptStatNum
attribute.description: The minimal number of handovers required by the handover optimization function before adjusting handover parameters.

attribute.name: mobCtrlAtPoorCovActive
attribute.description: Specifies if the feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage is enabled or disabled in the cell.

attribute.name: sdmActive
attribute.description: Specifies if SDM (Spatial Division Multiplexing) for CombinedCell configuration is activated or not. If SDM is activated, it is possible to multiplex multiple Ues in different sectors in the same time and same frequency resource.
attribute.disturbances: Change can affect traffic

attribute.name: sectorCarrierRef
attribute.description: Reference to a list of instances of SectorCarrier MO.
attribute.disturbances: Change can affect traffic

attribute.name: lbUtranOffloadThreshold
attribute.description: Threshold for eNodeB The value applies for offload towards UTRAN target cells. The eNodeB attempts to offload traffic from the source cell corresponding to the subscription ratio above the threshold.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: externalCdma20001xRttCellRef
attribute.description: Reference to an ExternalCdma20001xRttCell

attribute.name: acBarringForCsfb
attribute.description: Access class barring parameters for mobile originating CSFB calls. The information is broadcasted in SIB2.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: zzzTemporary13
attribute.description: Temporary attributes are intended for temporary solutions, and their usage may vary depending on the installed software. It is strongly recommended to only set the attributes that correspond to a desired functionality and leave all other temporary attributes set to default value. Information in the descriptions about what attributes are in use may be overridden by the information in CPI Info documents. Note that a later release may use another attribute to control the functionality previously provided by a temporary attribute, or may remove the functionality altogether. In these cases, the change is documented in the NIR.
attribute.statusInformation: Since L16A. Replaced by ReportConfigSearch::inhibitA2SearchConfig. Planned to be removed.

attribute.name: pdcchAdmThreshold
attribute.description: Sets the threshold for the CCE usage when ue starts to be rejected. This will only cause real rejects if pdcchAdmEnabled = true. Otherwise we will only step pmCellAdmControlPdcchRejMeas both no rejects will take place.
attribute.statusInformation: Since L16A. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.

attribute.name: pdcchAdmEnabled
attribute.description: Enable the pdcch admission control feature. All rejects will be logged in counter pmCellAdmControlPdcchRej. If set to false we will not reject any Ues due to this function but the potential rejects will be logged in counter pmCellAdmControlPdcchRejMeas.
attribute.statusInformation: Since L16A. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.

attribute.name: serviceAreaId
attribute.description: The MBMS Service Area Identity.
attribute.statusInformation: Since L16B. Replaced by MbsfnArea::serviceAreaId. Planned to be removed.
attribute.dependencies: At least one defined serviceAreaId needs to be configured in the eNB to ENABLE a TermPointToMmeM3

attribute.name: activeServiceAreaId
attribute.description: The active MBMS Service Area Identity. The content of this attribute is either empty or has the value of the attribute MbsfnArea::serviceAreaId for one or more MbsfnArea MOs. Purpose of this attribute is to support OSS SNAD functionality. This attribute is mirrored by OSS to ExternalEUtranCellFDD/TDD.
attribute.dependencies: A (configured) MbsfnArea::serviceAreaId becomes Active ServiceAreaId if: - the MBMS Multicarrier feature is activated - the cell has an unreserved MBSFNAreaCellRelation to an UNLOCKED MBSFNArea - time and phase synchronization accuracy fulfills requirements for LTE Broadcast

attribute.name: pdcchPowerBoostMax
attribute.description: Maximum power boost applied to UE-specific PDCCHs that require more CCEs than the maximum available CCE aggregation level. If UE-specific PDCCHs require equal or less, an automatic power boost algorithm is applied. Attribute pdcchPowerBoostMax does not affect those PDCCHs. If set to 0, there is no PDCCH power boost of the maximum CCE aggregation level. PDCCH coverage is not increased but the feature still optimizes the PDCCH power setting for PDCCHs that require equal or less CCEs than the maximum CCE aggregation level. This still allows for higher PDCCH capacity.

attribute.name: alpha
attribute.description: The pathloss compensation factor for power control of the Physical Uplink Shared Channel (PUSCH).
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: lbEUtranTriggerOffloadThreshold
attribute.description: This attribute is a threshold for eNodeB. The value applies for offload towards EUTRAN target cells. The eNodeB attempts to offload traffic from the source cell to Inter-Frequency LTE neighbors corresponding to the subscription ratio above the threshold.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: lbEUtranAcceptOffloadThreshold
attribute.description: This attribute is a threshold for eNodeB. The value applies in the target cell for incoming offload. The eNodeB accepts incoming offload traffic in the target cell as long as the subscription ratio is below the threshold.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: lbEUtranCellOffloadCapacity
attribute.description: This attribute indicates the offload subscription capacity associated with the EUTRAN target cell. The value is used to moderate the offload rate to the EUTRAN target cell.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: additionalFreqBandList
attribute.description: A list of additional frequency bands the cell belongs to, not including the frequency band indicated by the EARFCN value of the cell (primary frequency band). The list is automatically set by the eNB. These additional frequency bands are broadcasted to the UEs in SystemInformationBlockType1 in case the feature Multiple Frequency Band Indicators is enabled in the cell.

attribute.name: freqBand
attribute.description: The primary frequency band the cell belongs to according to its defined EARFCN.

attribute.name: hoOptAdjThresholdAbs
attribute.description: The absolute threshold value for adjusted handover failure rate required to adjust handover parameters.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can stop outgoing HO.

attribute.name: hoOptAdjThresholdPerc
attribute.description: The permillage threshold value for adjusted handover failure rate required to adjust handover parameters.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can stop outgoing HO.

attribute.name: crsGain
attribute.description:
Sets the DL power of the Cell specific Reference Signal (CRS) relatively a reference level defined by the power of the PDSCH type A resource elements. If crsGain is +3dB, the CRS power is 3dB higher than that of a PDSCH type A resource element.
The settings crsGain=4.77db and 6dB are mapped to 3dB. These settings are not supported.
PDSCH type A resource elements are located in symbols that do not contain CRS.
attribute.dependencies: The crsGain only takes effect if the configured number of antenna ports used in a sector is 2, 4, or 8. In the one port case, crsGain is hardcoded to 0dB.

attribute.name: dynCellSubscrCap
attribute.description: Parameter that contains the automatically estimated cell capacity value. The value 0 indicates that no estimated value exists.

attribute.name: cellCapMinCellSubCap
attribute.description: Minimum value for the estimated cell capacity.
attribute.dependencies: cellCapMinCellSubCap < cellCapMaxCellSubCap

attribute.name: cellCapMaxCellSubCap
attribute.description: Maximum value for the estimated cell capacity.
attribute.dependencies: cellCapMinCellSubCap < cellCapMaxCellSubCap

attribute.name: additionalSpectrumEmissionValues
attribute.description: A list of network signaling values, where each value corresponds to the frequency band on the same position in additionalFreqBandList. Enables additional spectrum emission requirements according to 3GPP TS 36.101, table 6.2.4-1 when the feature Multiple Frequency Band Indicators is enabled in the cell. The content of this list is based on spectrumEmissionReqMapping. This list will be broadcasted in SIB2 as multiBandInfoList.

attribute.name: spectrumEmissionReqMapping
attribute.description: A list which maps frequency bands to network signaling values specifying additional spectrum emissions, as described by 3GPP TS 36.101, table 6.2.4-1. A band which is not explicitly mapped to a network signaling value by this list, will use the value NS_01. This list is used to generate the value of additionalSpectrumEmissionValues.

attribute.name: expectedMaxNoOfUsersInCell
attribute.description: The expected max number of UE in RRC_CONNECTED mode in the cell. Will be used at unlock of the cell to distribute cells to different cores in Digital Units and Baseband Units with a multicore Main Processor. A value of -1 indicates that measuredMaxNoOfUsersInCell will be used to control the cell distribution.

attribute.name: measuredMaxNoOfUsersInCell
attribute.description: Peak number of UE in RRC_CONNECTED mode measured in the cell. This attribute will be updated during operation of the eNB and used at unlock of the cell to distribute cells to different cores in Digital Units and Baseband Units with a multicore Main Processor. If attribute expectedMaxNoOfUsersInCell is changed from -1 to zero or higher, attribute measuredMaxNoOfUsersInCell will be reset to zero and not used to control the cell distribution.

attribute.name: pdcchLaGinrMargin
attribute.description: GINR back-off parameter for PDCCH link adaptation. Applies to all UEs when the feature Enhanced PDCCH Link Adaptation is disabled. In FDD, if the licenses for both Enhanced PDCCH Link Adaptation and Carrier Aggregation are enabled, this parameter applies to secondary cell PDCCH for UEs capable of carrier aggregation. In TDD, if the license for Enhanced PDCCH Link Adaptation is enabled, this parameter applies to: - UEs configured with carrier aggregation, and - UEs configured with HARQ-ACK PUCCH format 3 or HARQ-ACK multiplexing.

attribute.name: initialBufferSizeDefault
attribute.description: The number of bytes that is assumed to be in the UE buffer when an SR is received through PUCCH.

attribute.name: cioUpperLimitAdjBySon
attribute.description: Indicates the upper limit value of cellIndividualOffsetEUtran range that the SON function is allowed to adjust.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can stop outgoing HO.

attribute.name: cioLowerLimitAdjBySon
attribute.description: Indicates the lower limit value of cellIndividualOffsetEUtran range that the SON function is allowed to adjust.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can stop outgoing HO.

attribute.name: servOrPrioTriggeredIFHo
attribute.description: Specifies the trigger used in the feature Service or Priority-Triggered Inter-Frequency Handover.

attribute.name: otdoaCheckEnabled
attribute.description: Determines if the OTDOA functionality should be considered in the feature Service or Priority-Triggered Inter-Frequency Handover.

attribute.name: servOrPrioRedirectEnabled
attribute.description: Indicates if release with redirection is allowed in the feature Service or Priority-Triggered Inter-Frequency Handover.

attribute.name: arpPriorityLevelForSPIFHo
attribute.description: ARP Priority Level list used in the feature Service or Priority-Triggered Inter-Frequency Handover. The first instance in the list is for ARP Priority Level 0, second for 1, and so on. Value "false" means the UE with this bearer is not intended to be moved to other frequency.

attribute.name: lbabIncr
attribute.description: How fast the Access Class Barring probability is increased, that is how fast acBarringFactor in SIB2 is decreased when the cell load is increased.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect when feature Load-Based Access Barring or feature Progressive Access Barring is activated.

attribute.name: acBarringPresence
attribute.description: Specifies if Access Class Barring is present in SIB2.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: lbabThreshTimeHigh
attribute.description: Time period to measure the RRC Connection Reject Ratio with the Load-Based Access Barring threshold lbabThreshRejectRateHigh or the Progressive Access Barring threshold lbabThreshRejectRateHigh.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect when feature Load-Based Access Barring or feature Progressive Access Barring is activated.

attribute.name: lbabThreshTimeLow
attribute.description: Time period to measure RRC Connection Reject Ratio with the Load-Based Access Barring threshold lbabThreshRejectRateLow or the Progressive Access Barring threshold lbabThreshRejectRateLow.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect when feature Load-Based Access Barring or feature Progressive Access Barring is activated.

attribute.name: lbabThreshRejectRateHigh
attribute.description: RRC Connection Reject Ratio when the feature Load-Based Access Barring activates presence of the Access Class Barring parameters in SIB2 or when the feature Progressive Access Barring activates presence of the Access Class Barring parameters in SIB2.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect when feature Load-Based Access Barring or feature Progressive Access Barring is activated.

attribute.name: lbabThreshRejectRateLow
attribute.description: RRC Connection Reject Ratio when the feature Load-Based Access Barring reduces the Access Class Barring probability, that is an increase of acBarringFactor in SIB2 or when the feature Progressive Access Barring activates presence of the Access Class Barring parameters in SIB2.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect when feature Load-Based Access Barring or feature Progressive Access Barring is activated.

attribute.name: lbabDecr
attribute.description: How fast the Access Class Barring probability is decreased, that is how fast acBarringFactor in SIB2 is increased when the cell load is decreased.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect when feature Load-Based Access Barring or feature Progressive Access Barring is activated.

attribute.name: lbabPeriod
attribute.description: Minimum time for how often the acBarringFactor in SIB2 can be changed.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect when feature Load-Based Access Barring or feature Progressive Access Barring is activated.

attribute.name: loadBasedBarringFactor
attribute.description: Current barring factor based on LBAB algorithm or PAB algorithm.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect when feature Load-Based Access Barring or feature Progressive Access Barring is activated.

attribute.name: prsTransmisScheme
attribute.description: Used for selecting whether the PRS transmission must use antenna switching or pre-coder switching.

attribute.name: prsPowerBoosting
attribute.description: Used for selecting the different power boosting alternatives for PRS transmissions. If set to 0, a default table based on the number of PBCH antennas and transmission scheme is shown. If set to 1, 2, or 3, it results in a power boosting of 0 dB, 3 dB, or 6 dB respectively.

attribute.name: prsMutingPatternLen
attribute.description: Used for selecting the length of the PRS muting pattern. Setting the pattern length to 1 results in deactivation of PRS muting. The muting pattern is set to "1111111111111" in this case. Other recommended muting pattern lengths are: 2, 4, 8, and 16 bits.

attribute.name: prsMutingPattern
attribute.description: Used for storing the calculated muting pattern for the cell. This parameter cannot be manually set.

attribute.name: preambleInitialReceivedTargetPower
attribute.description: Initial preamble power value in dBm, according to 3GPP specification 36.331 and 36.321.

attribute.name: servOrPrioTriggeredErabAction
attribute.description: Specifies the action performed when a S1AP:E-RAB SETUP REQUEST arrives and both the feature Service or Priority-Triggered Inter-Frequency Handover is active and the conditions for the bearer request are fulfilled.
attribute.dependencies: This attribute only takes effect when attribute servOrPrioTriggeredIFHo has value 'QCI'.

attribute.name: pdschTypeBGain
attribute.description:
Sets the DL power of the PDSCH type B resource elements relatively the PDSCH type A resource elements. Values pdschTypeBGain=(0,1,2,3) define the gains (5/4,1,3/4,1/2) respectively, corresponding to the multi-antenna scenario specified in 3GPP TS 36.213.
Example: If the pdschTypeBGain is 3 (gain=1/2), the power of the PDSCH type B resource elements is a factor 1/ 2 of the power of the PDSCH type A resource elements.
PDSDH type A resource elements are located in symbols that do not contain cell specific reference signals (CRS). PDSCH type B resource elements are located in symbols that contain CRS.
attribute.dependencies:
The pdschTypeBGain=0 (gain=5/4) is not allowed if crsGain=1.77,3.0, 4.77,6.0 dB. This combination causes over allocation of DL mean radio power and attribute pdschTypeBGain is set to 1 (gain=1).
The pdschTypeBGain only takes effect if the configured number of antenna ports is 2,4, or 8. In the one port case, the power of resource elements for PDSCH type A and B is equal.

attribute.name: incrPrioServingFreqActive
attribute.description: Specifies whether or not the function to set the serving frequency as sticky carrier is active in the current cell.
attribute.statusInformation: Since 17.Q3. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: puschMaxNrOfPrbsPerUe
attribute.description: Maximum number of physical resource blocks allowed on PUSCH for each UE.
attribute.dependencies: This parameter only takes effect if the feature PUCCH Overdimensioning is activated.

attribute.name: dummyCdmaBandClass
attribute.description: Dummy CDMA frequency band in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 information element that can be used to force registration each time the UE moves across LTE and CDMA 1xRTT networks. This can be achieved by setting both this parameter to a dummy band class that is not used in the native CDMA 1xRTT network and by setting the powerUpReg flag to TRUE in SIB-8. The default value of 99 or UNDEFINED_VALUE means the value configured in Cdma2000FreqBand::cdmaBandClass is sent in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 information element which is the same value as the one sent in SIB-8.

attribute.name: ulHarqVolteBlerTarget
attribute.description: The UL BLER target to be used for VoLTE UEs. This BLER target will be used for all UL transmissions for UEs that have a QCI1 bearer configured. If a UE does not have QCI1 bearer configured the normal UL BLER target will be used.

attribute.name: tTimeAlignmentTimer
attribute.description: A timer used for supervision and control of uplink synchronization. Special value: 0 means infinity.

attribute.name: cellCapMinMaxWriProt
attribute.description:
Write protection that prevents feature Automated Cell Capacity Estimation from changing the value on parameters cellCapMinCellSubCap and cellCapMaxCellSubCap.
If set to true, feature Automated Cell Capacity Estimation cannot reset cellCapMinCellSubCap and cellCapMaxCellSubCap at cell unlock. If set to false, feature Automated Cell Capacity Estimation can change cellCapMinCellSubCap and cellCapMaxCellSubCap at cell unlock.

attribute.name: noOfPucchFormat1PrbPairsPerFrame
attribute.description: PRB usage for PUCCH Format1. Based on PUCCH SR, CFI and Carrier Aggregation user configuration.

attribute.name: noOfPucchFormat2PrbPairsPerFrame
attribute.description: PRB usage for PUCCH Format2. Based on PUCCH CQI user configuration.

attribute.name: noOfPucchFormat3PrbPairsPerFrame
attribute.description: PRB usage for PUCCH Format3. Based on 3CC Carrier Aggregation user configuration.

attribute.name: lbTpNonQualFraction
attribute.description: The fraction of non-qualified UEs at UE selection for throughput aware load balancing. In case throughput aware UE selection is enabled, this parameter sets a target size for the fraction of UE to be disqualified for load balancing due to insufficient relative gain when moving UE from source to target cell. Special value 0 means that the throughput aware UE selection for this cell is disabled.

attribute.name: lbTpRankThreshMin
attribute.description: The minimum threshold for the relative gain at throughput aware load balancing. A negative value may allow for some throughput loss for the individual UE, if the load balancing criteria requires so. Higher values may increase the fraction of non-qualified UEs at UE selection for throughput aware load balancing and may cause the load balancing to stall. Special value -100 means the lower boundary for the threshold is disabled.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: primaryPlmnAlarmSuppr
attribute.description:
Indicates if the primary PLMN ID in the cell is suppressed for alarms PLMN Service Degraded and PLMN Service Unavailable when primary PLMN is not available in the cell.
The primary PLMN ID is suppressed if this attribute is set to true.
If the configured PLMN ID is not a served PLMN ID, then the alarm is suppressed independent of the configured settings.

attribute.name: additionalPlmnAlarmSupprList
attribute.description:
The list of PLMN IDs in the cell indicates if they are suppressed for alarms PLMN Service Degraded and PLMN Service Unavailable when PLMN is not available in the cell.
The PLMN ID appearing in additionalPlmnList[x] is suppressed when additionalPlmnAlarmSupprList[x] is true.
If the configured PLMN ID is not a served PLMN ID, then the alarm is suppressed independent of the configured settings.
attribute.dependencies: The length of this list must be the same as the list in addtionalPlmnList.

attribute.name: idleModePrioAtReleaseRef
attribute.description: Reference to an IdleModePrioAtRelease MO. Assigns an IdleModePrioAtRelease to a cell.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: minQciLatencyMeas
attribute.description: Smallest numerical value corresponding to the highest priority of the QCIs included into MAC latency measurements.
attribute.statusInformation: Since L16A. Planned to be removed.
attribute.dependencies: minQciLatencyMeas =< maxQciLatencyMeas

attribute.name: maxQciLatencyMeas
attribute.description: Largest numerical value corresponding to the lowest priority of the QCIs included into MAC latency measurements.
attribute.statusInformation: Since L16A. Planned to be removed.
attribute.dependencies: maxQciLatencyMeas >= minQciLatencyMeas

attribute.name: includeLcgInMacUeThp
attribute.description: Controls the LCGs that are included in pmMacUeThpVolUl, pmMacUeThpTimeUl, and pmMacUeThpUlDistr. To include the n:th LCG, set includeLcgInMacUeThp[n]=true.

attribute.name: acBarringSkipForMmtelVoice
attribute.description: Indicates whether or not access attempts for MMTEL voice from UEs are to skip Access Class Barring functionality.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can block VoLTE calls.

attribute.name: acBarringSkipForMmtelVideo
attribute.description: Indicates whether or not access attempts for MMTEL video from UEs are to skip Access Class Barring functionality.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can block Video calls.

attribute.name: acBarringSkipForSms
attribute.description: Indicates whether or not access attempts for SMS over SGs or SMS over IP from UEs are to skip Access Class Barring functionality.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can block sms.

attribute.name: puschPwrOffset64qam
attribute.description: Power offset to the target-received PUSCH Power Spectral Density (PSD) for 64-QAM-capable UEs. Used to control the received SINR target. It is used to enable maximum throughput for 64QAM, which in some configurations is not possible otherwise, see dependencies.
attribute.dependencies: Only relevant if the license for 64-QAM Uplink is present and the feature is active. For 2Rx, pZeroNominalPusch + puschPwrOffset64qam needs to be -100 dBm or higher to achieve maximum throughput. puschPwrOffset64Qam should be set to 0 when both UL 64QAM and UL MU-MIMO are enabled in eNB.
attribute.disturbances: Changes can affect traffic.

attribute.name: ul64qamEnabled
attribute.description: Enables UL 64-QAM at cell level.
attribute.dependencies: Only relevant if the license for UL 64-QAM is present and the feature is active.

attribute.name: ulDynUeAdmCtrlOverloadThr
attribute.description: Highest allowed UL radio resource utilization ratio for admission of a non-privileged UE. Applies to each UL resource considered by Dynamic UE Admission Control. Resource utilization is checked against this threshold for all new, re-established, or incoming handover RRC connections.
attribute.dependencies: ulDynUeAdmCtrlOverloadThr >= ulDynUeAdmCtrlRetDiffThr
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect the following: - the number of RRC-connected users - cell throughput and the number of rejected non-privileged RRC connection requests - rejected non-privileged RRC connection re-establishment requests and rejected non- privileged incoming handover requests.

attribute.name: dlDynUeAdmCtrlOverloadThr
attribute.description: Highest allowed DL radio resource utilization ratio for admission of a non-privileged UE. Applies to each DL resource considered by Dynamic UE Admission Control. Resource utilization is checked against this threshold for all new, re-established, or incoming handover RRC connections.
attribute.dependencies: dlDynUeAdmCtrlOverloadThr >= dlDynUeAdmCtrlRetDiffThr
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect the following: - the number of RRC-connected users - cell throughput and the number of rejected non-privileged RRC connection requests - rejected non-privileged RRC connection re-establishment requests and rejected non-privileged incoming handover requests.

attribute.name: cceDynUeAdmCtrlOverloadThr
attribute.description: Highest allowed control channel element radio resource utilization ratio for admission of a non-privileged UE. Resource utilization is checked against this threshold for all new, re-established, or incoming handover RRC connections.
attribute.dependencies: cceDynUeAdmCtrlOverloadThr >= cceDynUeAdmCtrlRetDiffThr
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect the following: - the number of RRC-connected users - cell throughput and the number of rejected non-privileged RRC connection requests - rejected non-privileged RRC connection re-establishment requests and rejected non-privileged incoming handover requests.

attribute.name: ulDynUeAdmCtrlRetDiffThr
attribute.description: Highest allowed UL radio resource utilization ratio for admission of a new non-privileged UE. Applies to each UL resource considered by Dynamic UE Admission Control. Resource utilization is checked against this threshold for all new RRC connections.
attribute.dependencies: ulDynUeAdmCtrlRetDiffThr =< ulDynUeAdmCtrlOverloadThr
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect the following: - the number of RRC-connected users - cell throughput and the number of rejected non-privileged RRC connection requests.

attribute.name: dlDynUeAdmCtrlRetDiffThr
attribute.description: Highest allowed DL radio resource utilization ratio for admission of a new non-privileged UE. Applies to each DL resource considered by Dynamic UE Admission Control. Resource utilization is checked against this threshold for all new RRC connections.
attribute.dependencies: dlDynUeAdmCtrlRetDiffThr =< dlDynUeAdmCtrlOverloadThr
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect the following: - the number of RRC-connected users - cell throughput and the number of rejected non-privileged RRC connection requests.

attribute.name: cceDynUeAdmCtrlRetDiffThr
attribute.description: Highest allowed control channel element radio resource utilization ratio for admission of a new non-privileged UE. Resource utilization is checked against this threshold for all new RRC connections.
attribute.dependencies: cceDynUeAdmCtrlRetDiffThr =< cceDynUeAdmCtrlOverloadThr
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect the following: - the number of RRC-connected users - cell throughput and the number of rejected non-privileged RRC connection requests.

attribute.name: dynUeAdmCtrlFilterConst
attribute.description: Time constant of the exponential-weighted moving average filter applied to the radio resource utilization ratios considered by Dynamic UE Admission Control.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect the following: - the number of RRC-connected users - cell throughput and the number of rejected non-privileged RRC connection requests - rejected non-privileged RRC connection re-establishment requests and rejected non-privileged incoming handover requests.

attribute.name: dynUeAdmCtrlEnabled
attribute.description: Enable Dynamic UE Admission Control at cell level.
attribute.dependencies: Only relevant if the license for Dynamic UE Admission Control is present and the feature is active.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect the following: - the number of RRC-connected users - cell throughput and the number of rejected non-privileged RRC connection requests - rejected non-privileged RRC connection re-establishment requests and rejected non-privileged incoming handover requests.

attribute.name: servOrPrioIFHoSetupBearer
attribute.description: Determines whether a bearer that fulfills the criteria for the feature Service- or Priority-Triggered Inter-Frequency Handover is set up, or rejected in UE .

attribute.name: networkSignallingValueCa
attribute.description: Enables additional spectrum emission requirements for CA according to 3GPP TS 36.101, table 6.2.4A-1.

attribute.name: elcEnabled
attribute.description: Enables Ericsson Lean Carrier functionality in the cell.
attribute.dependencies: Only relevant if the licence for ELC is present and the feature is active.

attribute.name: cellDownlinkCaCapacity
attribute.description: Normalized downlink cell capacity available for use by carrier aggregation. The value is used to calculate the aggregated capacity of a UE:s possible aggregation possibilities, for example by the CA Aware IFLB feature.

attribute.name: estCellCapUsableFraction
attribute.description:
Scaling factor for the estimated cell subscription capacity. Can be used to reduce the traffic load balancing attraction of the cell. Used if traffic handling capacity of the cell is constrained by circumstances the ACCE feature is unable to capture. An example of such a circumstance is at limited UL capacity in a TDD cell.
When the attribute is value is set to 0, the corresponding cell uses the value cellSubscriptionCapacity as the Cell Subscription Capacity value for the cell. This bypasses the automatically estimated Cell Subscription Capacity value for the cell.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: maxSoftLockBackoffTime
attribute.description: Indicates a maximum handover backoff time. The value is applied to inhibit further handover attempts to a EUTRAN target cell that rejects incoming handover for soft-lock of cell.

attribute.name: ailgAutoRestartEnabled
attribute.description: If set to true, AILG is automatically restarted when: - cell disabled followed by cell enabled, for example at node start or restart.

attribute.name: ulBlerTargetEnabled
attribute.description: Turns feature Configurable UL BLER Target on and off.

attribute.name: rtpTimeout
attribute.description: Enables operator configuration of the RTP timeout value at the eNodeB at a cell level that corresponds to the RTP timeout value get set at the IMS layer.

attribute.name: dl256QamEnabled
attribute.description: Enable or disable 256 QAM support in DL.

attribute.name: dl256QamStatus
attribute.description: Indication if 256 QAM in DL is supported in the cell.

attribute.name: maxNoClusteredPuschAlloc
attribute.description: Maximum number of UEs with Clustered PUSCH allocations allowed in a TTI.

attribute.name: clusteredPuschMprFactor
attribute.description: Multiplication factor applied to the 3GPP-defined Maximum Power Reduction values for Clustered PUSCH. Low settings imply high usage of Clustered PUSCH, high settings imply the opposite.

attribute.name: enableUeAssistedAdaptiveDrx
attribute.description: Enable or disable the UE-Assisted Adaptive DRX feature.

attribute.name: enableUeAssistedSigReduction
attribute.description: Enable or disable the UE-Assisted Signaling Reduction feature.

attribute.name: spifhoSetupBearerAtInitialCtxtSetup
attribute.description: Decides if a bearer handled by the feature Service or Priority Triggered Inter-Frequency Handover (SPIFHO) is set up at Initial Context Setup even when attribute servOrPrioIFHoSetupBearer is false.
attribute.dependencies: The value of this attribute is only considered when the value of servOrPrioIFHoSetupBearer=false.

attribute.name: allocThrPucchFormat1
attribute.description: Threshold in terms of number of remaining SR resources available for the cell. Below this threshold, allocTimerPucchFormat1 for allocation of an additional PUCCH format 1 PRB pair is triggered. Occurs if feature Dynamic PUCCH is activated. Value 0 means the dynamic PUCCH allocation/deallocation operation for this cell is disabled.

attribute.name: allocTimerPucchFormat1
attribute.description: A guard time. After this time, a PUCCH format 1 PRB pair is allocated if threshold allocThrPucchFormat1 is still passed.

attribute.name: deallocThrPucchFormat1
attribute.description: Threshold in terms of number of remaining SR resources available for the cell. Above this threshold, deallocTimerPucchFormat1 for deallocation of a PUCCH format 1 PRB pair is triggered. Occurs if feature Dynamic PUCCH is activated.

attribute.name: deallocTimerPucchFormat1
attribute.description: A guard time. After this time, a PUCCH format 1 PRB pair is deallocated if threshold deallocThrPucchFormat1 is still passed.

attribute.name: primaryPsdOffset
attribute.description: Offset value that controls the maximum allowed difference between pZeroNominalPusch and the received power below pZeroNominalPusch in the primary sector when UL CoMP is used.

attribute.name: outOfCoverageThreshold
attribute.description: Threshold for when UE is considered to be Out Of Coverage (OOC). If the number of OOC trigger events is greater than or equal to the threshold, the UE is in the OOC state; if the number of OOC trigger events is less than the threshold, the UE is not in the OOC state.

attribute.name: outOfCoverageSrTimerPeriodicity
attribute.description: Repetition rate of UL sparse grants that are eNodeB-triggered to Out Of Coverage (OOC) UEs.

attribute.name: ulSchedCtrlForOocUesEnabled
attribute.description: Enables feature UL Scheduling Control for Out Of Coverage (OOC) UEs.

attribute.name: resourcePartitionGroupRef
attribute.description: Reference to an instance of ResourcePartitionGroup MO.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.
