attribute.name: ulTrigActive
attribute.description: Specifies if outgoing uplink-triggered mobility actions are enabled or disabled in the cell. Used when Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is enabled. The parameter has effect if Mobility Control in Poor Coverage is enabled and mobCtrlAtPoorCovActive is set to true in the cell.

attribute.name: pdcchCovImproveSrb
attribute.description: PDCCH DCI format 1A is used for SRB to increase transmission success rate and to minimize interruption time.

attribute.name: pdcchCovImproveQci1
attribute.description: PDCCH DCI format 1A to increase MOS for QCI1 in high interference or high path loss scenarios.

attribute.name: pdcchCovImproveDtx
attribute.description: PDCCH DCI format 1A for first re-transmission due to DTX of SRB and QCI1.

attribute.name: ulSCellPriority
attribute.description: Relative priority in initial SCell selection for cells that can be configured with UL Carrier Aggregation. Applicable where several SCells are initially configured simultaneously. Lowest value has highest priority.

attribute.name: prioAdditionalFreqBandList
attribute.description: List of additional frequency bands the cell belongs to. Primary frequency band, EARFCN value of the cell, is not included. Secondary cell evaluation is done according to list order, and/or the list is broadcasted in SIB1. Highest priority band is position 0 in the list.
attribute.dependencies: List only contains frequency bands from additionalFreqBandList.

attribute.name: srDetectHighThres
attribute.description: Defines how many dB higher than the original SR detection threshold can be used as high SR detection threshold. Used together with srProcessingLevel to reduce false SR detection.

attribute.name: srProcessingLevel
attribute.description: Defines how many SRs eNodeB must receive in a row in order to process it. Used together with srDetectHighThres to reduce false SR detection.

attribute.name: adaptiveCfiHoProhibit
attribute.description: Controls adaptive CFI to avoid using CFI=1 or CFI=1,2, when scheduling UEs that are in handover. The highest CFI value in available CFI values determined by pdcchCfiMode is not prohibited.
attribute.dependencies: Applicable only when attribute pdcchCfiMode is set to CFI_AUTO_MAXIMUM_2 or CFI_AUTO_MAXIMUM_3.

attribute.name: lastSchedLinkAdaptEnabled
attribute.description: Controls if link adaptation function allocates largest possible resource to last scheduled UE in the DL. Used to improve UE decoding success rate with reduced code rate.

attribute.name: pdschMaxNrOfPrbsPerUe
attribute.description: Maximum number of physical resource blocks (PRBs) allowed on PDSCH for each UE. Note: If the set value is larger than the system bandwidth, then the system bandwidth value will be used instead. For PDSCH resource allocation type 0, the actual maximum number of PRBs that is allocated will be a multiple of RBGs (Resource Block Groups) that is nearest to the set value but without exceeding it.

attribute.name: mappingInfoBr
attribute.description: SI message to which each SIB is mapped. Note: SIB2 is always mapped to SI message 1 according to 3GPP TS 36.331.
attribute.statusInformation: Since 17.Q4. Planned to be removed.

attribute.name: siValidityTimeBr
attribute.description: SI validity timer. The timer is set to 3h or 24h.

attribute.name: qRxLevMinCe
attribute.description: Min received RSRP level in E-UTRA frequency for cell reselection for UE in enhanced coverage mode. Corresponds to parameter Qrxlevmin_CE in 3GPP TS 36.304. This attribute is broadcast in SIB1-BR.

attribute.name: qQualMinRsrqCe
attribute.description:
Min quality level (RSRQ) in cell for UE in enhanced coverage mode.
Corresponds to Qqualmin_CE in TS 36.304, sent in SIB1-BR. If 0, it is not sent and UE applies default value of negative infinity for Qqualmin_CE.

attribute.name: dynUlResourceAllocEnabled
attribute.description: Enables Dynamic uplink resource allocation on cell level.
attribute.dependencies: Only relevant if license UlDynamicResourceAllocation is present and feature is active.

attribute.name: enableSinrUplinkClpc
attribute.description: Specifies if SINR-based UL power control can be used or not. If enabled, SNR-based closed-loop power control and SINR-based closed-loop power control can be adaptively selected.
attribute.dependencies: Attribute only has effect if feature Differential Uplink Power Control is activated.

attribute.name: rxSinrTargetClpc
attribute.description: SINR target value for SINR-based UL closed-loop power control.
attribute.dependencies: SINR target only has effect if attribute enableSinrUplinkClpc is true.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: interferenceThresholdSinrClpc
attribute.description: Threshold value for measured noise plus interference level. If measured noise plus interference is higher than interferenceThresholdSinrClpc, then SINR-based UL closed-loop power control can be considered.
attribute.dependencies: Threshold only has effect if attribute enableSinrUplinkClpc is true.

attribute.name: ulPsdLoadThresholdSinrClpc
attribute.description: Threshold of UL transmission power per PRB. If averaged UL transmission power measurement per PRB is lower than ulPsdLoadThresholdSinrClpc over a set percentage of UL bandwidth, then SINR-based UL closed-loop power control can be considered.
attribute.dependencies: Threshold only has effect if attribute enableSinrUplinkClpc is true.

attribute.name: zzzTemporary51
attribute.description: Temporary attributes are intended as temporary solutions. Their usage can vary depending on the installed software. It is strongly recommended to only set the attributes that correspond to a desired functionality and leave all other temporary attributes set to default value. Information in the descriptions about what attributes are in use can be overridden by the information in CPI documents. Note that a later release can use another attribute to control functionality previously provided by a temporary attribute, or can remove functionality altogether. In these cases, the change is documented in the NIR.
attribute.statusInformation: Since 18.Q1. Replaced by ns05FullBandSchedEnabled. Planned to be removed.

attribute.name: zzzTemporary52
attribute.description: Temporary attributes are intended as temporary solutions. Their usage can vary depending on the installed software. It is strongly recommended to only set the attributes that correspond to a desired functionality and leave all other temporary attributes set to default value. Information in the descriptions about what attributes are in use can be overridden by the information in CPI documents. In these cases, the change is documented in the NIR.
attribute.statusInformation: Since 18.Q1. Replaced by ns05FullBandUsersInCellThres. Planned to be removed.

attribute.name: caPrioThreshold
attribute.description: The threshold number of SCells configured using prioritized SCell selection. When the number of SCells configured for UEs connected in this PCell is higher than caPrioThreshold, all frequency carriers configured for carrier aggregation are assumed to have equal priority regardless of the configured values.
attribute.dependencies: Only applicable when CarrierAggregationFunction::dynamicSCellSelectionMethod == PRIORITIZED.

attribute.name: measBasedElcControl
attribute.description: Enables or disables measurement-based Ericsson Lean Carrier Control.
attribute.dependencies: Only relevant if license Ericsson Lean Carrier is present and feature is active.

attribute.name: pdcchOuterLoopInitialAdj
attribute.description: The initial value for PDCCH outer loop adjustment for UEs that do not have any secondary cell configured and do not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP. In TDD, this parameter applies only to UEs which are configured with HARQ-ACK bundling.

attribute.name: pdcchOuterLoopInitialAdjVolte
attribute.description: The initial value for PDCCH outer loop adjustment for UEs with any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP. In TDD, this parameter applies only to UEs which are configured with HARQ-ACK bundling.

attribute.name: pdcchOuterLoopInitialAdjPCell
attribute.description: The initial value for primary cell PDCCH outer loop adjustment in case of carrier aggregation. This applies to UEs that have at least one secondary cell configured and do not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP. In TDD, this parameter is not used.

attribute.name: pdcchOuterLoopUpStep
attribute.description: PDCCH outer loop up step size for UEs that do not have any secondary cell configured and do not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP. In TDD, this parameter applies only to UEs which are configured with HARQ-ACK bundling.

attribute.name: pdcchOuterLoopUpStepVolte
attribute.description: PDCCH outer loop up step size for UEs with any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP. In TDD, this parameter applies only to UEs which are configured with HARQ-ACK bundling.

attribute.name: pdcchOuterLoopUpStepPCell
attribute.description: PDCCH outer loop up step size for primary cells in case of carrier aggregation. This applies to UEs that have at least one secondary cell configured and do not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP. In TDD, this parameter is not used.

attribute.name: pdcchTargetBler
attribute.description: PDCCH target error rate for UEs that do not have any secondary cell configured and do not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP. In TDD, this parameter applies only to UEs which are configured with HARQ-ACK bundling.

attribute.name: pdcchTargetBlerVolte
attribute.description: PDCCH target error rate for UEs with any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP. In TDD, this parameter applies only to UEs which are configured with HARQ-ACK bundling.

attribute.name: pdcchTargetBlerPCell
attribute.description: PDCCH target error rate for primary cells in case of carrier aggregation. This applies to UEs that have at least one secondary cell configured and do not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP. In TDD, this parameter is not used.

attribute.name: eDrxAllowed
attribute.description: Set to true when idle mode eDRX shall be allowed in the cell.

attribute.name: elcLongDrxCycle
attribute.description: Long DRX cycle for ELC. Value of elcLongDrxCycle is in number of sub-frames.
attribute.dependencies: Feature Ericsson Lean Carrier is present active.

attribute.name: tReorderingAutoConfiguration
attribute.description:
Enable automatic configuration of tReorderingDl and tReorderingUl. Configuration is based on HARQ-interval together with an offset defined by harqOffsetDl/harqOffsetUl.tReordering >= 'Max number of HARQ' * HARQ-interval + harqOffset, where closest higher or equal allowed value is used.
This configuration is only applied to UM bearers. AM bearers will still use tReorderingUl and tReorderingDl from QciProfilePredefined or QciProfileOperatorDefined.

attribute.name: harqOffsetDl
attribute.description: Offset used when tReorderingDl is calculated by automatic configuration. tReorderingDl = 'Max number of HARQ for DL' * HARQ-interval + harqOffsetDl.

attribute.name: harqOffsetUl
attribute.description: Offset used when tReorderingUl is calculated by automatic configuration. tReorderingUl = 'Max number of HARQ for UL' * HARQ-interval + harqOffsetUl.

attribute.name: enableDrxAwareRlcArq
attribute.description: Enables function to automatically adapt t-PollretransmitTimer to the time it takes to complete HARQ procedure + harqOffset (UL and DL).

attribute.name: enableServiceSpecificHARQ
attribute.description: Enable/disable service-specific HARQ on cell level. Function must have valid license.

attribute.name: lessPrbUsageThreshold
attribute.description: Maximum downlink PRB usage that scheduling stays on-hold for Low Energy Scheduler Solution.

attribute.name: dlBlerTargetEnabled
attribute.description: Turns on/off Configurable DL BLER Target.

attribute.name: interEnbUlCompUserSelSinrThr
attribute.description: SINR threshold for inter-eNodeB UL CoMP user selection.
attribute.dependencies: Must be used together with interEnbUlCompUserSelSinrHys.
attribute.disturbances: If changed, system performance can be affected. As values go higher, more candidates are selected for Inter-eNodeB Uplink CoMP, but more user measurements are triggered. This impacts MP load and transport load over X2.

attribute.name: interEnbUlCompUserSelSinrHys
attribute.description: Hysteresis of SINR threshold for inter-eNodeB UL CoMP user selection.
attribute.dependencies: Must be used together with interEnbUlCompUserSelSinrThr.
attribute.disturbances: If changed, system performance can be affected. As values get bigger, gaps for triggering Inter-eNodeB Uplink CoMP user switching get bigger.

attribute.name: ulTxPsdDistrThr
attribute.description: Threshold for % of PRBs with "UL Tx power per PRB >= ulPsdLoadThresholdSinrClpc" during measSinrClpcPeriod. Below threshold means low cell power load and then SINR based UL closed-loop power control can be considered.
attribute.dependencies: Attribute enableSinrUplinkClpc must be true.

attribute.name: commonSFAllocList
attribute.description: Shows the subframes that are reserved for MBSFN in DL.

attribute.name: ulImprovedUeSchedLastEnabled
attribute.description: Whether or not UL scheduler is enabled to force allocation of PRBs to Data-Aware, UL-Scheduling UEs last.

attribute.name: noOfUlImprovedUe
attribute.description: Number of data-aware UL-scheduling UEs that can be improved at allocation of PDCCH and PUSCH.

attribute.name: ulImprovedUeAdapRetransEnabled
attribute.description: Whether or not UL-scheduler is enabled that uses adaptive re-transmission more frequently for data-aware UL-scheduling UEs, to reduce fragments in UL spectrum.
attribute.statusInformation: Since 17.Q3. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.

attribute.name: bsrThreshold
attribute.description: Threshold used to help identify data-aware UL scheduling UEs. If BSR >= bsrThreshold, UE becomes candidate UE for UL improvement.

attribute.name: tUeBlockingTimer
attribute.description: Length of time eNodeB rejects traffic requests from non-privileged UEs when detecting high procedure latency. Used in Procedure Latency Supervision. Privileged traffic, such as High Priority Access (HPA) and Emergency, is never rejected due to high procedure latency conditions.

attribute.name: sCellHpueEnabled
attribute.description: Whether or not SCell selection for high power UE that is not capable of CA simultaneously is enabled.
attribute.statusInformation: Since 17.Q3. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.

attribute.name: zzzTemporary63
attribute.description: Temporary attribute intended for temporary solution. Usage depends on the installed software. Only set this attribute when it corresponds to a desired functionality and leave all other temporary attributes set to default values. Information in the descriptions about the used attributes can be overridden by information in CPI documents. Note that a later release can use another attribute or completely remove the functionality. Changes are documented in the NIR.

attribute.name: lbabBarringPriorityLevel
attribute.description: Current barring priority level based on PAB algorithm.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect when feature Progressive Access Barring is activated.

attribute.name: lbabMinBarringFactor
attribute.description: Minimum barring factor for LBAB algorithm, or PAB algorithm, priority level 0.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect when feature Load-Based Access Barring or feature Progressive Access Barring is activated.

attribute.name: lbabMinBarringFactorPrio1
attribute.description: Minimum barring factor for PAB algorithm, priority level 1.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect when feature Progressive Access Barring is activated.

attribute.name: lbabMinBarringFactorPrio2
attribute.description: Minimum barring factor for PAB algorithm, priority level 2.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect when feature Progressive Access Barring is activated.

attribute.name: physicalLayerCellId
attribute.description: Physical-layer cell ID.
attribute.dependencies: Equal to 3 x physicalLayerCellIdGroup + physicalLayerSubCellId.

attribute.name: prioHpueCapability
attribute.description: Priority of high power UE capability.

attribute.name: noOfEnhAdptReTxCand
attribute.description: Threshold used in restrict SE number that enhanced adaptive Retransmission candidates, if there are too many non-adaptive retransmission candidates, only "noOfEnhAdptReTxCand" numbers SE can be the enhanced adaptive retransmission queue. Maximum number of SEs added to the enhanced adaptive retransmission queue as candidates. If set to -1, number of candidates is automatically decided by eNodeB. If set to 0, no UEs added to queue and thus feature has no effect.

attribute.name: mappingInfoCe
attribute.description: SI message to which each SIB is mapped. Note: SIB2 is always mapped to SI message 1 according to 3GPP TS 36.331.

attribute.name: prescheduling
attribute.description: Whether or not prescheduling is enabled.

attribute.name: eranUlCompUserSelSinrThr
attribute.description: SINR threshold for Elastic RAN UL CoMP user selection.
attribute.dependencies: Must be used together with eranUlCompUserSelSinrHys.

attribute.name: eranUlCompUserSelSinrHys
attribute.description: Hysteresis of SINR threshold for Elastic RAN UL CoMP user selection.
attribute.dependencies: Must be used together with eranUlCompUserSelSinrThr.

attribute.name: cellResourceRef
attribute.description: References to an instance of CellResource MO.
attribute.statusInformation: Since 18.Q2. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.
attribute.dependencies: CellResource MO having non empty plmnList and CellResource MO having non empty spidList shouldn't be referred together(CellResource MO having empty plmnList and empty spidList is considered as configuring spidList(non empty spidList)). Duplication of PLMN or SPID within referred CellResouce MOs is not allowed.

attribute.name: liteMcsReduction
attribute.description: LiteMcsReduction feature mode.

attribute.name: zzzTemporary67
attribute.description: Temporary attribute intended for temporary solution. Usage depends on the installed software. Only set this attribute when it corresponds to a desired functionality and leave all other temporary attributes set to default values. Information in the descriptions about the used attributes can be overridden by information in CPI documents. Note that a later release can use another attribute or completely remove the functionality. Changes are documented in the NIR.

attribute.name: measCellGroupCellRef
attribute.description: References to an instance of MeasCellGroup MO for grouping on a cell basis.
attribute.dependencies: MeasCellGroup having "0" groupId should not be referred.

attribute.name: iuaEnabled
attribute.description: Enables Instant Uplink Access (IUA) for a cell.

attribute.name: iuaInterval
attribute.description: Time interval between UL short-SPS (semi-persistent scheduling) instances. Value 0 means load based selection of IUA interval.
attribute.dependencies: In MO EUtranCellFDD, only values 0,1,2,4 are allowed. In MO EUtranCellTDD, only values 0,1,5 are allowed.

attribute.name: iuaMaxResourcePerCell
attribute.description: Maximum percentage of UL PRBs and SEs that are used by IUA at cell level. The actual number of resources per cell depends on iuaMaxResourcePerBbm.

attribute.name: iuaMaxPrbsPerUe
attribute.description: Maximum UL PRBs that are used by an IUA UE. The actual number of PRBs per UE depends on iuaMaxResourcePerCell.

attribute.name: ns05FullBandSchedEnabled
attribute.description: Enables PUSCH 100 PRBs scheduling.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect if: - license for NS 05 Additional Maximum Power Reduction Support is present and the feature is active, and - attribute networkSignallingValue in MOC EUtranCellFDD/TDD is NS_05.

attribute.name: ns05FullBandUsersInCellThres
attribute.description: Value of threshold to enable the PUSCH 100 PRBs scheduling. PUSCH 100 PRBs scheduling is triggered when the number of UE in RRC_CONNECTED mode in the cell is less than or equal to ns05FullBandUsersInCellThres.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect if: - license for NS 05 Additional Maximum Power Reduction Support is present and the feature is active, and - attribute networkSignallingValue in MOC EUtranCellFDD/TDD is NS_05, and - attribute ns05FullBandSchedEnabled in MOC EUtranCellFDD/TDD is true.

attribute.name: ns05LowBandSchedMode
attribute.description: Controls if the low band can be allocated to NS_05 UEs. When ns05LowBandSchedMode is configured to 'ALWAYS_PROHIBIT', the low band cannot be allocated to the NS_05 UEs. When ns05LowBandSchedMode is configured to 'ALWAYS_AVAILABLE', the low band can always be allocated to the NS_05 UEs. When ns05LowBandSchedMode is configured to 'ADAPTIVE_AVAILABLE_BY_REPEATER_DETECTION', the low band can only be allocated to the NS_05 UEs which are detected as not in repeater zone.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect if: - license for NS 05 Additional Maximum Power Reduction Support is present and the feature is active, and - attribute networkSignallingValue in MOC EUtranCellFDD/TDD is NS_05.

attribute.name: ns05PathlossOffsetThres
attribute.description: Value of threshold to detect if the NS_05 UE is in repeater zone. If the NS_05 UE's pathloss measured on low band is bigger than or equal to the value of other band plus ns05PathlossOffsetThres, the NS_05 UE is detected as in repeater zone.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect if: - license for NS 05 Additional Maximum Power Reduction Support is present and the feature is active, and - attribute networkSignallingValue in MOC EUtranCellFDD/TDD is NS_05, and - attribute ns05LowBandSchedMode is ADAPTIVE_AVAILABLE_BY_REPEATER_DETECTION.

attribute.name: srvccDelayTimer
attribute.description: The length of time the eNodeB delays Single Radio Voice Call Continuity (SRVCC) handover. Value 0 means no delay.

attribute.name: voiceMeasAccEnabled
attribute.description: Enables voice IRAT measurement acceleration in the cell.
attribute.dependencies: Only relevant if mobCtrlAtPoorCovActive is set to true.

attribute.name: hpueCaSwitchThres
attribute.description: SINR threshold for triggering a switch to high power UE.

attribute.name: hpueCaSwitchHyst
attribute.description: Hysteresis of SINR threshold for triggering a switch to high power UE.

attribute.name: hpueCaSwitchTimeToTrigger
attribute.description: Time-to-trigger value for UL measurement in switching between High Power UE to Carrier Aggregation.

attribute.name: additionalMultipleNSPmax
attribute.description: The attribute in broadcast in SIB1 as multiBandInfoList-v10j0. A list of additionalPmax and additionalSpectrumEmission values. If E-UTRAN includes multiBandInfoList-v10j0, it includes the same number of entries, and listed in the same order, as in multiBandInfoList.

attribute.name: multipleNSPmaxReqMapping
attribute.description: A list which maps frequency bands to additional Pmax value, and additional spectrum emissions as described by 3GPP TS 36.101, table 6.2.4-1. This list is used to generate the value of additionalMultipleNSPmax.
attribute.disturbances: Changing the pMax value for additional band can cause loss of traffic. additionalPMax in MultipleNSPmaxReqMapping structure indicates the pMax value.

attribute.name: dlPowerRampUpInitialRatio
attribute.description: Initial ratio for downlink output power to start power ramp up. Value 100 indicates full cell coverage.

attribute.name: dlPowerRampUpRate
attribute.description: Power ramp up rate per second for downlink output power to reach full cell coverage.

attribute.name: puschNcpChannelEstWindowSize
attribute.description: Normal or Large Window Size for PUSCH filter channel estimation for normal CP.

attribute.name: useBandPrioritiesInSib1
attribute.description:
If enabled, prioritized additional frequency band list is broadcast in SIB1 according to priorities set in EUtranCellFDD::prioAdditionalFreqBandList or in EUtranCellTDD::prioAdditionalFreqBandList. The priorities must be valid.
If disabled, EUtranCellFDD::additionalFreqBandList or EUtranCellTDD::additionalFreqBandList is used.
attribute.precondition: eNodeB must support Multiple Frequency Band Indicators feature.

class.name: EUtranCellRelation
class.description: This managed object represents the handover relationship between two neighboring EUTRAN cells.

attribute.name: eUtranCellRelationId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: cellIndividualOffsetEUtran
attribute.description: Offset value for the neighbor cell. Used when UE is in connected mode. This attribute can be modified by SON functions.

attribute.name: neighborCellRef
attribute.description: Reference to an instance of EUtranCellFDD, ExternalEUtranCellFDD, EUtranCellTDD or ExternalEUtranCellTDD managed object.

attribute.name: isHoAllowed
attribute.description: Specifies if handover between the cells in this relation is allowed.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute to false stops outgoing HO.

attribute.name: qOffsetCellEUtran
attribute.description: Offset value applied to a specific cell in idle mode mobility state.

attribute.name: isRemoveAllowed
attribute.description: Indicates if the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function is allowed to remove this object. It does not restrict operator removal of the object. Objects created by ANR have this parameter set to true initially.

attribute.name: includeInSystemInformation
attribute.description:
Indicates if the referred cell is included in System Information.
When the attribute is set to false, the cell is not included in either freqNeighList or blackCellList in SIB4 or SIB5.

attribute.name: coverageIndicator
attribute.description: Indicates whether the coverage area of the cell indicated by the relation has approximately the same coverage area (overlap) as this cell, or whether it fully covers this cell, or if it is fully contained in this cell.
attribute.disturbances: Changes may affect traffic

attribute.name: createdBy
attribute.description: Indicates whether the MO has been created by the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function or operator or X2

attribute.name: timeOfCreation
attribute.description: Indicates the time and date when the MO was created. Format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS

attribute.name: lastModification
attribute.description: Indicates whether the MO was last modified by the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function or operator or X2 and if the MO is to be deleted who triggered the deletion

attribute.name: timeOfLastModification
attribute.description: Indicates the time and date when the MO was last modified. Format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS

attribute.name: loadBalancing
attribute.description: This attribute indicates whether Inter-Frequency Load Balancing is ALLOWED or NOT_ALLOWED or if Inter-Frequency Offload shall be applied from the current cell to the cell indicated by the cell relation.

attribute.name: sCellCandidate
attribute.description:
SCell candidate status.
The value indicates whether the cell indicated by parameter cellrelation can be used as SCell for UEs using this cell as their PCell. The SCell can be either local to the eNodeB, or on a remote eNodeB.
attribute.takesEffect: Changed value will take effect in relation to the next SCell configuration during the ongoing connection.

attribute.name: lbBnrAllowed
attribute.description: Specifies if the feature Best Neighbor Relations for Intra-LTE Load Management is allowed to automatically change the loadBalancing attribute for this EUtran cell relation.

attribute.name: incomingLoadBalancing
attribute.description:
Determines if feature Overlaid Cell Detection has qualified this cell relation as an overlaid neighbor, i.e. high-hitRate, on the corresponding frequency relation.
The value "true" means the neighbor cell is encouraged to initiate load balancing towards the source cell. The value "false" means no specific preferences exist.

attribute.name: lbCovIndicated
attribute.description: Determines if the cell relation has high hitRate towards the source cell. The attribute is automatically updated when the feature Overlaid Cell Detection is operable.

attribute.name: sleepModeCovCellCandidate
attribute.description:
Sleep Mode Coverage Cell candidate status.
Indicates if related cell can be used as coverage cell for Cell Sleep Mode.

attribute.name: sleepModeCapacityCell
attribute.description: Indicates if related cell is a dependent capacity cell for Cell Sleep Mode support.

attribute.name: sleepModeCoverageCell
attribute.description: Indicates if related cell is a coverage cell for Cell Sleep Mode support.

attribute.name: covCellDlPrbWakeUpThreshold
attribute.description: DL PRB usage percentage threshold. At least one of the coverage cells must exceed this threshold to wake-up the capacity cell.

attribute.name: covCellRrcConnWakeUpThreshold
attribute.description: Minimum number of RRC connections needed to wake-up the capacity cell. Sent by the capacity cell.

attribute.name: covCellWakeupMonitorDurTimer
attribute.description: Minimum duration for coverage cell to satisfy configured load thresholds before the capacity cell can wake-up. Used in feature Cell Sleep Mode.

attribute.name: crsAssistanceInfoPriority
attribute.description: Priority of neighbor cell whose CRS Assistance Information is sent to UE. For values between 1 and 100, the smaller the value, the higher the neighbor cell is prioritized for selection. Value 0 means the CRS Assistance Information of this neighbor cell is not sent. Note: This attribute is valid only for FDD cells.

attribute.name: mobilityStatus
attribute.description: Mobility status information for EUTRAN cell relation. When struct member mobilityStatus.available is set to false, no HO is performed on EUTRAN cell relation. Reason why HO is not allowed on EUTRAN cell relation is shown on mobilityStatus.reason.

attribute.name: hoSuccLevel
attribute.description: Handover statistics status information. Each value corresponds to the status of the handover statistics.

attribute.name: esCellCaConfigurationAvail
attribute.description: If indicated cell is currently able to serve as ESCell. - The ExternalEUtranCellFDD::remoteCellState (or ExternalEUtranCellTDD::remoteCellState) must be operState ENABLED. - Inter-eNodeB CA license must be active and baseband-to-baseband GTPU tunnel connection between ESCell and this eNodeB must be enabled. Or - Elastic RAN license must be active and baseband-to-baseband connections must be enabled. If not, no UEs are configured with this candidate. NOTE: UEs already configured with this cell can retain the configuration. If SCell is not external, this attribute is NOT_APPLICABLE.
attribute.dependencies: Depends on feature license and success of tunnels in TermPointToLbm (for the IeNB-CA feature only), TermPointToENB::interEnbSwCompatibilityState and on ExternalEUtranCellFDD::remoteCellState (or ExternalEUtranCellTDD::remoteCellState).

attribute.name: amoAllowed
attribute.description: Whether or not AMO function is allowed. Used to turn off AMO function on cell relation level.

attribute.name: amoState
attribute.description: Describes AMO function enabling state. RBS system sets the value.
attribute.dependencies: Depends on the operator configuration of AmoFunction::amoAllowedInterVendor, EUtranFreqRelation::amoAllowed, EUtranCellRelation::amoAllowed and the type of cell relation.

attribute.name: sCellPriority
attribute.description: Used for selecting an SCell within a frequency carrier. The SCell with highest priority is selected during initial blind SCell selection. 0 means lowest priority. -1 means the cell is excluded from blind SCell selection.
attribute.dependencies: Only applicable when CarrierAggregationFunction::dynamicSCellSelectionMethod == PRIORITIZED.

attribute.name: isShuttingdownSCellAllowed
attribute.description: Indicates whether a shutting down cell can be chosen as SCell or not.
attribute.statusInformation: Since 17.Q2. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.

attribute.name: ieNBUlCompCoopCellAllowed
attribute.description: Whether external cell is allowed to be used as cooperating cell candidates for inter-eNodeB UL CoMP.

attribute.name: externalUlCompGroupAvail
attribute.description: Whether external cell belongs to external UL Comp Group for each serving cell.
attribute.dependencies: Depends on feature license and success of UL CoMP tunnels in TermPointToLbm, which is decided by the values of TermPointToENB::interEnbUlCompSwCompatibility and ExternalEUtranCellFDD::remoteCellStateInterEnbUlComp (or ExternalEUtranCellTDD::remoteCellStateInterEnbUlComp) and EUtranCellRelation::ieNBUlCompCoopCellAllowed. Also depends on remote cell configuration, following conditions must be compatible with serving cell. - Same Frame Structure and Duplex mode - Same DL&UL EARFCN and UL Bandwidth for FDD - Same DL EARFCN, Bandwidth, Subframe Assignment for TDD

attribute.name: eranExternalUlCompGroupAvail
attribute.description: Whether external cell belongs to Elastic RAN external UL Comp Group for each serving cell.
attribute.dependencies: Depends on feature license and success of Elastic RAN UL CoMP tunnels in EranInterMeLink, which is decided by the values of TermPointToENB::eranUlCompSwCompatibility and ExternalEUtranCellFDD::remoteCellStateEranUlComp (or ExternalEUtranCellTDD::remoteCellStateIEranUlComp). Also depends on remote cell configuration, following conditions must be compatible with serving cell. - Same Frame Structure and Duplex mode - Same DL&UL EARFCN and UL Bandwidth for FDD - Same DL EARFCN, Bandwidth, Subframe Assignment for TDD

attribute.name: eranUlCompCoopCellAllowed
attribute.description: Whether external cell is allowed to be used as cooperating cell candidates for Elastic RAN UL CoMP.

attribute.name: isHoAllowedBr
attribute.description: Specifies if CAT-M Connected Mode Mobility between the cells in this relation is allowed.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute to false stops outgoing HO for CAT-M UE.

class.name: EUtranFreqRelation
class.description:
This MO represents a mobility relation between a EUtranCellFDD and a EUtranFrequency. It contains parameters that are specific for this relation. To include SIB3 in System Information, one instance of this MO must be created which refers to a EUtranFrequency MO with the parameter arfcnValueEUtranDl set to the same value as the parent EUtranCellFDD/EUtranCellTDDs parameter earfcndl.
It is only allowed to remove the EUtranFreqRelation, refering to the same frequency as the parent MO EUtranCellFDD/EUtranCellTDD has, when the EUtranCellFDD/EUtranCellTDD is locked.
Deleting this MO while the parent EUtranCellFDD/EUtranCellTDD has operationalState set to ENABLED is not recommended as it may affect traffic.

attribute.name: eUtranFreqRelationId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use.

attribute.name: eutranFrequencyRef
attribute.description: Refers to the EUTRAN frequency MO, EUtranFrequency.

attribute.name: qRxLevMin
attribute.description: The required minimum received Reference Symbol Received Power (RSRP) level in the (E-UTRA) frequency for cell reselection. Corresponds to parameter Qrxlevmin in 3GPP TS 36.304. This attribute is broadcast in SIB3 or SIB5, depending on whether the related frequency is intra- or inter-frequency.

attribute.name: pMax
attribute.description: Calculates the parameter Pcompensation (defined in 3GPP TS 36.304), at cell reselection to an E-UTRAN Cell. Corresponds to parameter PEMAX in 3GPP TS 36.101. Value 1000 means the parameter is not sent in the system information block.

attribute.name: tReselectionEutra
attribute.description: The cell reselection timer TreselectionRAT for E-UTRA. Value in seconds.

attribute.name: tReselectionEutraSfHigh
attribute.description: The attribute t-ReselectionEUTRA is multiplied with this factor if the UE is in high mobility state. Corresponds to the parameter Speed dependent ScalingFactor for TreselectionEUTRAN for medium high state in 3GPP TS 36.304. Value mapping: 25 = 0.25 50 = 0.5 75 = 0.75 100 = 1.0

attribute.name: tReselectionEutraSfMedium
attribute.description: The attribute t-ReselectionEUTRA is multiplied with this factor if the UE is in medium mobility state. Corresponds to the parameter Speed dependent ScalingFactor for TreselectionEUTRAN for medium mobility state in 3GPP TS 36.304. Value mapping: 25 = 0.25 50 = 0.5 75 = 0.75 100 = 1.0

attribute.name: cellReselectionPriority
attribute.description:
The absolute priority of the carrier frequency used by the cell reselection procedure. Corresponds to the parameter priority in 3GPP TS 36.304.
Value 0 means lowest priority. The UE behavior when no value is entered is specified in 3GPP TS 36.304.
attribute.dependencies: The value must be unique and not already used by other RAT, i.e. equal priorities between RATs are not supported.

attribute.name: threshXHigh
attribute.description: The threshold used by the UE when reselecting towards the higher priority frequency X from the current serving frequency. Each frequency of E-UTRAN can have a specific threshold. Refer to the parameter Thresx,high in 3GPP TS 36.304.

attribute.name: threshXLow
attribute.description: The threshold used in reselection towards frequency X priority from a higher priority frequency. Each frequency of E-UTRAN can have a specific threshold. Corresponds to parameter Thresx,low in 3GPP TS 36.304.

attribute.name: allowedMeasBandwidth
attribute.description: The maximum allowed measurement bandwidth on a carrier frequency. Note: The values indicate the number of resource blocks and correspond to the channel bandwidth 1,4MHz, 3MHz, 5MHz, 10MHz, 15MHz, 20MHz respectively specified in 3GPP TS 36.104.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: qOffsetFreq
attribute.description: Frequency specific offset for E-UTRAN frequencies used in connected mode. In idle mode, the negative value of this offset is used. Specification: 3GPP TS 36.331

attribute.name: presenceAntennaPort1
attribute.description: Indicates if all the neighboring cells use Antenna Port 1. When set to TRUE, the UE expects that at least two cell-specific antenna ports are used in all neighboring cells.

attribute.name: allowedPlmnList
attribute.description:
Lists all Public Land Mobile Network (PLMN) IDs allowed for this frequency relation.
A UE that does not support a PLMN included in allowedPlmnList does not measure on this frequency according to the UE Handover Restriction List.
No values in allowedPlmnList imply that the frequency has no restrictions for PLMN.
The PLMN identity consists of the following parts: 1. MobileCountryCode, MCC, 3 digits 2. MobileNetworkCode, MNC, 2 or 3 digits (the correct number of digits is set in the mncLength member of this Struct)
For example, if MCC=125 and MNC=46, then plmnId=12546.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: connectedModeMobilityPrio
attribute.description: Prioritizes EUTRAN frequencies among all frequencies related to the cell for UEs in connected mode. (0 means the lowest priority. -1 means the frequency is excluded.)

attribute.name: mobilityAction
attribute.description: The preferred way to transfer a UE in connected mode to this EUTRA frequency.

attribute.name: createdBy
attribute.description: Indicates whether the MO has been created by the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function or operator or X2

attribute.name: timeOfCreation
attribute.description: Indicates the time and date when the MO was created. Format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS

attribute.name: lastModification
attribute.description: Indicates whether the MO was last modified by the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function or operator or X2 and if the MO is to be deleted who triggered the deletion

attribute.name: timeOfLastModification
attribute.description: Indicates the time and date when the MO was last modified. Format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS

attribute.name: threshXHighQ
attribute.description:
Parameter "ThreshX, HighQ" in TS 36.304.
For the EUtranFreqRelation that points to the intra frequency EUtranFrequency MO, the attribute is invalid, that is, this attribute does not affect SIB3.
attribute.dependencies: The field is mandatory present if the Struct Member threshServingLowQ in SIB3 is used in systemInformationBlockType3.

attribute.name: threshXLowQ
attribute.description:
Parameter "ThreshX, LowQ" in TS 36.304.
For the EUtranFreqRelation that points to the intra frequency EUtranFrequency MO, the attribute is invalid, that is, this attribute does not affect SIB3.
attribute.dependencies: The field is mandatory present if the Struct Member threshServingLowQ in SIB3 is used in systemInformationBlockType3.

attribute.name: qQualMin
attribute.description:
Parameter "Qqualmin" in TS 36.304.
Value 0 means that it is not sent and UE applies in such case the (default) value of negative infinity for Qqualmin. Sent in SIB3 or SIB5.

attribute.name: neighCellConfig
attribute.description:
Provides to the UE information related to MBSFN and TDD UL/DL configuration of neighbor cells.
For TDD, the values DIFF_MBSFN_SUBFRAMES, SAME_MBSFN_SUBFRAMES and NO_MBSFN_SUBFRAMES indicates same UL/DL allocation in neighboring cells compared to the serving cell.
The value is included in SIB3, SIB5 and MeasObjectEUTRA.

attribute.name: voicePrio
attribute.description: Prioritizes EUTRAN frequencies among all frequencies related to the cell for UEs in connected mode. Sets the priority to which frequency to perform mobility to for a voice session. The value -1 means the frequency is excluded. The value 0 means the lowest priority. The value 7 means the highest priority.

attribute.name: blackListEntry
attribute.description: This parameter specifies a list of PCI that are blacklisted in EUTRAN measurements as described in 3GPP TS 36.331.

attribute.name: interFreqMeasType
attribute.description: The type of event based measurements on other LTE frequencies.

attribute.name: eutranFreqToQciProfileRelation
attribute.description: Encapsulates parameters for service specific load management for a certain QCI profile.

attribute.name: blackListEntryIdleMode
attribute.description: This parameter specifies blacklisted cells in SIB4 and SIB5.

attribute.name: lbBnrPolicy
attribute.description: Specifies the policy for updating the loadBalancing attribute by the feature Best Neighbor Relations for Intra-LTE Load Management. The policy is valid for all cell relations corresponding to this EUtranFreqRelation.

attribute.name: anrMeasOn
attribute.description: ANR performs measurement on the referenced frequency if this parameter is set to true. Otherwise, ANR does not perform any measurements on this frequency.

attribute.name: lbActivationThreshold
attribute.description: The minimum target cell load (subscription ratio) the source cell takes into account when determining the amount of load balancing action to a cell using this carrier frequency.

attribute.name: caTriggeredRedirectionActive
attribute.description: Parameter used to specify whether or not CA triggered redirection is activated from the current cell towards a certain frequency.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic

attribute.name: arpPrio
attribute.description: Prioritizes EUTRAN frequencies among all frequencies related to the cell. Sets the priority to which frequency to perform mobility for a bearer with specific ARP Priority Level when the feature Service or Priority-Triggered Inter-Frequency Handover is activated. The value -1 means the frequency is excluded. The value 0 means the lowest priority. The value 7 means the highest priority.

attribute.name: nonPlannedPhysCellId
attribute.description: Specific PCI reserved by operator for Femto Cell. It is the initial physical cell ID of Non-planned PCI. If value equals 1000, Non-planned PCI is not configured for this frequency relation.
attribute.dependencies: This attribute has a dependency to nonPlannedPhysCellIdRange.

attribute.name: nonPlannedPhysCellIdRange
attribute.description: PCI range for the Non-planned PCI.
attribute.dependencies: If nonPlannedPhysCellId != 1000, nonPlannedPhysCellId + nonPlannedPhysCellIdRange <= 504

attribute.name: nonPlannedPciCIO
attribute.description: Cell Individual Offset value for the Non-planned PCI, CSG or Hybrid CSG neighbor cell. Used when UE is in connected mode.

attribute.name: nonPlannedPciTargetIdType
attribute.description: Target eNodeB Identity type for the Non-planned PCI neighbor cell. Attribute is used to encode the message Handover Required when it is defined in TS36.413 ch. 9.1.5.1, S1AP parameter Global eNB ID.

attribute.name: candNeighborRel
attribute.description: The neighbor relations candidate list.

attribute.name: a5Thr1RsrpFreqOffset
attribute.description: The frequency-relation specific offset for the absolute threshold a5Threshold1Rsrp, RSRP threshold1 for event A5, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility.

attribute.name: a5Thr1RsrqFreqOffset
attribute.description: The frequency-relation specific offset for the absolute threshold a5Threshold1Rsrq, RSRQ threshold1 for event A5, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility.

attribute.name: a5Thr2RsrpFreqOffset
attribute.description: The frequency-relation specific offset for the absolute threshold a5Threshold2Rsrp, RSRP threshold2 for event A5, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility.

attribute.name: a5Thr2RsrqFreqOffset
attribute.description: The frequency-relation specific offset for the absolute threshold a5Threshold2Rsrq, RSRQ threshold2 for event A5, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility.

attribute.name: atoAllowed
attribute.description: Specifies whether Admission-triggered offload (ATO) is activated from the current cell towards a certain EUTRAN frequency.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: cellSleepCovCellMeasOn
attribute.description: Cell sleep mode performs measurement on the referenced frequency for coverage cell discovery if this parameter is set to true. Otherwise, cell sleep mode does not perform any measurements on this frequency.

attribute.name: interFreqMeasTypeUlSinr
attribute.description: The type of event based measurements used for inter-frequency LTE measurements when the measurements are uplink triggered.

attribute.name: csgPhysCellId
attribute.description: PCI for the closed access mode CSG cell. It is the start physical cell ID in the SIB4. If value is equal to 1000, it means that csg-PhysCellIdRange IE is not presented in SIB4.
attribute.dependencies: If csgPhysCellId != 1000, csgPhysCellId + csgPhysCellIdRange <= 504

attribute.name: csgPhysCellIdRange
attribute.description: The range of PCI for the closed access mode CSG cell. The information is broadcasted in SIB4.
attribute.dependencies: If csgPhysCellId != 1000, csgPhysCellId + csgPhysCellIdRange <= 504

attribute.name: hybridCsgPhysCellId
attribute.description: PCI for the Hybrid CSG cell. It is the start physical cell ID of Hybrid CSG cell. If value is equal to 1000, it means that Hybrid CSG cell is not supported for this frequency relation.
attribute.dependencies: If hybridCsgPhysCellId != 1000, hybridCsgPhysCellId + hybridCsgPhysCellIdRange <= 504

attribute.name: hybridCsgPhysCellIdRange
attribute.description: The range of PCI for the Hybrid CSG cell.
attribute.dependencies: If hybridCsgPhysCellId != 1000, hybridCsgPhysCellId + hybridCsgPhysCellIdRange <= 504

attribute.name: csgCellTargetIdType
attribute.description: Target eNodeB ID type for the CSG and Hybrid CSG neighbor cell. Attribute is used to encode the message Handover Required when it is defined in TS36.413 ch. 9.1.5.1, S1AP parameter Global eNB ID.

attribute.name: amoAllowed
attribute.description: Whether or not AMO function is allowed. Used to turn off AMO function on frequency relation level.

attribute.name: lbA5Thr1RsrpFreqOffset
attribute.description: The frequency-relation specific offset for the absolute threshold a5Threshold1Rsrp, RSRP threshold1 for event A5, used for Inter-frequency load balancing.

attribute.name: caFreqPriority
attribute.description: Prioritizes EUTRAN frequency carriers from which to pick SCells for carrier aggregation. 0 means lowest priority. -1 means the frequency is excluded from SCell selection.
attribute.dependencies: Only applicable when CarrierAggregationFunction::dynamicSCellSelectionMethod == PRIORITIZED. Can also be applied to dynamicSCellSelectionMethod == PRIORITIZED_AUTOMATIC as long as Configurable SCell Priority is licensed.

attribute.name: caFreqProportion
attribute.description: In conjunction with caPrioThreshold the value sets a threshold for the number of SCells on this frequency carrier that can be configured using prioritized SCell selection. A normalized value is applied. When frequency carriers have same priority, SCells are selected on the carrier with the lowest proportional SCell utilization.
attribute.dependencies: Only applicable when CarrierAggregationFunction::dynamicSCellSelectionMethod == PRIORITIZED.

attribute.name: tReselectionEutraCe
attribute.description: The cell reselection timer TreselectionEUTRA_CE for E-UTRA.

attribute.name: qRxLevMinCe
attribute.description: Min received RSRP level in E-UTRA frequency for cell reselection for UE in enhanced coverage mode. Corresponds to parameter Qrxlevmin_CE in 3GPP TS 36.304. This attribute is broadcast in SIB1-BR. This attribute is broadcast in SIB3 or SIB5. Depends on whether related frequency is intra- or inter-frequency.

attribute.name: qQualMinRsrqCe
attribute.description: Min quality level (RSRQ) in cell for UE in enhanced coverage mode. Corresponds to Qqualmin_CE in TS 36.304. Sent in SIB3 or SIB5. Depends on whether related frequency is intra- or inter-frequency. If 0, it is not sent and UE applies default value of negative infinity for Qqualmin_CE.

attribute.name: csmUeCapMonitorEnabled
attribute.description: Whether or not UE capability monitoring for the coverage frequency on capacity cell is enabled.

attribute.name: csmUeCapMonitorTime
attribute.description: Length of time that sleep criteria monitors UE capability for coverage frequency. Only valid if attribute csmUeCapMonitorEnabled is set to true. Value 0 means that sleep criteria checks connected UEs.

attribute.name: mdtMeasOn
attribute.description: If true, MDT measures referenced frequency. Otherwise, MDT does not perform any MDT measurements on this frequency. This attribute is only applicable for MDT reportingTrigger set to PERIODICAL.

attribute.name: a5OffsetPerPC
attribute.description: The frequency-relation specific offset for the absolute threshold, RSRP/RSRQ threshold1 and threshold2 for event A5, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility and high power UE.

class.name: EUtranFrequency
class.description: This Managed Object contains information of a specific EUtran frequency.

attribute.name: eUtranFrequencyId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: reservedBy
attribute.description: Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use.

attribute.name: arfcnValueEUtranDl
attribute.description: Indicates the ARFCN applicable for a downlink E-UTRA carrier frequency, as defined in 3GPP TS 36.104 for specified E-UTRA bands. For TDD this also indicates the ARFCN for uplink. The values that can be used depends on national operator specific frequency allocation as well as from the supported frequency band(s) of the equipment in the eNodeB.

attribute.name: additionalFreqBandList
attribute.description: A list of additional frequency bands the frequency belongs to. The list is automatically set by the eNB. The list does not include the frequency band indicated by the EARFCN value of the frequency (primary frequency band). These additional frequency bands are broadcasted to the UEs in SystemInformationBlockType5 in case the feature Multiple Frequency Band Indicators is enabled in the cell.

attribute.name: excludeAdditionalFreqBandList
attribute.description: A list of frequency bands to be excluded from the list of additional frequency bands in the additionalFreqBandList MOM attribute. The list shall not include the frequency band indicated by the EARFCN value of the frequency (primary frequency band). These frequency bands are excluded from the list of broadcasted additional frequency bands in SystemInformationBlockType5 in case the feature Multiple Frequency Band Indicators is enabled in the cell.

attribute.name: freqBand
attribute.description: The primary frequency band the frequency belongs to according to its defined EARFCN.

class.name: Cdma2000CellRelation
class.description: This Managed Object represents a mobility relation between a EUtranCellFDD or an EUtranCellTDD and an Cdma2000Cell. It contains parameters that are specific for this relation.

attribute.name: cdma2000CellRelationId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use.

attribute.name: externalCdma2000CellRef
attribute.description: Reference to a ExternalCdma2000Cell.

attribute.name: includeInSystemInformation
attribute.description:
Indicates if the CDMA2000 cell shall be included in System Information or not.
When the includeInSystemInformation is set to false, the CDMA2000 cell is not included in SIB8. A maximum of 16 CDMA2000 cells can be included per frequency. A maximum of 32 CDMA2000 cells can be included in SIB8.

attribute.name: includeInSystemInformationRel9
attribute.description:
Indicates if the CDMA2000 cell shall be included in the Release 9 part of System Information or not.
When the includeInSystemInformationRel9 is set to false, the CDMA2000 cell is not included in the Release 9 part of SIB8. A maximum of 16 CDMA2000 cells can be included per frequency in the Release 9 part. A total maximum of 32 CDMA2000 cells can be included in SIB8.
attribute.dependencies: In 3GPP rel9, the possiblity to add 16 additional CDMA2000 cells on the same frequency, was added. The additional CDMA2000 cells are controled by the parameter includeInSystemInformationRel9.

class.name: Cdma2000Freq
class.description: This Managed Object contains information of a specific CDMA2000 frequency within a Bandclass.

attribute.name: freqCdma
attribute.description: Identifies the carrier frequency within a CDMA2000 Band.

attribute.name: cdma2000FreqId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: reservedBy
attribute.description: Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use.

class.name: Cdma2000FreqBand
class.description: This Managed Object holds information on a CDMA2000 Bandclass.

attribute.name: cdma2000FreqBandId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use.

attribute.name: reservedBy
attribute.description: Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.
attribute.dependencies: The MO may not be deleted if it is reserved.

attribute.name: cdmaBandClass
attribute.description:
The CDMA frequency band in which the HRPD or 1xRTT carrier is located
The UNDEFINED_VALUE can never be used - either at create or modify of an MO.

class.name: Cdma2000FreqBandRelation
class.description:
This Managed Object represents a mobility relation between an EUtranCellFDD or an EUtranCellTDD and a Cdma2000FreqBand. It contains parameters that are specific for this relation.
Deleting this MO while the parent EUtranCellFDD/EUtranCellTDD has operationalState set to ENABLED is not recommended as it may affect traffic.

attribute.name: cdma2000FreqBandRelationId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use.

attribute.name: cdma2000FreqBandRef
attribute.description: Reference to the Cdma2000 frequency band MO, Cdma2000FreqBand.

attribute.name: threshXHighHrpd
attribute.description:
The threshold used in reselection towards a high priority CDMA2000 HRPD band class, expressed as an unsigned binary number equal to FLOOR ([-2 x 10 x log10 Ec/Io]) in units of 0.5 db.
If sNonServingCell > threshXHighHrpd, reselection is considered towards the band class with higher priority. The condition must be valid during the period defined by attribute tReselectionCdmaHrpd.
sNonServingCell is the RX-level value of a neighboring cell.

attribute.name: threshXLowHrpd
attribute.description:
The threshold used in reselection towards a low priority CDMA2000 HRPD band class expressed as an unsigned binary number equal to FLOOR ([-2 x 10 x log10 Ec/Io]) in units of 0.5 db.
If sServingCell < threshServingLow and sNeighbor > threshXLow (see corresponding attribute), reselection towards this lower prioritized band class is considered. The condition must be valid during the period defined by attribute tReselectionCdmaHrpd.
sServingCell is the RX level value of the serving cell and sNeighborCell is the RX level value of a neighbor frequency.

attribute.name: cellReselectionPriority
attribute.description: Absolute priority of the RAT (0 means: lowest priority).
attribute.dependencies: The value must be unique and not already used by other RAT, i.e. equal priorities between RATs are not supported.

class.name: Cdma2000Network
class.description: This Managed Object is a container for CDMA2000 related Managed Objects.

attribute.name: cdma2000NetworkId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use.

class.name: EUtranCellTDD
class.description: This MO represents a TDD cell and contains parameters needed by the cell. It also contains parameters for the mandatory common channels. The cell need to have the same duplex mode (FDD or TDD) as the already existing intra-RBS cells, if any.

action.name: changeFrequency
action.description:
Changes the frequency of the cell. The attribute earfcn is changed. This MO action includes the following steps:
- An instance of EUtranFrequency with correct frequency is created (if not already existing).
- For neigbouring cells with existing cell relations to the cell, create new EUtranFreqRelation instances (if not already existing) and new EUtranCellRelation instances (with the same attribute values as the existing EUtranFreqRelation and EUtranCellRelation MOs).
- For the changed cell an instance of EUtranFreqRelation with reference to the correct instance of EUtranFrequency is created, if not already existing (with the same attribute values as the existing EUtranFreqRelation MO).
Note that changing frequency of a EUtranCellTDD will imply that all other eNBs that have this cell configured as an ExternaEUtranCellTDD will be updated with the new frequency. This means that new EUtranFreqRelation and corresponding EUtranFrequency MOs might be created.

parameter.name: earfcn
parameter.description: The new frequency for this cell.

action.disturbances: Executing this action can cause loss of traffic. The cell is locked and unlocked automatically if needed. LAA cell (attribute isLaa = true) must be locked and unlocked manually for the change of frequency to take effect.

action.name: setCbrsTxExpireTime
action.description: Action requests node to set transmission expire time on externally supervised cell. Action sets date and time to attribute cbrsTxExpireTime on cell. If transmitExpireTime is -1, "" is set (empty). Spectrum access system controls transmission. Do not execute manually.

parameter.name: transmitExpireTime
parameter.description: A time period granted for transmission on the assigned spectrum.

action.disturbances: Executing this action can cause loss of traffic. Cell can be disabled automatically after transmitExpireTime, or immediately if transmitExpireTime is set to -1.

action.name: stopAilg
action.description: Stops execution of the optional feature Air Interface Load Generator.

action.name: startAilg
action.description: Starts execution of the optional feature Air Interface Load Generator.
action.disturbances: Executing this action can cause loss of traffic if high priority load is configured.

attribute.name: subframeAssignment
attribute.description: The assignment of uplink and downlink subframes for the TDD frame structure (called UL/DL configuration in 3GPP TS 36.211). All TDD cells in the same DU or Baseband, or same frequency band, or specific frequency band combinations where one frequency band overlaps with another (e.g. Band 38 and Band 41) must have the same uplink and downlink subframe assignment.
attribute.dependencies: For cellRange greater than 15 subframeAssignment must be set to 1.
attribute.disturbances: Changes may affect traffic.

attribute.name: specialSubframePattern
attribute.description: The special subframe pattern configuration for Downlink Part of Time Slot (DwPTS), Guard Period (GP), and Uplink Part of Time Slot (UpPTS). All TDD cells in the same frequency band, or specific frequency band combinations where one frequency band overlaps with another (e.g. Band 38 and Band 41) must have the same special subframe pattern configuration.
attribute.dependencies: specialSubframePattern = 5 can not be used in combination with nB=T4 on MO Paging, see 3GPP TS 36.213. The round trip time at the cellRange together with switching time must be less than the time available in special subframe.
attribute.disturbances: Changes may affect traffic.

attribute.name: channelBandwidth
attribute.description: The channel bandwidth in the cell.
attribute.disturbances: Changes may affect traffic.

attribute.name: earfcn
attribute.description:
The E-UTRA Absolute Radio Frequency Channel Number (EARFCN) for the TDD cell. The mapping from EARFCN to physical frequency is for E-UTRA bands is described in 3GPP TS 36.104. The values depend on national, operator specific frequency allocation, as well as from the supported frequency band(s) of the equipment in the RBS.
Use MO action changeFrequency for changing the frequency after that cell is initially setup. See description of changeFrequency, on how change takes effect and disturbances.
attribute.disturbances: Changes may affect traffic.

attribute.name: eUtranCellTDDId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: frameStartOffset
attribute.description: The frame start offset of the cell. All TDD cells in the same frequency band, or specific frequency band combinations where one frequency band overlaps with another (e.g. Band 38 and Band 41) must have the same frame start offset.
attribute.disturbances: Changes may affect traffic.

attribute.name: noOfPucchCqiUsers
attribute.description: The number of Channel Quality Indicator (CQI) resources available on the PUCCH channel. For TDD Subframe Assignment 1 the recommended value is 64.
attribute.disturbances: Cell runs new set-up procedure. All cell-connected UEs are released and connected again.

attribute.name: noOfPucchSrUsers
attribute.description: The number of Scheduling Request (SR) resources available on the PUCCH channel. For TDD Subframe Assignment 1 the recommended value is 64.
attribute.disturbances: Cell runs new set-up procedure. All cell-connected UEs are released and connected again.

attribute.name: cellRange
attribute.description: The maximum distance from the base station where a connection to a UE can be setup and maintained.
attribute.dependencies: For cellRange greater than 15 subframeAssignment must be set to 1. The round trip time at the cellRange together with switching time must be less than the time available in special subframe.
attribute.disturbances: Changes may affect traffic.

attribute.name: transmissionMode
attribute.description: Defines the Transmission Mode (e.g. Transmit Diversity and Closed-Loop Spatial Multiplexing) that shall be used for the UEs that are connected to the cell. See 3GPP TS 36.213 table 7.1-5 for a definition of Transmission Mode.

attribute.name: zzzTemporary1
attribute.description: Temporary attributes are intended for temporary solutions, and their usage may vary depending on the installed software. It is strongly recommended to only set the attributes that correspond to a desired functionality and leave all other temporary attributes set to default value. Information in the descriptions about what attributes are in use may be overridden by the information in CPI Info documents. Note that a later release may use another attribute to control the functionality previously provided by a temporary attribute, or may remove the functionality altogether. In these cases, the change is documented in the NIR.
attribute.statusInformation: Since L17A. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.

attribute.description: Temporary attributes are intended for temporary solutions, and their usage may vary depending on the installed software.
