attribute.name: lbabBarringPriorityLevel
attribute.description: Current barring priority level based on PAB algorithm.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect when feature Progressive Access Barring is activated.

attribute.name: lbabMinBarringFactor
attribute.description: Minimum barring factor for LBAB algorithm, or PAB algorithm, priority level 0.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect when feature Load-Based Access Barring or feature Progressive Access Barring is activated.

attribute.name: lbabMinBarringFactorPrio1
attribute.description: Minimum barring factor for PAB algorithm, priority level 1.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect when feature Progressive Access Barring is activated.

attribute.name: lbabMinBarringFactorPrio2
attribute.description: Minimum barring factor for PAB algorithm, priority level 2.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect when feature Progressive Access Barring is activated.

attribute.name: physicalLayerCellId
attribute.description: Physical-layer cell ID.
attribute.dependencies: Equal to 3 x physicalLayerCellIdGroup + physicalLayerSubCellId.

attribute.name: prioHpueCapability
attribute.description: Priority of high power UE capability.

attribute.name: noOfEnhAdptReTxCand
attribute.description: Threshold used in restrict SE number that enhanced adaptive Retransmission candidates, if there are too many non-adaptive retransmission candidates, only "noOfEnhAdptReTxCand" numbers SE can be the enhanced adaptive retransmission queue. Maximum number of SEs added to the enhanced adaptive retransmission queue as candidates. If set to -1, number of candidates is automatically decided by eNodeB. If set to 0, no UEs added to queue and thus feature has no effect.

attribute.name: mappingInfoCe
attribute.description: SI message to which each SIB is mapped. Note: SIB2 is always mapped to SI message 1 according to 3GPP TS 36.331.

attribute.name: prescheduling
attribute.description: Whether or not prescheduling is enabled.

attribute.name: eranUlCompUserSelSinrThr
attribute.description: SINR threshold for Elastic RAN UL CoMP user selection.
attribute.dependencies: Must be used together with eranUlCompUserSelSinrHys.

attribute.name: eranUlCompUserSelSinrHys
attribute.description: Hysteresis of SINR threshold for Elastic RAN UL CoMP user selection.
attribute.dependencies: Must be used together with eranUlCompUserSelSinrThr.

attribute.name: cellResourceRef
attribute.description: References to an instance of CellResource MO.
attribute.statusInformation: Since 18.Q2. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.
attribute.dependencies: CellResource MO having non empty plmnList and CellResource MO having non empty spidList shouldn't be referred together(CellResource MO having empty plmnList and empty spidList is considered as configuring spidList(non empty spidList)). Duplication of PLMN or SPID within referred CellResouce MOs is not allowed.

attribute.name: liteMcsReduction
attribute.description: LiteMcsReduction feature mode.

attribute.name: zzzTemporary67
attribute.description: Temporary attribute intended for temporary solution. Usage depends on the installed software. Only set this attribute when it corresponds to a desired functionality and leave all other temporary attributes set to default values. Information in the descriptions about the used attributes can be overridden by information in CPI documents. Note that a later release can use another attribute or completely remove the functionality. Changes are documented in the NIR.

attribute.name: measCellGroupCellRef
attribute.description: References to an instance of MeasCellGroup MO for grouping on a cell basis.
attribute.dependencies: MeasCellGroup having "0" groupId should not be referred.

attribute.name: iuaEnabled
attribute.description: Enables Instant Uplink Access (IUA) for a cell.

attribute.name: iuaInterval
attribute.description: Time interval between UL short-SPS (semi-persistent scheduling) instances. Value 0 means load based selection of IUA interval.
attribute.dependencies: In MO EUtranCellFDD, only values 0,1,2,4 are allowed. In MO EUtranCellTDD, only values 0,1,5 are allowed.

attribute.name: iuaMaxResourcePerCell
attribute.description: Maximum percentage of UL PRBs and SEs that are used by IUA at cell level. The actual number of resources per cell depends on iuaMaxResourcePerBbm.

attribute.name: iuaMaxPrbsPerUe
attribute.description: Maximum UL PRBs that are used by an IUA UE. The actual number of PRBs per UE depends on iuaMaxResourcePerCell.

attribute.name: ns05FullBandSchedEnabled
attribute.description: Enables PUSCH 100 PRBs scheduling.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect if: - license for NS 05 Additional Maximum Power Reduction Support is present and the feature is active, and - attribute networkSignallingValue in MOC EUtranCellFDD/TDD is NS_05.

attribute.name: ns05FullBandUsersInCellThres
attribute.description: Value of threshold to enable the PUSCH 100 PRBs scheduling. PUSCH 100 PRBs scheduling is triggered when the number of UE in RRC_CONNECTED mode in the cell is less than or equal to ns05FullBandUsersInCellThres.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect if: - license for NS 05 Additional Maximum Power Reduction Support is present and the feature is active, and - attribute networkSignallingValue in MOC EUtranCellFDD/TDD is NS_05, and - attribute ns05FullBandSchedEnabled in MOC EUtranCellFDD/TDD is true.

attribute.name: ns05LowBandSchedMode
attribute.description: Controls if the low band can be allocated to NS_05 UEs. When ns05LowBandSchedMode is configured to 'ALWAYS_PROHIBIT', the low band cannot be allocated to the NS_05 UEs. When ns05LowBandSchedMode is configured to 'ALWAYS_AVAILABLE', the low band can always be allocated to the NS_05 UEs. When ns05LowBandSchedMode is configured to 'ADAPTIVE_AVAILABLE_BY_REPEATER_DETECTION', the low band can only be allocated to the NS_05 UEs which are detected as not in repeater zone.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect if: - license for NS 05 Additional Maximum Power Reduction Support is present and the feature is active, and - attribute networkSignallingValue in MOC EUtranCellFDD/TDD is NS_05.

attribute.name: ns05PathlossOffsetThres
attribute.description: Value of threshold to detect if the NS_05 UE is in repeater zone. If the NS_05 UE's pathloss measured on low band is bigger than or equal to the value of other band plus ns05PathlossOffsetThres, the NS_05 UE is detected as in repeater zone.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect if: - license for NS 05 Additional Maximum Power Reduction Support is present and the feature is active, and - attribute networkSignallingValue in MOC EUtranCellFDD/TDD is NS_05, and - attribute ns05LowBandSchedMode is ADAPTIVE_AVAILABLE_BY_REPEATER_DETECTION.

attribute.name: srvccDelayTimer
attribute.description: The length of time the eNodeB delays Single Radio Voice Call Continuity (SRVCC) handover. Value 0 means no delay.

attribute.name: voiceMeasAccEnabled
attribute.description: Enables voice IRAT measurement acceleration in the cell.
attribute.dependencies: Only relevant if mobCtrlAtPoorCovActive is set to true.

attribute.name: hpueCaSwitchThres
attribute.description: SINR threshold for triggering a switch to high power UE.

attribute.name: hpueCaSwitchHyst
attribute.description: Hysteresis of SINR threshold for triggering a switch to high power UE.

attribute.name: hpueCaSwitchTimeToTrigger
attribute.description: Time-to-trigger value for UL measurement in switching between High Power UE to Carrier Aggregation.

attribute.name: additionalMultipleNSPmax
attribute.description: The attribute in broadcast in SIB1 as multiBandInfoList-v10j0. A list of additionalPmax and additionalSpectrumEmission values. If E-UTRAN includes multiBandInfoList-v10j0, it includes the same number of entries, and listed in the same order, as in multiBandInfoList.

attribute.name: multipleNSPmaxReqMapping
attribute.description: A list which maps frequency bands to additional Pmax value, and additional spectrum emissions as described by 3GPP TS 36.101, table 6.2.4-1. This list is used to generate the value of additionalMultipleNSPmax.
attribute.disturbances: Changing the pMax value for additional band can cause loss of traffic. additionalPMax in MultipleNSPmaxReqMapping structure indicates the pMax value.

attribute.name: dlPowerRampUpInitialRatio
attribute.description: Initial ratio for downlink output power to start power ramp up. Value 100 indicates full cell coverage.

attribute.name: dlPowerRampUpRate
attribute.description: Power ramp up rate per second for downlink output power to reach full cell coverage.

attribute.name: puschNcpChannelEstWindowSize
attribute.description: Normal or Large Window Size for PUSCH filter channel estimation for normal CP.

attribute.name: useBandPrioritiesInSib1
attribute.description:
If enabled, prioritized additional frequency band list is broadcast in SIB1 according to priorities set in EUtranCellFDD::prioAdditionalFreqBandList or in EUtranCellTDD::prioAdditionalFreqBandList. The priorities must be valid.
If disabled, EUtranCellFDD::additionalFreqBandList or EUtranCellTDD::additionalFreqBandList is used.
attribute.precondition: eNodeB must support Multiple Frequency Band Indicators feature.

class.name: ExternalEUtranCellTDD
class.description: This managed object represents a neighbor EUTRAN cell (TDD) in another ENodeB in any MME pool.

parameter.name: earfcn
parameter.description: Changes the frequency of the external cell. This means it should change the value of the attribute eutranFrequencyRef to refer to the correct EUtranFrequency MO (creating it if necessary). It also includes moving the EUtranCellRelation MO:s to the corresponding EUtranFrequencyRelation MO.

attribute.name: channelBandwidth
attribute.description: The downlink channel bandwidth in a cell that is served by a neighboring RBS. In TDD mode, the uplink bandwidth is equal to the downlink bandwidth. The attribute is set by the RBS at X2 SETUP procedure. The value 0 means there is no valid value available.

attribute.name: eutranFrequencyRef
attribute.description: Refers to the EUTRAN frequency MO, EUtranFrequency. Cannot be changed as long as this MO is referred to by a EUtranCellRelation MO.

attribute.name: externalEUtranCellTDDId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: localCellId
attribute.description: RBS internal ID attribute for the ExternalEUtranCellTDD. Must be unique in the RBS. Together with the Node ID and PLMN ID this is a globally unique eUTRAN Cell ID (ECGI).

attribute.name: physicalLayerCellIdGroup
attribute.description: The physical-layer cell identity group. Physical-layer cell IDs are grouped into 168 unique groups, each group containing 3 unique subidentities.

attribute.name: physicalLayerSubCellId
attribute.description: The physical-layer cell identity group. Physical-layer cell IDs are grouped into 168 unique groups, each group containing 3 unique subidentities.

attribute.name: reservedBy
attribute.description: Lists the EUtranCellRelation managed object instances that reserve this managed object instance.
attribute.dependencies: The managed object cannot be deleted if it is reserved.

attribute.name: tac
attribute.description: Identifies a Tracking Area Code (TAC) of an external cell.

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use.

attribute.name: isRemoveAllowed
attribute.description: Indicates if the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function is allowed to remove this object. It does not restrict operator removal of the object. Objects created by ANR have this parameter set to true initially.

attribute.name: masterEUtranCellTDDId
attribute.description: The ID of the EUtranCellTDD that this MO represents for automatically created ExternalEUtranCellTDD managed objects.

attribute.name: activePlmnList
attribute.description: Lists the PLMN IDs in the external E-UTRAN cell. The list may include up to 6 PLMN IDs. The list tracks the activePlmnList in the corresponding instance of EUtranCellFDD/TDD in another RBS. It is configured by ANR when ANR feature creates the MO and then set to the PLMN Id from the CGI report. The list is updated via X2 or OSS-RC, or manually.

attribute.name: createdBy
attribute.description: Indicates whether the MO has been created by the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function or operator or X2

attribute.name: timeOfCreation
attribute.description: Indicates the time and date when the MO was created. Format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS

attribute.name: lastModification
attribute.description: Indicates whether the MO was last modified by the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function or operator or X2 and if the MO is to be deleted who triggered the deletion

attribute.name: timeOfLastModification
attribute.description: Indicates the time and date when the MO was last modified. Format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS

It is strongly recommended to only set the attributes that correspond to a desired functionality and leave all other temporary attributes set to default value. Information in the descriptions about what attributes are in use may be overridden by the information in CPI Info documents. Note that a later release may use another attribute to control the functionality previously provided by a temporary attribute, or may remove the functionality altogether. In these cases, the change is documented in the NIR.

attribute.name: pciConflict
attribute.description: A PCI confusion exists if a source cell has relations to two neighbor cells where both neighbor cells have the same PCI and frequency. A PCI collision exists if a source cell has a relation to a neighbor cell where both the source cell and neighbor cell have the same PCI and frequency.

attribute.name: pciConflictCell
attribute.description: Indicates the CGI of the other cell that is involved in the PCI collision/confusion. This value is only valid if the attribute pciConflict is "YES" or "YES_CONFLICTING_CELL".

attribute.name: csgPhysCellId
attribute.description: Physical Cell Identity for the CSG (Closed Subscriber Group). It is the start physical cell ID in the SIB4. If value is equal to 1000, it means that csg-PhysCellIdRange IE is not presented in SIB4.
attribute.statusInformation: Since L16B. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.
attribute.dependencies: This attribute has a dependency to csgPhysCellIdRange.

attribute.name: csgPhysCellIdRange
attribute.description: It is the range of Physical Cell Identity for the CSG (Closed Subscriber Group). The information is broadcasted in SIB4.
attribute.statusInformation: Since L16B. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.
attribute.dependencies: If csgPhyscellId != 1000, csgPhysCellId + csgPhysCellIdRange <= 504

attribute.name: pciDetectingCell
attribute.description: Indicates the CGI of the cell that detected the PCI collision/confusion. This value is only valid if the corresponding attribute pciConflict is "YES" or "YES_CONFLICTING_CELL". The first cell in the pciDetectingCell list corresponds to the first cell in the pciConflictCell list and the first value of pciConflict. The second cell in the pciDetectingCell list corresponds to the second cell in the pciConflictCell list and the first value of pciConflict.

attribute.name: activeServiceAreaId
attribute.description: The active MBMS Service Area Identity of an external cell.

attribute.name: lbEUtranCellOffloadCapacity
attribute.description: This attribute indicates the offload subscription capacity associated with the EUTRAN target cell. The value is used to moderate the offload rate to the EUTRAN target cell.

attribute.name: additionalFreqBandList
attribute.description: A list of additional frequency bands the cell belongs to, not including the frequency band indicated by the EARFCN value of the cell (primary frequency band). The list is automatically set by the eNB.

attribute.name: freqBand
attribute.description: The primary frequency band the cell belongs to according to its defined EARFCN. This frequency band indicator is broadcasted to the UEs in SystemInformationBlockType1.

attribute.name: subframeAssignment
attribute.description: The assignment of uplink and downlink subframes for the TDD frame structure (called UL/DL configuration in 3GPP TS 36.211). The parameter is set by the RBS at X2 SETUP procedure. Undefined value: -1

attribute.name: remoteCellState
attribute.description: Reflects whether the indicated cell is currently able to serve as an SCell. The remote cell must be operState ENABLED and adminState UNLOCKED.
attribute.dependencies: Depends on X2 connection being operational and software compatibility.

attribute.name: sCellCaConfigurationAvailabilty
attribute.description: Reflects whether the indicated cell is currently able to serve as an SCell. The remoteCellState must be operState ENABLED and Inter-eNodeB license must be active. As well, at least one tunnel connecting the indicated ESCell to this eNodeB must be enabled. If not, no UEs are configured with this candidate, though UEs already configured with this cell will possibly retain the configuration.
attribute.statusInformation: Since L16B. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.
attribute.dependencies: Depends on feature license and success of tunnels in TermPointToLbm, interEnbSwCompatibilityState and on remoteCellState.

attribute.name: remoteCellStateInterEnbUlComp
attribute.description: Whether indicated cell can serve as external cell for inter-eNodeB UL CoMP.
attribute.dependencies: X2 connection must be operational and software compatible. Remote cell must be operState ENABLED and adminState UNLOCKED.

attribute.name: commonSFAllocList
attribute.description: Shows the subframes that are reserved for MBSFN in DL.

attribute.name: physicalLayerCellId
attribute.description: Physical-layer cell ID.
attribute.dependencies: Equal to 3 x physicalLayerCellIdGroup + physicalLayerSubCellId.

attribute.name: specialSubframePattern
attribute.description: The special subframe pattern configuration for Downlink Part of Time Slot (DwPTS), Guard Period (GP), and Uplink Part of Time Slot (UpPTS) (used to control special subframe in 3GPP TS 36.211). The parameter is set by the RBS at X2 SETUP procedure. Undefined value: -1

attribute.name: remoteCellStateEranUlComp
attribute.description: Whether indicated cell can serve as external cell for Elastic RAN UL CoMP.
attribute.dependencies: X2 connection must be operational and software compatible. Remote cell must be operState ENABLED and adminState UNLOCKED.

class.name: AirIfLoadProfile
class.description: Contains parameters and constraints for Air Interface Load Generator needed to start the function in a Cell.

attribute.name: reservedBy
attribute.description: Contains a list of managed object instances that reserves this managed object instance.
attribute.dependencies: The MO may not be deleted if it is reserved.

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use

attribute.name: airIfLoadProfileId
attribute.description: The value component of the (Relative Distinguished Name) RDN

attribute.name: dlPrbLoadLevel
attribute.description:
Minimal load level associated with downlink Physical Resource Block (PRB) use.
If the sum of higher priority artificial load defined according to ailgHighPrio and real UE is below this level, lower priority artificial load is generated to reach the minimal load level.
0 means that no minimal load level is defined

attribute.name: ailgLowPrioModType
attribute.description: Supported modulation type for lower priority artificial load.

attribute.name: noOfOcngPrbSeries
attribute.description: The number of series (where each series is defined in ocngPrbSerie) to be allocated for the OFDMA Channel Noise Generator (OCNG) pattern, as defined in 3GPP TS 36.133.
attribute.dependencies: Valid if ailgHighPrio = OCNG

attribute.name: ocngPrbSerie
attribute.description: Contains the attributes required to configure the OFDMA Channel Noise Generator (OCNG) Frequency Division Duplex (FDD) pattern to use for filling the Physical Resource Blocks (PRBs), according to 3GPP TS 36.133.
attribute.dependencies: Valid if ailgHighPrio = OCNG

attribute.name: trafficModelPrb
attribute.description: Contains the attributes required to configure a traffic model pattern to use for filling the Physical Resource Blocks (PRBs).
attribute.dependencies: Valid if ailgHighPrio = TRAFFIC_MODEL

attribute.name: ailgHighPrio
attribute.description: The method used to generate high priority artificial load.

attribute.name: ailgChangePeriod
attribute.description: The pattern for generated artificial load changes periodically after each ailgChangePeriod. The period applies to both PDSCH and PDCCH artificial load. Within each period the same load pattern in terms of positions of PDSCH PRBs and/or PDCCH CCEs within the available bandwidth is used.

attribute.name: minLoadLevelPdcch
attribute.description:
Minimum load level for PDCCH in terms of utilization of the available Control Channel Elements (CCE). If the PDCCH load from real UE is below this level, lower priority artificial load is generated to reach this minimum load level.
The value "0" means that no minimum load level is defined.

attribute.name: ailgLoadType
attribute.description: Decides the type of load to be generated by means of different combinations of PDSCH load, Beam Forming (BF) and PDCCH load.

class.name: ReportConfigA1Prim
class.description: This managed object contains report configuration settings for the primary A1 event measurements. The A1 event is used to detect the Bad Coverage Cease condition. Primary and secondary reporting configuration MOs refer to the option to use different settings for two simultaneous measurements for the event A1.

attribute.name: reportConfigA1PrimId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: a1ThresholdRsrpPrim
attribute.description: The Reference Signal Received Power (RSRP) threshold value for the primary eventA1.
attribute.dependencies: Only used if triggerQuantityA2Prim is set to RSRP.

attribute.name: a1ThresholdRsrqPrim
attribute.description: The Reference Signal Received Quality (RSRQ) threshold value for the primary eventA1.
attribute.dependencies: Only used if triggerQuantityA2Prim is set to RSRQ.

attribute.name: hysteresisA1Prim
attribute.description: The hysteresis value for the primary eventA1 measurement.

attribute.name: timeToTriggerA1Prim
attribute.description: The time-to-trigger value for the primary eventA1 measurement.

class.name: ReportConfigA1Sec
class.description: This managed object contains report configuration settings for the secondary A1 event measurements. The A1 event is used to the detect traffic-related Bad Coverage Cease condition. Primary and secondary reporting configuration MOs refer to the option to use different settings for two simultaneous measurements for the event A1.

attribute.name: reportConfigA1SecId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: a1ThresholdRsrpSec
attribute.description: The Reference Signal Received Power (RSRP) threshold value for the secondary eventA1.
attribute.dependencies: Only used if triggerQuantityA2Sec is set to RSRP.

attribute.name: a1ThresholdRsrqSec
attribute.description: The Reference Signal Received Quality (RSRQ) threshold value for the secondary eventA1.
attribute.dependencies: Only used if triggerQuantityA2Sec is set to RSRQ.

attribute.name: hysteresisA1Sec
attribute.description: The hysteresis value for the secondary eventA1 measurement.

attribute.name: timeToTriggerA1Sec
attribute.description: The time-to-trigger value for the secondary eventA1 measurement.

class.name: ReportConfigA5
class.description: This managed object contains report configuration settings for the A5 event measurements. The A5 event is used to detect when serving cell becomes worse than threshold1, and neighbor cell becomes better than threshold2. The actual threshold values used can be adjusted by frequency relation related offsets if the feature Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility (MLSTM) is enabled.

attribute.name: reportConfigA5Id
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: a5Threshold1Rsrp
attribute.description: The Reference Signal Received Power (RSRP) threshold1 value for eventA5.
attribute.dependencies: Only used if triggerQuantityA5 is set to RSRP.

attribute.name: a5Threshold2Rsrp
attribute.description: The Reference Signal Received Power (RSRP) threshold2 value for eventA5.
attribute.dependencies: Only used if triggerQuantityA5 is set to RSRP.

attribute.name: a5Threshold1Rsrq
attribute.description: The Reference Signal Received Quality (RSRQ) threshold1 value for eventA5.
attribute.dependencies: Only used if triggerQuantityA5 is set to RSRQ.

attribute.name: a5Threshold2Rsrq
attribute.description: The Reference Signal Received Quality (RSRQ) threshold2 value for eventA5.
attribute.dependencies: Only used if triggerQuantityA5 is set to RSRQ.

attribute.name: hysteresisA5
attribute.description: The hysteresis value for the eventA5 measurement.

attribute.name: timeToTriggerA5
attribute.description: Time-to-trigger value for event A5. If timeToTriggerA5Rsrq is -1, this attribute is used for both RSRP and RSRQ. But if not set to -1, this attribute is used only for RSRP.

attribute.name: triggerQuantityA5
attribute.description: The quantity that triggers the eventA5 for the eventA5 measurement.

attribute.name: hysteresisA5RsrqOffset
attribute.description: Offset to obtain the Hysteresis for A5 measurement for trigger quantity RSRQ. hysteresisA5Rsrq = hysteresisA5 + hysteresisA5RsrqOffset
attribute.dependencies: Feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage must be active.

attribute.name: timeToTriggerA5Rsrq
attribute.description: Time-to-trigger value for event A5 with trigger quantity RSRQ. If set to -1, this attribute is not used for report configuration.
attribute.dependencies: Feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage must be active.

class.name: ReportConfigB2Utra
class.description: This managed object contains report configuration settings for the B2 event for UTRA measurements. The B2 event is used to detect when a UTRAN cell becomes better than threshold2, and serving cell becomes worse than threshold1. The actual threshold values used can be adjusted by frequency relation related offsets if the feature Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility (MLSTM) is enabled.

attribute.name: reportConfigB2UtraId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: b2Threshold1Rsrp
attribute.description: The Reference Signal Received Power (RSRP) threshold1 value for eventB2.
attribute.dependencies: Only used if triggerQuantityB2 is set to RSRP.

attribute.name: b2Threshold1Rsrq
attribute.description: The Reference Signal Received Quality (RSRQ) in the threshold1 value for eventB2.
attribute.dependencies: Only used if triggerQuantityB2 is set to RSRQ.

attribute.name: b2Threshold2RscpUtra
attribute.description: Received Signal Code Power in the ThresholdUTRA, threshold2 value for eventB2.
attribute.dependencies: Used when measQuantityUtraFDD is set to RSCP. Also present for UTRA TDD.

attribute.name: b2Threshold2EcNoUtra
attribute.description: Ratio of energy per modulation bit to noise spectral density in the ThresholdUTRA, threshold2 value for eventB2. Not applicable for UTRA TDD.
attribute.dependencies: Only used when measQuantityUtraFDD is set to ECNO

attribute.name: hysteresisB2
attribute.description: The hysteresis value for the eventB2 measurement

attribute.name: timeToTriggerB2
attribute.description: Time-to-trigger value for event B2 measurements. If timeToTriggerB2Rsrq is -1, this attribute is used for both RSRP and RSRQ. But if not set to -1, this attribute is used only for RSRP.

attribute.name: triggerQuantityB2
attribute.description: The quantity for threshold1 (serving EUTRAN cell) that is sent to the UE, and is used together with threshold2 to trigger the eventB2.

attribute.name: timeToTriggerB2Rsrq
attribute.description: Time-to-trigger value for event B2 with trigger quantity RSRQ. If set to -1, this attribute is not used for report configuration.
attribute.dependencies: Feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage must be active.

attribute.name: hysteresisB2RsrqOffset
attribute.description: Offset to obtain the Hysteresis for B2 measurement for trigger quantity RSRQ. hysteresisB2Rsrq = hysteresisB2 + hysteresisB2RsrqOffset
attribute.dependencies: Feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage must be active.

class.name: Cdma2000FreqRelation
class.description:
This Managed Object represents a mobility relation between a EUtranCellFDD or an EUtranCellTDD and a CDMA2000Frequency. It contains parameters that are specific for this relation.
Deleting this MO while the parent EUtranCellFDD/EUtranCellTDD has operationalState set to ENABLED is not recommended as it may affect traffic.

attribute.name: cdma2000FreqRelationId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use.

attribute.name: connectedModeMobilityPrio
attribute.description: Prioritizes CDMA2000 frequencies among all frequencies related to the cell for UEs in connected mode. (0 means the lowest priority. -1 means the frequency is excluded.)

attribute.name: qOffsetFreq
attribute.description: Indicates a frequency-specific offset to apply when evaluating triggering conditions for measurement reporting.

attribute.name: cdma2000FreqRef
attribute.description: Reference to the Cdma2000Freq MO

attribute.name: b2Thr1RsrpCdma2000FreqOffset
attribute.description: The frequency-relation specific offset for the absolute threshold b2Threshold1Rsrp, RSRP threshold1 for event B2, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility.

attribute.name: b2Thr1RsrqCdma2000FreqOffset
attribute.description: The frequency-relation specific offset for the absolute threshold b2Threshold1Rsrq, RSRQ threshold1 for event B2, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility.

attribute.name: b2Thr2Cdma2000FreqOffset
attribute.description: The frequency-relation specific offset for the absolute threshold b2Threshold2Cdma2000, Signal quality in the thresholdCDMA2000 for event B2, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility.

attribute.name: qciB2ThrOffsets
attribute.description: Parameters for adding QCI profile and frequency relation specific offsets to B2 threshold values used for mobility decisions. Applicable if Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility (MLSTM) is active.

attribute.name: b2Cdma2000OffsetPerPC
attribute.description: The frequency-relation specific offset for the absolute threshold, RSRP/RSRQ threshold1 for event B2, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility and High Power UE.

class.name: ReportConfigA5Anr
class.description: The Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) delta report configuration settings for the A5 event measurements as compared to mobility provided in the parent MO class.

attribute.name: reportConfigA5AnrId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: a5Threshold1RsrpAnrDelta
attribute.description: This parameter together with a5Threshold1Rsrp specifies "The Reference Signal Received Power (RSRP) threshold1 value for eventA5." . The equation for calculating the RSRP threshold1 value for ANR is a5Threshold1Rsrp + a5Threshold1RsrpAnrDelta . Only used if triggerQuantityA5 onReportConfigA5 MO is set to RSRP.
attribute.dependencies: Not pure dependence towards parameter on ReportConficA5 Mo, but there should be a check that this attribute and corresponding attribute on ReportConfigA5 MO together sends out a valid number to the UE

attribute.name: a5Threshold2RsrpAnrDelta
attribute.description: This parameter together with a5Threshold2Rsrp specifies "The Reference Signal Received Power (RSRP) threshold2 value for eventA5." . The equation for calculating the RSRP threshold2 value for ANR is a5Threshold2Rsrp - a5Threshold2RsrpAnrDelta . Only used if triggerQuantityA5 onReportConfigA5 MO is set to RSRP.
attribute.dependencies: Not pure dependence towards parameter on ReportConficA5 Mo, but there should be a check that this attribute and corresponding attribute on ReportConfigA5 MO together sends out a valid number to the UE

attribute.name: a5Threshold1RsrqAnrDelta
attribute.description: This parameter together with a5Threshold1Rsrq specifies "The Reference Signal Received Quality (RSRQ) threshold1 value for eventA5." . The equation for calculating the RSRQ threshold1 value for ANR is a5Threshold1Rsrq + a5Threshold1RsrqAnrDelta . Only used if triggerQuantityA5 onReportConfigA5 MO is set to RSRQ.
attribute.dependencies: Not pure dependence towards parameter on ReportConficA5 Mo, but there should be a check that this attribute and corresponding attribute on ReportConfigA5 MO together sends out a valid number to the UE

attribute.name: a5Threshold2RsrqAnrDelta
attribute.description: This parameter together with a5Threshold2Rsrq specifies "The Reference Signal Received Quality (RSRQ) threshold2 value for eventA5." . The equation for calculating the RSRQ threshold2 value for ANR is a5Threshold2Rsrq -a5Threshold2RsrqAnrDelta . Only used if triggerQuantityA5 onReportConfigA5 MO is set to RSRQ.
attribute.dependencies: Not pure dependence towards parameter on ReportConficA5 Mo, but there should be a check that this attribute and corresponding attribute on ReportConfigA5 MO together sends out a valid number to the UE

attribute.name: timeToTriggerA5
attribute.description: The time-to-trigger value for the eventA5 measurement.

attribute.name: hysteresisA5
attribute.description: The hysteresis value for the eventA5 measurement.

class.name: ReportConfigEUtraBestCellAnr
class.description: The ANR delta report configuration settings for the A3 event measurements as compared to mobility provided in the parent MO class.

attribute.name: a3offsetAnrDelta
attribute.description: The offset value for eventA3. Dependent on triggerQuantityA3 on MO ReportConfigEUtraBestCell and is a delta towards a3offset on triggerQuantityA3, The a3offset used in the ANR measure is calculated as a3offset (on ReportConfigEUtraBestCell) - a3offset AnrDelta
attribute.dependencies: Not pure dependence towards parameter on ReportConfigEUtraBestCell Mo, but there should be a check that this attribute and corresponding attribute on ReportConfigEUtraBestCell MO together sends out a valid number to the UE

attribute.name: hysteresisA3
attribute.description: The hysteresis value for eventA3.

attribute.name: reportConfigEUtraBestCellAnrId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: timeToTriggerA3
attribute.description: The time to trigger value for eventA3.

class.name: AdmissionControl
class.description: Contains parameters for the admission control function.

attribute.name: paArpOverride
attribute.description:
The eNB interprets Allocation Retention Priority Levels, received from the Core Network, between 1 and paArpOverride (inclusive) as Privileged Access.
The value zero will disable Privileged Access ARP override.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can impact accessibility at high load.

attribute.name: admissionControlId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: dlTransNwBandwidth
attribute.description: Downlink transport network bandwidth for LTE. Not used for Baseband.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect in DU radio node.

attribute.name: ulTransNwBandwidth
attribute.description: Uplink transport network bandwidth for LTE. Not used for Baseband.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect in DU radio node.

attribute.name: arpBasedPreEmptionState
attribute.description: Activates or deactivates the Allocation and Retention Priority (ARP) based pre-emption function. The value of the attribute is irrelevant when no valid license key is installed for the Differentiated Admission Control feature.

attribute.name: resourceReservationForPAState
attribute.description: Activates or deactivates the Resource Reservation for Priviliged Access.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can impact accessibility at high load.

attribute.name: dlMbmsGbrRatio
attribute.description:
This parameter sets the wanted downlink resource utilization ratio of Mbms-Gbr bearers on transport network. The value given in this parameter specifies the Mbms-Gbr part of the total bandwidth. The parameter will be used by the Admission Control to balance Gbr, Mbms-Gbr and Non-Gbr use of resources.
Unit: 0.001
attribute.dependencies: The downlink transport network bandwidth for LTE needs to be configured into attribute AdmissionControl::dlTransNwBandwidth.

attribute.name: resourceReservationForDifferentiation
attribute.description: Sets the resource reservation used for ARP based differentiation. The value of this attribute is irrelevant when no valid license key is installed for the Differentiated Admission Control feature.

attribute.name: dlAdmOverloadThr
attribute.description: Sets the highest allowed downlink radio resource utilization ratio for admission of a GBR radio bearer. Applies to each resource considered by Dynamic GBR Admission Control. Resource utilization is checked against this threshold for all new, re-established or incoming handover GBR bearer requests.
attribute.dependencies: dlAdmOverloadThr>=dlAdmDifferentiationThr

attribute.name: ulAdmOverloadThr
attribute.description: Sets the highest allowed uplink radio resource utilization ratio for admission of a GBR radio bearer. Applies to each resource considered by Dynamic GBR Admission Control. Resource utilization is checked against this threshold for all new, re-established or incoming handover GBR bearer requests.
attribute.dependencies: ulAdmOverloadThr>=ulAdmDifferentiationThr

attribute.name: dlAdmDifferentiationThr
attribute.description:
If both Dynamic GBR Admission Control and Differentiated Admission Control are licensed and activated:
Sets the highest allowed downlink radio resource utilization ratio for the GBR bearers with lower ARP priority in radio bearer admission. Applies to each resource considered by Dynamic GBR Admission Control.
If Dynamic GBR Admission Control is licensed and activated but Differentiated Admission Control is not licensed or not activated:
Sets the highest allowed downlink radio resource utilization ratio for the GBR bearers in radio bearer admission. Applies to each resource considered by Dynamic GBR Admission Control.
attribute.dependencies: dlAdmDifferentiationThr<=dlAdmOverloadThr

attribute.name: ulAdmDifferentiationThr
attribute.description:
If both Dynamic GBR Admission Control and Differentiated Admission Control are licensed and activated:
Sets the highest allowed uplink radio resource utilization ratio for the GBR bearers with lower ARP priority in radio bearer admission. Applies to each resource considered by Dynamic GBR Admission Control.
If Dynamic GBR Admission Control is licensed and activated but Differentiated Admission Control is not licensed or not activated:
Sets the highest allowed uplink radio resource utilization ratio for the GBR bearers in radio bearer admission. Applies to each resource considered by Dynamic GBR Admission Control.
attribute.dependencies: ulAdmDifferentiationThr<=ulAdmOverloadThr

attribute.name: admNrRrcDifferentiationThr
attribute.description: Highest allowed fraction of non-privileged RRC connections that might be admitted without ARP based differentiation. When fraction of RRC connected users versus available capacity exceeds this threshold, only RRC connections that setup bearers with high ARP priority are admitted. Other RRC connections may only be admitted if preemption is possible. The fraction is given with respect to the maximum capacity after privileged access resource reservation has been subtracted.

attribute.name: admNrRbDifferentiationThr
attribute.description: Highest allowed fraction of radio bearers not reserved for privileged access connections that might be admitted without ARP based differentiation. When fraction of active radio bearers versus available capacity exceeds this threshold, only bearer requests with high ARP priority are admitted. Other bearer requests may only be admitted if preemption is possible. The fraction is given with respect to the maximum capacity after privileged access resource reservation has been subtracted.

attribute.name: nrOfPaConnReservationsPerCell
attribute.description: Number of privileged access connections to be reserved per cell.
attribute.dependencies: Applicable only if resourceReservationForPAState is set to ACTIVATED.

attribute.name: nrOfRbReservationsPerPaConn
attribute.description: Number of Radio Bearers to be reserved per privileged access connection. This includes SRB1, SRB2 and DRBs.
attribute.dependencies: Applicable only if resourceReservationForPAState is set to ACTIVATED.

attribute.name: admResourceMinQciPrio
attribute.description: Lowest QCI priority (highest numerical value) for DRBs included into monitoring of radio resources considered in GBR bearer admission control. For any value of this parameter, bearer admission control also takes into account resource usage from non-DRB traffic with higher priority than DRBs, e.g. Signaling Radio Bearers. If this parameter is set to 0, only the resource usage for traffic with priority higher than DRBs is monitored.

attribute.name: lbAtoThresholdLevel1
attribute.description: When the usage for a monitored system resource has exceeded this threshold then Admission-Triggered Offload (ATO) Level 1 is triggered.
attribute.dependencies: lbAtoThresholdLevel1=<lbAtoThresholdLevel2<min(ulAdmDifferentiationThr, dlAdmDifferentiationThr)
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: lbAtoThresholdLevel2
attribute.description: When the usage for a monitored system resource has exceeded this threshold then Admission-Triggered Offload (ATO) Level 2 is triggered.
attribute.dependencies: lbAtoThresholdLevel1=<lbAtoThresholdLevel2<min(ulAdmDifferentiationThr, dlAdmDifferentiationThr)
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

class.name: ExternalGeranCell
class.description: This Managed Object contains a GERAN cell.

action.name: changeFrequency
action.description: Changes the frequency of an external Geran cell. Before running this action, make sure that the target GeranFrequency for the ExternalGeranCell is created and that it refer to one of the GeranFreqGroup(s) that is referred from the same eUtranCell as the ExternalGeranCell. This MO action includes the following steps: - The ExternalGeranCell will be updated to refer to the target GeranFrequency. - If the target GeranFrequency is not referred from same eUtranCell(s) as the ExternalGeranCell included in the changeFrequency action, the action will fail and an exception will be issued.

parameter.name: arfcnValueGeranDl
parameter.description: The new DL frequency for this cell.

parameter.name: bandIndicator
parameter.description: The attribute indicates the GERAN frequency band if the ARFCN value concerns either a DCS 1800 or a PCS 1900 carrier frequency. For ARFCN values not associated with either of these bands, the indicator has no meaning.

attribute.name: externalGeranCellId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: reservedBy
attribute.description: Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.

attribute.name: plmnIdentity
attribute.description: PLMN ID supported by the cell.
attribute.disturbances: Changes may affect traffic

attribute.name: lac
attribute.description: The Location Area Code of the external GERAN cell. A fixed-length code identifying the location area within a PLMN. Refer to 3GPP TS 23.003. Special values: The values 0 and 65534 are reserved for special cases where no valid Location Area Identity (LAI) exists in the network.
attribute.disturbances: Changes may affect traffic

attribute.name: cellIdentity

attribute.name: geranCellRelationId

attribute.description: Indicates whether the MO has been created by the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function or operator.

attribute.name: timeOfCreation
attribute.description: Indicates the date and time when the MO was created by the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function or operator. Format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS

attribute.name: coverageIndicator
attribute.description: Defines whether the coverage area of the EUTRAN cell and the GERAN cell are indicated to overlap (has approximately the same coverage area), or whether the coverage area of the GERAN cell is indicated to cover the EUTRAN cell, or if it is contained in the EUTRAN cell.
attribute.disturbances: Changes may affect traffic

attribute.name: isRemoveAllowed
attribute.description: Indicates if the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function is allowed to remove this object. It does not restrict operator removal of the object. Objects created by ANR have this parameter set to true initially.

attribute.description: Reference to ExternalGeranCell instance. At MO creation, it is mandatory to supply a valid reference to an ExternalGeranCell.

class.name: ExternalUtranCellFDD
class.description: This Managed Object contains a UTRAN cell for Frequency Division Duplex (FDD).

action.name: changeFrequency
action.description: Changes the frequency of the external cell. This MO action includes the following steps: - Create the UtranFrequency MO (with the specified arfcnValueUtranDl) if it does not already exist. - Create the UtranFreqRelation MO (with the same attribute values as the existing UtranFreqRelation MO) if it does not already exist. - Create a new ExternalUtranCellFDD MO (with the same attribute values as the existing ExternalUtranCellFDD MO) under the specified UtranFrequency MO. - For each UtranCellRelation to the old ExternalUtranCellFDD, create a new UtranCellRelation MO (with the same attribute values as the existing UtranCellRelation MO) referring to the new ExternalUtranCellFDD MO. The old UtranCellRelation MOs are then removed. - Remove the old ExternalUtranCellFDD MO. This will be performed after successful execution of this MO action.

parameter.name: arfcnValueUtranDl
parameter.description: The new DL frequency for this cell.

attribute.name: externalUtranCellFDDId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: physicalCellIdentity
attribute.description: Indicates the physical layer identity of the cell, that is, the primary scrambling code.

attribute.name: cellIdentity
attribute.description: UTRAN Cell Identity. Used to identity the cell uniquely within UTRAN Iu mode.
attribute.disturbances: Changes may affect traffic

attribute.name: plmnIdentity
attribute.description: PLMN ID supported by the cell.
attribute.disturbances: Changes may affect traffic

attribute.name: reservedBy
attribute.description: Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.

attribute.description: Label for free use.

attribute.description: Indicates whether the MO has been created by the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function or operator.

attribute.description: Indicates the time and date when the MO was created by the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function or operator. Format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS

attribute.description: The identity of the UtranCell represented by this MO, particularly for automatically created ExternalUtranCell managed objects. The masterUtranCellId is set to the Full Distinguished Name (FDN).

attribute.name: lac
attribute.description: The Location Area Code of the external UTRAN cell. A fixed-length code identifying the location area within a PLMN. Refer to 3GPP TS 23.003. The value 0 of the attribute is used to mark invalid/unusable lac information for the cell. For example, handover to an external UTRAN cell (that is part of a Utran cell relation) can be considered only if the value of the lac attribute is NOT 0.

attribute.description: The Routing Area Code of a routing area. The value -1 of the attribute is used to mark that the optional RAC IE should NOT be sent in the Target ID IE of the HANDOVER REQUIRED S1 message. Refer to 3GPP TS 36.413.

class.name: UtranTDDFreqRelation
class.description:
This Managed Object represents a UTRAN TDD mobility relation between a EUtranCellFDD or EUtranCellTDD and a UtranFrequency. It contains parameters that are specific for this relation.
Deleting this MO while the parent EUtranCellFDD/EUtranCellTDD has operationalState set to ENABLED is not recommended as it may affect traffic.

attribute.name: utranTDDFreqRelationId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use.

attribute.name: utranFrequencyRef
attribute.description: Reference to the UTRAN frequency MO, UtranFrequency.

attribute.name: cellReselectionPriority
attribute.description:
CellReselectionPriority concerns the absolute priority of the concerned carrier frequency, as used by the cell reselection procedure. Corresponds with parameter "priority" in TS 36.304.
Value 0 means lowest priority. The UE behaviour for the case the field is absent, if applicable, is specified in TS 36.304.
attribute.dependencies: The value must be unique and not already used by other RAT, i.e. equal priorities between RATs are not supported.

attribute.name: threshXHigh
attribute.description: This specifies the threshold used by the UE when reselecting towards the higher priority frequency X than current serving frequency. Each frequency of UTRAN might have a specific threshold. Parameter "Threshx,high" in TS 36.304

attribute.name: threshXLow
attribute.description: This specifies the threshold used in reselection towards frequency X priority from a higher priority frequency. Each frequency of UTRAN might have a specific threshold. Parameter "Threshx,low" in TS 36.304.

attribute.name: qRxLevMin
attribute.description: Parameter Qrxlevmin, see TS 25.304. Specifies the minimum required Rx level in the cell expressed in dBm.

attribute.name: pMaxUtra
attribute.description: The maximum allowed transmission power on the (uplink) carrier frequency, see TS 25.304.

attribute.name: allowedPlmnList
attribute.description:
List of all Public Land Mobile Network (PLMN) IDs allowed for this frequency relation.
A UE that does not support one of the IDs included in the allowedPlmnList does not measure on this frequency, according to the UE Handover Restriction List.
No values in allowedPlmnList imply that the frequency has no restrictions for PLMN.
The PLMN ID contains the following parts: 1. MobileCountryCode, MCC, 3 digits 2. MobileNetworkCode, MNC, 2 or 3 digits (the correct number of digits is set in the mncLength member of this Struct)
For example, if MCC=125 and MNC=46, then plmnId=12546.

attribute.name: connectedModeMobilityPrio
attribute.description: Prioritizes UTRA frequencies among all frequencies related to the cell for UEs in connected mode. (0 means the lowest priority. -1 means the frequency is excluded.)

attribute.name: csFallbackPrio
attribute.description: Prioritizes UTRAN frequencies among all frequencies related to the cell for UEs in connected mode. Sets the priority to which frequency/frequency group to make CS Fallback to. The value -1 means the frequency is excluded. The value 0 means the lowest priority. The value 7 means the highest priority.

attribute.name: csFallbackPrioEC
attribute.description: Prioritizes UTRAN frequencies for emergency calls among all frequencies/frequency groups related to the cell for UEs in connected mode. Sets the priority to which frequency to make emergency call CS Fallback to. The value -1 means the frequency is excluded. The value 0 means the lowest priority. The value 7 means the highest priority.

attribute.name: qOffsetFreq
attribute.description: Indicates a frequency-specific offset to apply when evaluating triggering conditions for measurement reporting.

attribute.name: mobilityAction
attribute.description: The preferred way to transfer a UE in connected mode to a UTRAN TDD frequency in case of coverage triggered mobility.

attribute.name: mobilityActionCsfb
attribute.description: The preferred way to transfer a UE in connected mode to a UTRAN TDD frequency in case of CS Fallback mobility.

attribute.name: anrMeasOn
attribute.description: ANR performs measurement on the referenced frequency if this parameter is set to true. Otherwise, ANR does not perform any measurements on this frequency.

attribute.name: b2Thr1RsrpUtraFreqOffset
attribute.description: The frequency-relation specific offset for the absolute threshold b2Threshold1Rsrp, RSRP threshold1 for event B2, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility.

attribute.name: b2Thr1RsrqUtraFreqOffset
attribute.description: The frequency-relation specific offset for the absolute threshold b2Threshold1Rsrq, RSRQ threshold1 for event B2, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility.

attribute.name: b2Thr2RscpUtraFreqOffset
attribute.description: The frequency-relation specific offset for the absolute threshold b2Threshold2Rscp, RSCP in the ThresholdUTRATDD for event B2, used for Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility.

attribute.name: qciB2ThrOffsets
attribute.description: Parameters for adding QCI profile and frequency relation specific offsets to B2 threshold values used for mobility decisions. Applicable if Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility (MLSTM) is active

attribute.description: This parameter indicates if the external UTRAN cell is RIM capable. If the value is RIMIncapable, no attempt will be made to create a RIM association to the external UTRAN cell, other values will result in a attempt to create a RIM association.
attribute.disturbances: If the value is other than RIMIncapable the eNB will try to set up a RIM association to the external cell

attribute.name: rimAssociationStatus
attribute.description: This parameter indicates the current status of the RIM association to this external cell.
