class.name: SubscriberProfileID
class.description: Parent for all SPID related MOCs

attribute.name: subscriberProfileIDId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use.

class.name: HoWhiteList
class.description: Contains a whitelist of SPID values that are allowed to perform a incoming handover requests when the cell is in the mode "reserved for operator use"

attribute.name: spidList
attribute.description: A list of UEs, that are allowed to perform incoming handover to a cell that is in mode "reserved for operator use". Note: When value is configured to -1000, the parameter is ignored.

attribute.name: hoWhiteListId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use.

class.name: RATFreqPrio
class.description: Contains data that overrides information in the IdleModeMobilityControlInfo and RedirectedCarrierInfo (sent to UE in RRC Connection Release) that is configured for the cell. It also contains attributes that control load balancing and offloading. Only UEs that have a SPID value matching the list in this MOC are affected.

attribute.name: rATFreqPrioId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN

attribute.name: spidList
attribute.description: A list that includes all UEs that are affected by the RAT priorities specified in this MOC. Note: When value is configured to -1000, the parameter is ignored.

attribute.name: t320
attribute.description: Validity time for cell reselection priority information provided by dedicated signalling. Used by the UE. This parameter is only used in the optional feature 'subscriber triggered mobility' when setting new cell reselection priorities based on SPID value for a specific UE.

attribute.name: freqPrioListEUTRA
attribute.description: Prioritizes EUTRAN frequencies among all frequencies related to the cell for UE cell reselection procedure and for UEs in connected mode.

attribute.name: freqGroupPrioListGERAN
attribute.description: Prioritizes GERAN frequencies among all frequencies related to the cell for UE cell reselection procedure and for UEs in connected mode.

attribute.name: freqPrioListUTRA
attribute.description: Prioritizes UTRAN frequencies among all frequencies related to the cell for UE cell reselection procedure and for Ues in connected mode.

attribute.name: bandClassPrioListCDMA2000
attribute.description: Prioritizes CDMA2000 frequencies among all frequencies related to the cell for UE cell reselection procedure and for Ues in connected mode. It is not possible to create every possible frequency and band relation since that would require to many instances using this representation.

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use.

attribute.name: bandClassPrioListCDMA1xRtt
attribute.description: CDMA2000 1xRTT frequency prioritization. This attribute prioritizes CDMA2000 1xRTT frequencies among all frequencies related to the cell for UE cell reselection procedure and for UEs in connected mode. It is not possible to create every possible frequency and band relation since that would require too many instances using this representation.

class.name: LoadBalancingFunction
class.description: Contains parameters and constraints for Idle Mode Load Balancing functions

attribute.name: loadBalancingFunctionId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: lbThreshold
attribute.description: The minimum load (subscription ratio) difference to trigger load balancing action.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: lbCeiling
attribute.description: The maximum load (subscription ratio) difference taken into account in load balancing action.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: lbRateOffsetCoefficient
attribute.description: Coefficient of rate-dependent load balancing offset. Moderates how much the load balancing must be offset towards a cell with higher capacity.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: lbUtranOffloadBackoffTime
attribute.description: Backoff time for eNodeB The value applies to inhibit further offload to a UTRAN target cell that rejects incoming offload.

attribute.name: lbEUtranOffloadBackoffTime
attribute.description: This attribute indicates a backoff time for eNodeB. The value applies to inhibit further offload to a EUTRAN target cell that rejects incoming offload.

attribute.name: lbCauseCodeS1SourceTriggersOffload
attribute.description:
This attribute determines the cause code set by the eNodeB in outgoing S1AP HANDOVER REQUIRED when the handover is triggered by offload to Inter-Frequency EUTRAN neighbor or Inter-RAT UTRAN neighbour. See 3GPP 36.413.
The cause code LOAD_BALANCING can not be used for S1 handovers according to 3GPP 36.413. In case LOAD_BALANCING is selected, then the default value is chosen and used by the eNB.

attribute.name: lbCauseCodeS1TargetAcceptsOffload
attribute.description:
This attribute determines the cause code in an incoming S1AP HANDOVER REQUEST used by the eNodeB to determine whether or not the incoming handover is triggered by offload or not. See 3GPP 36.413.
The cause code LOAD_BALANCING can not be used for S1 handovers according to 3GPP 36.413. In case LOAD_BALANCING is selected, then the default value is chosen and used by the eNB.

attribute.name: lbCauseCodeX2SourceTriggersOffload
attribute.description: This attribute determines the cause code set by the eNodeB in an outgoing X2AP HANDOVER REQUEST when the handover is triggered by offload to an Inter-Frequency EUTRAN neighbour. See 3GPP 36.423.

attribute.name: lbCauseCodeX2TargetAcceptsOffload
attribute.description: This attribute determines the cause code in an incoming X2AP HANDOVER REQUEST used by the eNodeB to determine whether or not the incoming handover is triggered by offload or not. See 3GPP 36.423.

attribute.name: lbHitRateEUtranMeasUeThreshold
attribute.description: Specifies the required minimum number of connected users in the (source) cell to allow initiation of UE measurements for lbHitRate estimation on E-UTRAN frequencies.

attribute.name: lbHitRateUtranMeasUeThreshold
attribute.description: Specifies the required minimum number of connected users in the (source) cell to allow initiation of UE measurements for lbHitRate estimation on UTRAN frequencies.

attribute.name: lbHitRateEUtranMeasUeIntensity
attribute.description: Specifies the number of UE measurements for lbHitRate estimation (per cell and Load Balancing cycle) for each E-UTRAN frequency.

attribute.name: lbHitRateUtranMeasUeIntensity
attribute.description: Specifies the number of UE measurements for lbHitRate estimation (per cell and Load Balancing cycle) for each UTRAN frequency.

attribute.name: lbHitRateEUtranAddThreshold
attribute.description: EUtran cell relations with a lbHitRate value greater than this threshold are considered suitable for load management.
attribute.dependencies: lbHitRateEUtranAddThreshold > lbHitRateEUtranRemoveThreshold

attribute.name: lbHitRateUtranAddThreshold
attribute.description: Utran cell relations with a lbHitRate value greater than this threshold are considered suitable for load management.
attribute.dependencies: lbHitRateUtranAddThreshold > lbHitRateUtranRemoveThreshold

attribute.name: lbHitRateEUtranRemoveThreshold
attribute.description: EUtran cell relations with a lbHitRate value lower than this threshold are NOT considered suitable for load management.
attribute.dependencies: lbHitRateEUtranAddThreshold > lbHitRateEUtranRemoveThreshold

attribute.name: lbHitRateUtranRemoveThreshold
attribute.description: Utran cell relations with a lbHitRate value lower than this threshold are NOT considered suitable for load management.
attribute.dependencies: lbHitRateUtranAddThreshold > lbHitRateUtranRemoveThreshold

attribute.name: txPwrForOverlaidCellDetect
attribute.description: Determines the maximum transmission power of the source cell on which feature Overlaid Cell Detection is allowed to be applied. For source cells with higher transmission power than specified in this attribute, overlaid neighbor cells are not identified.

attribute.name: ocdMaxNoHighHitRateCells
attribute.description: Maximum number of cell relations for each frequency that can be identified as neighbors with a high hit rate by feature Overlaid Cell Detection.

attribute.name: ocdMinHighHitThresh
attribute.description: Minimum required hit rate to qualify a cell relation as a neighbor with a high hit rate by feature Overlaid Cell Detection.

attribute.name: lbMeasScalingLimit
attribute.description: Scaling factor for the required number of UE candidates needed for load balancing measurements to meet the load balancing target. Note: The minimum value of the attribute is internally limited to 10.

attribute.name: lbDiffCaOffset
attribute.description: The maximum load difference between the target cell and the source cell in order to redirect a CA capable UE to that target cell. The maximum load difference between the source cell and the target cell in order to apply the capacity criterion when load balancing a CA capable UE.
attribute.dependencies: lbDiffCaOffset>lbThreshold
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic

attribute.name: lbRateOffsetLoadThreshold
attribute.description: Specifies the threshold for the source and target cell average load, above which the rate offset is set to zero.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic

attribute.name: lbCaThreshold
attribute.description: The maximum load in the target cell in order to redirect a CA capable UE to that target cell. The maximum load in the current cell in order to apply the capacity criterion when load balancing a CA capable UE.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic

attribute.name: lbCaCapHysteresis
attribute.description: Capacity related hysteresis value considered when checking the capacity criterion for both load balancing of CA capable UEs and CA triggered redirection.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic

attribute.name: lbUeEvaluationTimer
attribute.description: Timer to initiate evaluation of a UE for load balancing measurement. The timer is started at UE Context Setup. If value = 0 the timer is not started, and UEs will only be evaluated for load balancing measurement at UE Context Setup.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic

attribute.name: isUlEvalAllowedAtTpLbHo
attribute.description: Configures whether an uplink evaluation is allowed during a handover triggered by Throughput-Aware IFLB. Used when Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is enabled.

attribute.name: isUlEvalAllowedAtCaTrHo
attribute.description: Configures whether an uplink evaluation is allowed during a handover triggered by Carrier Aggregation-Aware IFLB. Used when Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is enabled.

class.name: ReportConfigA4
class.description: This managed object contains report configuration settings for the A4 event measurements. The A4 event is used to detect when neighbor cell becomes better than threshold.

attribute.name: reportConfigA4Id
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: a4ThresholdRsrp
attribute.description: The Reference Signal Received Power (RSRP) threshold value for eventA4.
attribute.dependencies: Only used if triggerQuantityA4 is set to RSRP.

attribute.name: a4ThresholdRsrq
attribute.description: The Reference Signal Received Quality (RSRQ) threshold value for eventA4.
attribute.dependencies: Only used if triggerQuantityA4 is set to RSRQ.

attribute.name: hysteresisA4
attribute.description: The hysteresis value for the eventA4 measurement.

attribute.name: timeToTriggerA4
attribute.description: The time-to-trigger value for the eventA4 measurement.

attribute.name: triggerQuantityA4
attribute.description: The quantity that triggers the eventA4 for the eventA4 measurement.

class.name: ReportConfigB1Geran
class.description: This managed object contains report configuration settings for the B1 event for GERAN measurements. The B1 event is used to detect when a GERAN cell becomes better than threshold.

attribute.name: reportConfigB1GeranId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: b1ThresholdGeran
attribute.description: The Signal Quality in the ThresholdGERAN, threshold value for eventB1.

attribute.name: hysteresisB1
attribute.description: The hysteresis value for the eventB1 measurement on GERAN

attribute.name: timeToTriggerB1
attribute.description: The time to trigger value for the eventB1 measurement.

class.name: ReportConfigB1Utra
class.description: This managed object contains report configuration settings for the B1 event for WCDMA measurements. The B1 event is used to detect when a WCDMA cell becomes better than threshold.

attribute.name: reportConfigB1UtraId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: b1ThresholdEcNoUtra
attribute.description: Ratio of energy per modulation bit to noise spectral density in the ThresholdUTRA, threshold value for eventB1. Not applicable for UTRA TDD.
attribute.dependencies: Only used when measQuantityUtraFDD is set to ECNO

attribute.name: hysteresisB1
attribute.description: The hysteresis value for the eventB1 measurement on UTRAN

attribute.name: timeToTriggerB1
attribute.description: The time to trigger value for the eventB1 measurement on UTRAN.

attribute.name: b1ThresholdRscpUtra
attribute.description: RSCP threshold value for the event B1 measurement for Coverage based IRAT handover to UTRAN.
attribute.dependencies: Only used when measQuantityUtraFDD is set to RSCP

class.name: ParameterChangeRequests
class.description: Contains the list of parameter change requests produced by open loop SON functions.

action.name: approve
action.description: Approves a set of pending change request.

parameter.name: pcrList
parameter.description: A list of integers matching the seqNo of the change requests. Any integer not matching a pending change request will be ignored.

action.name: reject
action.description: Rejects a set of pending change request.

parameter.name: pcrList
parameter.description: A list of integers matching the seqNo of the change requests. Any integer not matching a pending change request will be ignored.

attribute.name: parameterChangeRequestList
attribute.description: The complete list of outstanding parameter change requests.
attribute.dependencies: When a change request is added, updated, rejected, accepted or cancelled, the request is also copied to the latestUpdate parameter. The eNodeB may keep the rejected, accepted or cancelled change requests in this list for an indeterminate time.

attribute.name: latestUpdate
attribute.description: The latest changed parameter change request.
attribute.dependencies: When the eNodeB changes the parameterChangeRequestList, the changed struct is copied to this parameter, with the state field updated.

attribute.name: parameterChangeRequestsId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

class.name: ReportConfigEUtraInterFreqLb
class.description: Contains the Report Configuration settings for UE measurements initiated for EUTRA Inter-frequency Load Balancing

attribute.name: reportConfigEUtraInterFreqLbId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: a5Threshold2Rsrp
attribute.description: The Reference Signal Received Power (RSRP) threshold2 value for eventA5.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic

attribute.name: hysteresisA5
attribute.description: The hysteresis value for the eventA5 measurement.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic

attribute.name: a5Threshold1Rsrp
attribute.description: The Reference Signal Received Power (RSRP) threshold1 value for eventA5.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic

attribute.name: a5Threshold2Rsrq
attribute.description: The Reference Signal Received Quality (RSRQ) threshold2 value for eventA5.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic

class.name: DrxProfile
class.description: DRX profiles and DRX parameters that map to different QCIs. First instance, DrxProfileId 0, is default DRX profile. Profile eMBMS VoLTE DRX (drxProfile=18) is used when DRX is combined with eMBMS and VoLTE coexistence.

attribute.name: drxProfileId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN

attribute.name: onDurationTimer
attribute.description: Number of consecutive PDCCH-subframes at beginning of a DRX Cycle. TS36.331 ch. 6.3.2, RRC parameter onDurationTimer. Ericsson recommends to make shortDrxCycle value larger than onDurationTimer value.

attribute.name: drxInactivityTimer
attribute.description: Specifies the number of consecutive PDCCH-subframe(s) after successfully decoding a PDCCH indicating an initial UL or DL user data transmission for this UE. TS36.331 ch. 6.3.2, RRC parameter drx-InactivityTimer.

attribute.name: drxRetransmissionTimer
attribute.description: Specifies the maximum number of consecutive PDCCH-subframe(s) for as soon as a DL retransmission is expected by the UE. TS36.331 ch. 6.3.2, RRC parameter drx-RetransmissionTimer.

attribute.name: shortDrxCycle
attribute.description: Consecutive subframes between on-duration phases, that is period of re-occurring on-duration phases. Parameter is applied when UE follows short DRX cycle. Parameter is ignored if shortDrxCycleTimer = 0, instead longDrxCycle is applied and UE follows long DRX cycle only. Corresponds to 3GPP information element shortDRX-Cycle. Ericsson recommends to make shortDrxCycle value larger than onDurationTimer value.
attribute.dependencies: If attribute shortDrxCycleTimer = 0, shortDrxCycles is not used.

attribute.name: shortDrxCycleTimer
attribute.description: Specifies the number of consecutive subframes the UE must follow the short DRX cycle after the DRX Inactivity Timer has expired. Value in multiples of shortDRX-Cycles. A value of 1 corresponds to 1 * shortDRX-Cycle, a value of 2 corresponds to 2 * shortDRX-Cycle and so on. Corresponds to 3GPP timer drxShortCycleTimer. The value 0 means that short DRX cycles are not used.

attribute.name: longDrxCycle
attribute.description: The value of longDrxCycle is in number of sub-frames. If shortDrxCycle is configured, the value of longDrxCycle shall be a multiple of the shortDrxCycle value.
attribute.dependencies: Needs to be a multiple of shortDrxCycle

attribute.name: longDrxCycleOnly
attribute.description: The longDrxCycleOnly value is used as longDrxCycle when the UE does not support shortDrxCycle. The value of longDrxCycleOnly is in number of sub-frames.

attribute.name: drxState
attribute.description: Whether or not DRX is enabled for this profile. Hence if this DRX profile uses DRX.

class.name: PwsCmas
class.description: This MO class stores warning information to be broadcast in SIB12

attribute.name: pwsCmasId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

class.name: Mbms
class.description: This MO is the top level MO for Multimedia Broadcast Multicast Service (MBMS). It contains attributes, which are common for all parts of MBMS in the node.

attribute.name: mbmsId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use.

attribute.name: mappingInfoSIB13
attribute.description: Defines to which SI message SIB13 is mapped.
attribute.statusInformation: Since L16B. Replaced by MappingInfoSIBs.mappingInfoSIB13 in EUtranCellFDD/EUtranCellTDD::mappingInfo. Planned to be removed.
attribute.dependencies: See siWindowLength for further information.

attribute.name: changeNotificationSIB13
attribute.description: Indicates, when the SIB13 content is changed, if SI Change Notification shall be broadcasted prior to broadcast of updated SI.
attribute.statusInformation: Since L16B. Replaced by ChangeNotificationSIBs.changeNotificationSIB13 in EUtranCellFDD/EUtranCellTDD::changeNotification. Planned to be removed.

attribute.name: synchPeriodLength
attribute.description: MBMS synchronization period length.

attribute.name: tMbmsAuditTimer
attribute.description: The time the eNB waits with the deletion of ongoing MBMS sessions that are not re-started by MBMS SESSION START after a successful M3 SETUP procedure.

attribute.name: m1IpInterfaceRef
attribute.description: Refers to the InterfaceIPv4 and InterfaceIPv6 MO instances used to configure the IP interface for M1 user plane connections.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

class.name: MbsfnArea
class.description: This MO represents a MBMS Single Frequence Network (MBSFN) area and contains MBSFN area related parameters.

attribute.name: mbsfnAreaId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use.

attribute.name: mbsfnAreaIdentity
attribute.description: Specifies the MBSFN area identity.
attribute.precondition: Attribute administrativeState must be set to LOCKED before modifying this attribute.

attribute.name: nonMbsfnRegionLength
attribute.description: Specifies how many symbols from the beginning of the subframe constitute the non-MBSFN region. This value applies in all subframes of the MBSFN area used for PMCH transmission. The values 1 and 2 correspond to 1 and 2 symbols, respectively.
attribute.precondition: Attribute administrativeState must be set to LOCKED before modifying this attribute.

attribute.name: notificationIndicator
attribute.description: Specifies which PDCCH bit is used to notify the UE about change of the MCCH applicable for this MBSFN area. Value 0 corresponds with the least significant bit as defined in TS 36.212 and so on.
attribute.statusInformation: Since L16B. Planned to be removed.
attribute.precondition: Attribute administrativeState must be set to LOCKED before modifying this attribute.

attribute.name: mcchRepetitionPeriod
attribute.description: Specifies the interval between transmissions of MCCH information, in radio frames, Value 32 corresponds to 32 radio frames, 64 corresponds to 64 radio frames and so on.
attribute.dependencies: Attribute must be greater than mchSchedulingPeriod in MO class PmchMch.
attribute.precondition: Attribute administrativeState must be set to LOCKED before modifying this attribute.

attribute.name: mcchOffset
attribute.description: Specifies, together with the mcchRepetitionPeriod, the radio frames in which MCCH is scheduled i.e. MCCH is scheduled in radio frames for which: SFN mod mcchRepetitionPeriod = mcch-Offset.
attribute.statusInformation: Since L16A. Planned to be removed.
attribute.precondition: Attribute administrativeState must be set to LOCKED before modifying this attribute.

attribute.name: mcchModificationPeriod
attribute.description: Specifies periodically appearing boundaries, i.e. radio frames for which SFN mod mcch-ModificationPeriod = 0, The contents of different transmissions of MCCH information can only be different if there is at least one such boundary in-between them.
attribute.dependencies: The mchSchedulingPeriod in the MO class PmchMch must be smaller than or equal to mcchModificationPeriod.
attribute.precondition: Attribute administrativeState must be set to LOCKED before modifying this attribute.

attribute.name: sfAllocInfo
attribute.description: Indicates the subframes of the radio frames indicated by the mcch-RepetitionPeriod and the mcch-Offset, that may carry MCCH. Value "1" indicates that the corresponding subframe is allocated. Value "0" indicates that the corresponding subframe is not allocated. The following mapping applies: FDD: The first/ leftmost bit defines the allocation for subframe #1 of the radio frame indicated by mcch-RepetitionPeriod and mcch-Offset, the second bit for #2, the third bit for #3 , the fourth bit for #6, the fifth bit for #7 and the sixth bit for #8. TDD: The first/leftmost bit defines the allocation for subframe #3 of the radio frame indicated by mcch-RepetitionPeriod and mcch-Offset, the second bit for #4, third bit for #7, fourth bit for #8, fifth bit for #9. Uplink subframes are not allocated. The last bit is not used.
attribute.statusInformation: Since L16A. Planned to be removed.
attribute.precondition: Attribute administrativeState must be set to LOCKED before modifying this attribute.

attribute.name: signallingMCS
attribute.description: Indicates the Modulation and Coding Scheme (MCS) applicable for the subframes indicated by the field sf-AllocInfo and for the first subframe of each MCH scheduling period (which may contain the MCH scheduling information provided by MAC). Value 2 corresponds with the value 2 for parameter I-MCS in TS 36.213, Table 7.1.7.1-1], and so on.
attribute.precondition: Attribute administrativeState must be set to LOCKED before modifying this attribute.

attribute.name: commonSFAlloc
attribute.description: Specifies the subframes that are reserved for MBSFN in downlink.
attribute.statusInformation: Since L16B. Replaced by attribute commonSFAllocList. Planned to be removed.
attribute.precondition: Attribute administrativeState must be set to LOCKED before modifying this attribute.

attribute.name: commonSFAllocPeriod
attribute.description: Specifies the period during which resources corresponding with field commonSFAlloc are divided between the (P)MCH that are configured for this MBSFN area. The subframe allocation patterns, as defined by commonSFAlloc, repeat continuously during this period. Value 4 corresponds to 4 radio frames, 8 corresponds to 8 radio frames and so on.
attribute.dependencies: The mchSchedulingPeriod in the MO class PmchMch must be a multiple of commonSFAllocPeriod.
attribute.precondition: Attribute administrativeState must be set to LOCKED before modifying this attribute.

attribute.name: notificationConfiguration
attribute.description: Notification configuration Note: If several MbsfnArea are activated for a cell, the notificationConfiguration of highest notificationConfigurationPriority will be used.
attribute.statusInformation: Since L16B. Planned to be removed.
attribute.precondition: Attribute administrativeState must be set to LOCKED before modifying this attribute.

attribute.name: administrativeState
attribute.description: The administrative state. Note: If this attribute is set to SHUTTING_DOWN, it will immediately go into the state LOCKED.

attribute.name: serviceAreaId
attribute.description: MBMS Service Area identities that are covered by the MBSFN area.
attribute.dependencies: One defined serviceAreaId must be configured in eNodeB to ENABLE TermPointToMmeM3. Must not be changed when MbsfnArea is unlocked. Must not be changed if system-created MO instance MbmsService exists under any PmchMch MO instance under the MbsfnArea. QCI and serviceAreaId combination can be set for at most two PmchMch under different MbsfnAreas.

attribute.name: commonSFAllocList
attribute.description: Subframes that are reserved for MBSFN in DL.
attribute.precondition: Attribute administrativeState must be set to LOCKED before modifying this attribute.

class.name: PmchMch
class.description: This MO represents configuration related to the Uu physical and transport layers for Multimedia Broadcast Multicast Service (MBMS).

attribute.name: pmchMchId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use.

attribute.name: sfAllocEnd
attribute.description: Last subframe allocated to (P)MCH within a period identified by field commonSF-AllocPeriod. If value is 0, the first subframe defined by the field commonSF-Alloc. If Autoconfiguration of LTE Broadcast Subframes is used, new values are set by system every time subframe allocation changes for (P)MCH. If value is -1, no subframe is allocated.

attribute.name: dataMcs
attribute.description: Specifies the value for parameter I-MCS in TS 36.213, Table 7.1.7.1-1, which defines the Modulation and Coding Scheme (MCS) applicable for the subframes of this (P)MCH as indicated by the field commonSF-Alloc. The MCS does however neither apply to the subframes that may carry MCCH i.e. the subframes indicated by the field sf-AllocInfo within SystemInformationBlockType13 nor for the first subframe of each MCH scheduling period (which may contain the MCH scheduling information provided by MAC).

attribute.name: mchSchedulingPeriod
attribute.description: MCH scheduling period. Used to provide MCH scheduling information at applicable lower layers (MAC). Value 8 sets 8 radio frames, 16 sets 16 radio frames and so on. Values 512 and 1024 cannot be used.
attribute.dependencies: mchSchedulingPeriod must be: - a multiple of commonSFAllocPeriod in MO class MbsfnArea. - smaller than or equal to mcchRepetitionPeriod in MO class MbsfnArea.

attribute.name: qci
attribute.description: QCIs that are supported by this (P)MCH. When Autoconfiguration of LTE Broadcast Subframes is not used, use empty sequence.
attribute.dependencies: QCI must be unique value under MbsfnArea. QCI and serviceAreaId combination can be set for at most two PmchMch under different MbsfnAreas. QCI must not be changed when MbsfnArea is unlocked. QCI must not be changed if system-created MO instance exists under any PmchMch MO instance under the MbsfnArea.
attribute.disturbances: Can affect traffic if changed. MBMS services can become inconsistent between MBSFN areas.
attribute.precondition: All MbmsService MOs under the PmchMch must be deleted. The corresponding MbsfnArea must have administrative state LOCKED.

attribute.name: syncSequenceLength
attribute.description: Synchronization sequence length used for MBMS data on the M1 interface.
attribute.dependencies: syncSequenceLength must not exceed mchSchedulingPeriod.

class.name: MbmsService
class.description: MO represents configuration related to MBMS bearer service. If Autoconfiguration of LTE Broadcast Subframes is used, this MO will be created by the system.

attribute.name: mbmsServiceId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use.

attribute.name: availabilityStatus
attribute.description: The availability status. It contains details about operationalState. This attribute is set by the application in the RBS.

attribute.name: operationalState
attribute.description: The operational state.

attribute.name: tmgiList
attribute.description: List of temporary mobile group identities. Set by system if Autoconfiguration of LTE Broadcast Subframes is used.

attribute.name: logicalChannelIdentity
attribute.description: The logical channel identity.

attribute.name: syncSequenceLength
attribute.description: The synchronization sequence length used for MBMS data on the M1 interface.
attribute.statusInformation: Since L16B. Replaced by PmchMch::syncSequenceLength. Planned to be removed.
attribute.dependencies: The syncSequenceLength must be smaller than or equal to the mchSchedulingPeriod in the MO class PmchMch.

attribute.name: createdBy
attribute.description: Whether MbmsService is created by operator or by system.

class.name: MbsfnAreaCellRelation
class.description: This managed object represents the relationship between a MBSFN Area and a EUTRAN cell.

attribute.name: mbsfnAreaCellRelationId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use.

attribute.name: mbsfnAreaCellRef
attribute.description: Reference to a related EUtranCell that supports the MBSFN Area.

attribute.name: isReservedCell
attribute.description: Defines if the related EUtranCell in MBSFN Area reserved cell or not. A Reserved Cell is a unicast cell. No data is sent in the MBSFN subframes. The Cell CSR (cell specific reference) will be sent as a normal unicast cell.

attribute.name: mbsfnAreaCellStatus
attribute.description: The MBSFN area status of the related Cell.

class.name: ReportConfigEUtraIFBestCell
class.description: This managed object contains the report configuration settings for best cell measurements on other LTE frequencies.

attribute.name: reportConfigEUtraIFBestCellId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: a3offset
attribute.description: The offset value for eventA3.

attribute.name: hysteresisA3
attribute.description: The hysteresis value for eventA3.

attribute.name: triggerQuantityA3
attribute.description: The quantity that triggers the event.

attribute.name: timeToTriggerA3
attribute.description: Time-to-trigger value for event A3. If timeToTriggerA3Rsrq is -1, this attribute is used for both RSRP and RSRQ. But if not set to -1, this attribute is used only for RSRP.

attribute.name: timeToTriggerA3Rsrq
attribute.description: Time-to-trigger value for event A3 with trigger quantity RSRQ. If set to -1, this attribute is not used for report configuration.
attribute.dependencies: Feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage must be active.

attribute.name: a3RsrqOffset
attribute.description: Offset to obtain the A3Offset for inter-frequency A3 measurement for trigger quantity RSRQ. a3OffsetRsrq = a3offset + a3RsrqOffset
attribute.dependencies: Feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage must be active.

attribute.name: hysteresisA3RsrqOffset
attribute.description: Offset to obtain the Hysteresis for inter-frequency A3 measurement for trigger quantity RSRQ. hysteresisA3Rsrq = hysteresisA3 + hysteresisA3RsrqOffset
attribute.dependencies: Feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage must be active.

class.name: ReportConfigSearch
class.description: Contains report configuration settings for search area measurements that relate to features Mobility Control at Poor Coverage and Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility (MLSTM). Corresponds to parameters needed for A2search, A1Search, A2OuterSearch and A2Critical events and QCI specific offsets to such parameters.

attribute.name: reportConfigSearchId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: a1a2SearchThresholdRsrp
attribute.description: The Reference Signal Received Power (RSRP) threshold value for events A1Search and A2Search. If Multi-Layer Service Triggered Mobility feature is enabled QCI offsets in QciProfilePredefined configuration is overridden by this feature QCI configuration.

attribute.name: a1a2SearchThresholdRsrq
attribute.description: The Reference Signal Received Quality (RSRQ) threshold value for events A1Search and A2Search. If Multi-Layer Service Triggered Mobility feature is enabled QCI offsets in QciProfilePredefined configuration is overridden by this feature QCI configuration.

attribute.name: hysteresisA1A2SearchRsrp
attribute.description: The hysteresis value for RSRP in events A1Search and A2Search measurements.

attribute.name: hysteresisA1A2SearchRsrq
attribute.description: The hysteresis value for RSRQ in events A1Search and A2Search measurements.

attribute.name: timeToTriggerA1Search
attribute.description: Time-to-trigger value for measurement in event A1Search. If timeToTriggerA1SearchRsrq is -1, this attribute is used for both RSRP and RSRQ. But if not set to -1, this attribute is used only for RSRP.

attribute.name: timeToTriggerA2Search
attribute.description: Time-to-trigger value for measurement in event A2Search. If timeToTriggerA2SearchRsrq is -1, this attribute is used for both RSRP and RSRQ. But if not set to -1, this attribute is used only for RSRP.

attribute.name: a2CriticalThresholdRsrp
attribute.description: The Reference Signal Received Power (RSRP) threshold value for event A2Critical.

attribute.name: a2CriticalThresholdRsrq
attribute.description: The Reference Signal Received Quality (RSRQ) threshold value for event A2Critical.

attribute.name: hysteresisA2CriticalRsrp
attribute.description: The hysteresis value for RSRP in event A2Critical measurement.

attribute.name: hysteresisA2CriticalRsrq
attribute.description: The hysteresis value for RSRQ in event A2Critical measurement.

attribute.name: timeToTriggerA2Critical
attribute.description: Time-to-trigger value for measurement in event A2Critical. If timeToTriggerA2CriticalRsrq is -1, this attribute is used for both RSRP and RSRQ. But if not set to -1, this attribute is used only for RSRP.

attribute.name: qciA1A2ThrOffsets
attribute.description: Parameters for adding QCI profile specific offsets to threshold values for events A1Search and A2Search used for mobility decisions. Applicable if Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility is active.

attribute.name: a2OuterSearchThrRsrpOffset
attribute.description: Offset for threshold a1a2SearchThresholdRsrp to configure RSRP threshold value for events A2OuterSearch.

attribute.name: a2OuterSearchThrRsrqOffset
attribute.description: Offset for threshold a1a2SearchThresholdRsrq to configure RSRQ threshold value for events A2OuterSearch. Note: RSRQ thresholds are configured in 0.5dB steps according to 3GPP TS36.331. Use multiples of 5 for this attribute. Other values are rounded down to the closest lower multiple of 5.

attribute.name: timeToTriggerA1SearchRsrq
attribute.description: Time-to-trigger value for measurement in event A1Search with trigger quantity RSRQ. The value -1 means that this attribute is not used for report configuration.

attribute.name: timeToTriggerA2CriticalRsrq
attribute.description: Time-to-trigger value for measurement in event A2Critical with trigger quantity RSRQ. The value -1 means that this attribute is not used for report configuration.

attribute.name: timeToTriggerA2SearchRsrq
attribute.description: Time-to-trigger value for measurement in event A2Search with trigger quantity RSRQ. The value -1 means that this attribute is not used for report configuration.

attribute.name: timeToTriggerA2OutSearch
attribute.description: Time-to-trigger value for measurement in event A2OuterSearch. If timeToTriggerA2OutSearchRsrq is -1, this attribute is used for both RSRP and RSRQ. But if not set to -1, this attribute is used only for RSRP.

attribute.name: timeToTriggerA2OutSearchRsrq
attribute.description: Time-to-trigger value for measurement in event A2OuterSearch with trigger quantity RSRQ. The value -1 means that this attribute is not used for report configuration.

attribute.name: hysteresisA2OuterSearchRsrp
attribute.description: Hysteresis value for RSRP in events A2OuterSearch measurements.

attribute.name: hysteresisA2OuterSearchRsrq
attribute.description: Hysteresis value for RSRQ in events A2OuterSearch measurements.

attribute.name: a2CriticalThrQci1RsrpOffset
attribute.description: QCI1 offset on cell level for threshold a2CriticalThresholdRsrp, RSRP threshold value for events A2Critical.

attribute.name: a2CriticalThrQci1RsrqOffset
attribute.description: QCI1 offset on cell level for threshold a2CriticalThresholdRsrq, RSRQ threshold value for events A2Critical. Note: RSRQ thresholds are configured in 0.5dB steps according to 3GPP TS36.331. Use multiples of 5 for this attribute. Other values are rounded down to the closest lower multiple of 5.

attribute.name: inhibitA2SearchConfig
attribute.description: Inhibit type of A2Search Report configuration.

attribute.name: a1a2UlSearchThreshold
attribute.description: UL-normalized SINR max threshold value for events A1 UL and A2 UL search.
attribute.dependencies: a1a2UlSearchThreshold >= a2UlCriticalThreshold

attribute.name: hysteresisA1A2UlSearch
attribute.description: Hysteresis value for UL events A1 UL search and A2 UL search measurements.

attribute.name: a2UlCriticalThreshold
attribute.description: UL-normalized SINR max threshold value for event A2 UL critical.
attribute.dependencies: a1a2UlSearchThreshold >= a2UlCriticalThreshold

attribute.name: hysteresisA2UlCritical
attribute.description: Hysteresis value for UL event A2 UL critical measurements.

attribute.name: timeToTriggerA1UlSearch
attribute.description: Time-to-trigger value for UL measurement in event A1 UL search.

attribute.name: timeToTriggerA2UlSearch
attribute.description: Time-to-trigger value for UL measurement in event A2 UL search.

attribute.name: timeToTriggerA2UlCritical
attribute.description: Time-to-trigger value for UL measurement in event A2 UL critical.

attribute.name: qciA1A2UlThrOffsets
attribute.description: Array of structure type ReportConfigParamsUlQciOffset, containing parameters for addition of QCI profile specific offsets to UL threshold values for events A1 UL and A2 UL search used for mobility decisions. Applicable if Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility is active.

attribute.name: a2CriticalOffsetPerPC
attribute.description: The high power UE specific offset for the absolute threshold. RSRP/RSRQ threshold value for event A2Critical.

class.name: SectorCarrier
class.description: This MO represents the power and frequency usage of the SectorEquipmentFunction that covers an area.

attribute.name: sectorCarrierId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: availabilityStatus
attribute.description: The availability status. It contains details about operationalState. This attribute is set by the application in the RBS.
attribute.disturbances: Change can affect traffic

attribute.name: operationalState
attribute.description: The operational state. This attribute is set by the application in the RBS.
attribute.disturbances: Change can affect traffic

attribute.name: sectorFunctionRef
attribute.description: Reference to an instance of SectorEquipmentFunction MO.

attribute.name: reservedBy
attribute.description: Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.

attribute.name: noOfRxAntennas
attribute.description: Number of antennas that SectorCarrier uses for UL transmission. When there are SectorCarriers with different number of RX antennas in the node, set the parameter explicitly to the number of RX antennas that the SectorCarrier uses. If parameter is set to 0, and optional features enabling usage of RX antennas are deactivated, then SectorCarrier uses two RX branches. If parameter is set to 0, and optional features enabling usage of RX antennas are activated, then SectorCarrier uses the maximum number of RX antennas defined by the operable features.
attribute.dependencies: Dependent on optional features that enable usage of multiple Rx antennas.
attribute.disturbances: Change can affect traffic

attribute.name: noOfTxAntennas
attribute.description: Number of antennas that SectorCarrier uses for DL transmission. When there are SectorCarriers with different number of TX antennas in the node, set the parameter explicitly to the number of TX antennas that the SectorCarrier uses. If parameter is set to 0, and optional features enabling usage of TX antennas are deactivated, then SectorCarrier uses one TX branch. If parameter is set to 0, and optional features enabling usage of TX antennas are activated, then SectorCarrier uses the maximum number of TX antennas defined by the operable features.
attribute.dependencies: Dependent on optional features that enable usage of multiple Tx antennas.
attribute.disturbances: Change can affect traffic

attribute.name: partOfSectorPower
attribute.description:
Requested part of the total power in the SectorEquipment that must be allocated for the sectorCarrier. The output power is evenly distributed over antenna connectors used for TX transmission allocated for the SectorCarrier.
When the total amount of power for each antenna connector of a SectorEquipment exceeds the limit of 100%, an alarm is generated when the cell that uses the SectorCarrier is unlocked.
To prevent the cell from transmitting, it must be locked.
attribute.statusInformation: Since L16B. Replaced by configuredMaxTxPower. Planned to be removed.
attribute.disturbances: Change may affect traffic

attribute.name: maximumTransmissionPower
attribute.description:
Maximum possible power at the antenna reference point, for all downlink channels in all TX branches used simultaneously in the SectorCarrier. -1 is used as an undefined value.
Note: Setting configuredMaxTxPower (MO SectorCarrier) has an impact on this attribute. See Radio Network Configuration user guide 11/1553-HSC 105 50/1.

attribute.name: prsEnabled
attribute.description: If true, the Positioning Reference Signal is sent from this sector carrier. 1: For indoor antennas at the same location, if the sector carriers are isolated, set prsEnabled to true for all sector carriers. Transmission of PDSCH on the PRS subframe is not scheduled. 2: For combined macro and pico sector carriers, set prsEnabled to true for the macro sector only. The other sector or sectors have prsEnabled = false. However, transmission of PDSCH is still not scheduled on the same subframe to prevent undesirable interferences. Note: To reclaim PRS subframe for PDSCH transmission, OTDOA Supl license state must be set to DISABLED.
attribute.disturbances: Change can affect traffic

attribute.name: rfBranchRxRef
attribute.description: Contains references to the RF Branches whose RF ports are to be used for RX Carrier allocations for this particular SectorCarrier. If no reference is specified Carrier allocation is based on the RF Branch MOM list (default behavior).
attribute.disturbances: Modifying this attribute requires blocking and de-blocking the cell.

attribute.name: rfBranchTxRef
attribute.description: Contains references to the RF Branches whose RF ports are to be used for TX Carrier allocations for this particular SectorCarrier. If no reference is specified Carrier allocation is based on the RF Branch MOM list (default behavior).
attribute.disturbances: Modifying this attribute requires blocking and de-blocking the cell.

attribute.name: ulForcedTimingAdvanceCommand
attribute.description: Forced additional value for Timing Advance Command in Random Access Response according to 3GPP TS 36.213.

attribute.name: noOfMutedTxAntennas
attribute.description: Number of muted Tx antennas when MIMO sleep mode is activated.

attribute.name: radioTransmitPerformanceMode
attribute.description: A desired radio transmit operating mode, which is tailored to achieve good throughput performance for a given highest modulation in downlink.

attribute.name: configuredMaxTxPower
attribute.description:
Maximum output power to be used in a SectorCarrier. The output power is evenly distributed over antenna connectors used for TX transmission allocated for the SectorCarrier.
Value 0 must not be used. To prevent the cell from transmitting, it must be locked.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic
attribute.precondition: Attribute can be set only when cell is locked.

attribute.name: txPowerPersistentLock
attribute.description:
Indicates if attribute configuredMaxTxPower is locked or not. When true, attribute configuredMaxTxPower cannot be changed and parent MO cannot be deleted.
Note: This attribute is only intended to be used on mRBS and mRRU.
attribute.precondition: Once set to true there is no possibility to change the value back to false unless a node re-integration is performed.

attribute.name: dlCalibrationData
attribute.description: Downlink antenna calibration information.

attribute.name: pimcFunctionReference
attribute.description: Reference to PimCancellationFunction MO to indicate PIM cancellation function SectorCarrier is participating in. The value is the LDN of refered PimCancellationFunction MO.
attribute.statusInformation: Since 17.Q2. Replaced by PimCancellationConfig::pimCancellationFunctionRef. Planned to be removed.

attribute.name: ulPimCancellationMode
attribute.description: PIM cancellation mode on UL carriers.
attribute.statusInformation: Since 17.Q2. Replaced by PimCancellationConfig::ulPimCancellationMode. Planned to be removed.

attribute.name: dlPimCandidate
attribute.description: Include DL carriers for PIM calculation.
attribute.statusInformation: Since 17.Q2. Replaced by PimCancellationConfig::dlPimCandidate. Planned to be removed.

attribute.name: zzzTemporary1
attribute.description: Temporary attribute intended for temporary solution. Usage depends on the installed software. Only set this attribute when it corresponds to a desired functionality and leave all other temporary attributes set to default values. Information in the descriptions about the used attributes can be overridden by information in CPI documents. Note that a later release can use another attribute or completely remove the functionality. Changes are documented in the NIR.

attribute.name: microSleepTxActivation
attribute.description: Micro Sleep Tx functions in baseband are activated at cell unlock.

attribute.name: virtualSector
attribute.description: Whether or not sector carrier is virtual sector, modelled by MO SectorCarrier. Sector carriers can have different sector carrier shapes by using custom channel beamforming weights, so called "virtual sector". Virtual sector cannot carrier aggregate with other virtual sectors in same sector.
attribute.dependencies: If true, then virtualComChBeamfrmWtsAmplitude must be valid.

attribute.name: virtualComChBeamfrmWtsAmplitude
attribute.description: Array of eight amplitudes for common channel beamforming weights of virtual sector. One of eight amplitudes must be non-zero for beamforming weights to take effect. Actual value = Set value / 100.
attribute.disturbances: Changed coverage can affect traffic.

attribute.name: virtualComChBeamfrmWtsPhase
attribute.description: Array of eight phases for common channel beamforming weights of virtual sector.
attribute.disturbances: Changed coverage can affect traffic.

attribute.name: digitalTilt
attribute.description: Digitally-controlled tilt through beamforming. Positive value gives downwards tilt and negative value gives upwards tilt. Only MACRO, MACRO_2LOBE, MACRO_NARROW and MACRO_WIDE sector shapes are affected. Select a value supported by installed radio equipment. Refer to CPI for installed radio equipment for supported values.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect if radio equipment supports AAS functionality.

attribute.name: sectorShape
attribute.description: Shape of sector carrier. Select a value supported by installed radio equipment. Refer to CPI for installed radio equipment for supported values.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect if radio equipment supports AAS functionality.

attribute.name: ulCalibrationData
attribute.description: UL antenna calibration information.

class.name: UlCompGroup
class.description: Defines a set of sectorCarriers. Uplink Coordinated multi-point reception of antenna signals is possible only between antenna signals from sectorCarriers within the same set of sectorCarriers.

attribute.name: ulCompGroupId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: sectorCarrierRef
attribute.description: Defines a set of sectorCarriers. Uplink Coordinated multi-point reception of antenna signals is possible only between antenna signals from sectorCarriers within the same set of sectorCarriers. There shall be at least one sectorCarrier per UlCompGroup.

attribute.name: administrativeState
attribute.description: The administrative state. Note: If this attribute is set to SHUTTING_DOWN, it will immediately go into the state LOCKED.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute to LOCKED or SHUTTINGDOWN disables UL CoMP.

attribute.name: availabilityStatus
attribute.description: The availability status. It contains details about operationalState. This attribute is set by the application in the RBS.

attribute.name: operationalState
attribute.description: The operational state. This attribute is set by the application in the RBS.

class.name: ReportConfigInterRatLb
class.description: The MO contains the report configuration settings for UE measurements that are initiated for Inter-RAT load balancing actions.

attribute.name: reportConfigInterRatLbId
attribute.description: Value component of the RDN

attribute.name: utranB1ThresholdRscp
attribute.description: RSCP threshold value for the event B1 measurement for Load based IRAT handover to UTRAN.
attribute.dependencies: Only used when UeMeasControl::measQuantityUtraFDD is set to RSCP.

attribute.name: utranHysteresisB1
attribute.description: Hysteresis value for the event B1 measurement

attribute.name: utranB1ThresholdEcNo
attribute.description: Ratio of energy per modulation bit to noise spectral density in the ThresholdUTRA, threshold value for event B1. Not applicable for UTRA TDD.
attribute.dependencies: Only used when UeMeasControl::measQuantityUtraFDD is set to ECNO.

class.name: ExternalCdma20001xRttCell
class.description: The MO represents a CDMA2000 1xRTT cell.

attribute.name: externalCdma20001xRttCellId
attribute.description: Value component of the RDN

attribute.name: pnOffset
attribute.description: CDMA physical cell identity

attribute.name: reservedBy
attribute.description: List of MO instances that reserve this MO instance
attribute.dependencies: The MO cannot be deleted if it is reserved.

attribute.name: acBarring1xRttForMoDataPresent
attribute.description: Presence indication in SIB8 of Information Element acBarring1xRttMoData

attribute.name: mscIdentifier
attribute.description: MSC identity in CDMA 1xRTT network If this 1xRTT cell is referred by EUtranCellFDD or EUtranCellTDD, this identifier will be used by eNodeB for tunneling of 1xRTT signaling messages towards this MSC. It has to be configured for LTE CSFB to 1xRTT features since it is used to fill a field in S1AP message sent to MME.

attribute.name: sid
attribute.description: System unique identifier (15bits) This attribute is used along with the NID as a pair to control when the UE should register or reregister with the CDMA2000 1xRTT network. SID=0 is reserved. It is broadcast on SIB8. It is also used with CellId, SectorNumber and NID for the 1xRTT cell global identity.

attribute.name: nid
attribute.description: Network unique identifier (16 bits) within a system used along with the SID as a pair to control when the UE should register or reregister with the CDMA2000 1xRTT network. NID=0 and NID=65535 are reserved.

attribute.name: cellIdentifier
attribute.description: Cell identifier If a 1xRTT cell is referred by EUtranCellFDD or EUtranCellTDD, this cell/sector attribute in conjunction with marketId and switchNumber shall be used to set the IE CDMA2000 Sector ID in Uplink S1 CDMA2000 tunneling message.

attribute.name: acBarring1xRttMoData
attribute.description: Access Barring parameters for CDMA2000 1xRTT capable UE originating signaling The information is broadcast in SIB8. This is controlled by the licensing MO CsfbTo1xRtt and acBarring1xRttForMoDataPresent

attribute.name: csfbRegParams1xRttMoData
attribute.description: Information for preregistration to 1xRTT system The information is broadcast in SIB8. This information, together with the information in mobilityParams1xRttMoData, must be used to build IE in RRC messages: CSFBParametersResponseCDMA2000 and HandoverFromEUTRAPreparationRequest. This is controlled by the licensing MO CsfbTo1xRtt.

attribute.name: mobilityParams1xRttMoData
attribute.description: Information for registration/reregistration to 1xRTT system The information, together with the information in csfbRegParams1xRttMoData, is used to build the IE in RRC messages: CSFBParametersResponseCDMA2000 and HandoverFromEUTRAPreparationRequest. This is controlled by the licensing MO CsfbTo1xRtt.

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use

attribute.name: srvccCapability
attribute.description: Describes the SRVCC capability of the external cell.

class.name: Cdma20001xRttBandRelation
class.description: The MO represents a mobility relation between an EUtranCellFDD or an EUtranCellTDD and a Cdma20001xRTTFreqBand. It contains parameters that are specific for this relation.

attribute.name: cdma2000FreqBandRef
attribute.description: Reference to the CDMA2000 frequency band MO, Cdma2000FreqBand

attribute.name: cdma20001xRttBandRelationId
attribute.description: Value component of the RDN

attribute.name: cellReselectionPriority
attribute.description: Absolute priority of the RAT (0 means: lowest priority)

attribute.name: threshXHigh1xRtt
attribute.description:
Threshold used in reselection towards a high priority CDMA2000 1xRTT band class, expressed as an unsigned binary number equal to FLOOR ([-2 x 10 x log10 Ec/Io]) in units of 0.5 dB
If sNonServingCell > threshXHigh1xRtt, reselection is considered towards the band class with higher priority. The condition must be valid during the period defined by attribute tReselectionCdma1xRtt.
sNonServingCell is the RX-level value of a neighboring cell.

attribute.name: threshXLow1xRtt
attribute.description:
Threshold used in reselection towards a low priority CDMA2000 1xRTT band class expressed as an unsigned binary number equal to FLOOR ([-2 x 10 x log10 Ec/Io]) in units of 0.5 db.
If sServingCell < threshServingLow and sNeighbor > threshXLow (see corresponding attribute), reselection towards this lower prioritized band class is considered. The condition must be valid during the period defined by attribute tReselectionCdma1xRtt.
sServingCell is the RX level value of the serving cell and sNeighborCell is the RX level value of a neighbor frequency.

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use

class.name: CarrierAggregationFunction
class.description: Contains parameters and constraints for the Carrier Aggregation function

attribute.name: caUsageLimit
attribute.description: The value configures the number of SCell connections which can be in use for carrier aggregation. A secondary cell (SCell) costs in memory the same as a primary cell (PCell) for each UE. It is preferred to avoid limiting SCell connections with caUsageLimit, and use caPreemptionThreshold instead.

attribute.name: caPreemptionThreshold
attribute.description: Configures the resource consumption margin in percentage, beyond which Secondary Cells shall not be configured.

attribute.name: sCellActDeactDataThres
attribute.description:
One or more SCells can be activated if minimum time needed to transmit all bits in all priority queues of UE is higher than sCellActDeactDataThres.
When deciding the activation of one SCell, minimum time needed to transmit all bits is calculated as the number of bits in all priority queues, divided by the number of bits that can be transmitted in one TTI by all active serving cells prior to activation decision. This is computed as though the UE is given all resources in those cells. If the condition for activating one SCell is satisfied, a second SCell is also considered for activation but the minimum time needed to transmit all bits is now calculated by considering the added capacity of the first new SCell that is already considered for activation.
For FDD, the unit "number of DL subframes" is equivalent to ms, but for TDD UL/DL subframe configuration 1, there are 6 DL subframes in 10ms, and for UL/DL subframe configuration 2, there are 8 DL subframes in 10ms.
"-1" means the data-triggered activation condition is always satisfied even with no data in the buffer, and also that the data-triggered deactivation condition is never satisfied.
attribute.dependencies: sCellActDeactDataThresHyst <= sCellActDeactDataThres when sCellActDeactDataThres is not equal to -1

attribute.name: sCellActDeactDataThresHyst
attribute.description:
If the minimum time needed to transmit all bits in all priority queues of a UE is less than or equal to sCellActDeactDataThres minus sCellActDeactDataThresHyst, then deactivation of one component carrier is considered.
Minimum time needed to transmit all bits is calculated as number of bits in all priority queues, divided by the number of bits that can be transmitted in one TTI by all active serving cells after deactivation decision. This is computed as though the UE is given all resources in those cells.
For FDD, the unit "number of DL subframes" is equivalent to ms, but for TDD UL/DL subframe configuration 1, there are 6 DL subframes in 10ms, and for UL/DL subframe configuration 2, there are 8 DL subframes in 10ms.
If sCellActDeactDataThres is set to "-1", the data-triggered deactivation condition is never satisfied and the value of sCellActDeactDataThresHyst is ignored.
attribute.dependencies: sCellActDeactDataThresHyst <= sCellActDeactDataThres when sCellActDeactDataThres is not equal to -1

attribute.name: sCellScheduleSinrThres
attribute.description: No data is scheduled on SCell if wideband SINR is lower than sCellScheduleSinrThres. If SINR remains below threshold, SCell is deactivated when sCellDeactOutOfCoverageTimer expired.

attribute.name: sCellActDeactProhibitTimer
attribute.description: Activation/deactivation prohibit timer. No new activation/deactivation of an SCell is allowed while this timer is running.
attribute.statusInformation: Since L16B. Replaced by sCellActProhibitTimer and sCellDeactProhibitTimer. Planned to be removed.

attribute.name: waitForCaOpportunity
attribute.description:
Controls the length of time that elapses until a UE is considered once again for SCell configuration after the eNB was not able to configure this UE with a suitable Scell.
"-1" means wait forever.
Changed value may take effect related to the next SCell configuration during the ongoing connection.
attribute.disturbances: Extreme settings can turn off CA for the eNB.

attribute.name: waitForBetterSCellRep
attribute.description:
Controls the length of time a UE searches for SCells on a particular frequency, or set of frequencies based on measurements when it is in poor SCell coverage.
"-1" means wait forever.
Changed value can take effect related to the next SCell configuration during the ongoing connection.

attribute.name: carrierAggregationFunctionId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: waitForAdditionalSCellOpportunity
attribute.description:
Controls the length of time that elapses until a UE is reconsidered for additional SCell configuration after the eNB was unable to configure this UE with more than one SCell.
"-1" means wait forever.
Changed value can take effect related to the next SCell configuration during the ongoing connection.

attribute.name: caRateAdjustCoeff
attribute.description: Used to adjust factor of CC rate for CA UEs, which is used in scheduler's proportional fairness algorithm. A smaller value gives CA UE a greater advantage over non-CA UE. Value 0 sets rate as 0 and this is for testing purpose only; values 1 - 4 set the rate as fraction of the cell rate in increased order; value 5 sets cell based rate; values 6 - 9 set the rate as cell rate plus rate influence from other CCs in increased order; value 10 sets the rate as aggregated rate of all CCs .

attribute.name: sCellActDeactUlDataThresh
attribute.description: If the minimum time needed to transmit all bits in all priority queues in UL of a UE is higher than sCellActDeactUlDataThresh, activation of one or more secondary cells is considered.
attribute.dependencies: sCellActDeactUlDataThreshHyst =< sCellActDeactUlDataThresh

attribute.name: sCellActDeactUlDataThreshHyst
attribute.description: If minimum time needed to transmit all bits in all priority queues in UL of a UE is less than sCellActDeactUlDataThresh minus sCellActDeactUlDataThreshHyst, deactivation of one CC is considered.
attribute.dependencies: sCellActDeactUlDataThreshHyst =< sCellActDeactUlDataThresh

attribute.name: sCellScheduleUlPathlossThresh
attribute.description: No data is scheduled on the SCell if UL pathloss is higher than sCellScheduleUlPathlossThresh. If the pathloss stays above the threshold, the SCell is eventually deactivated.
attribute.statusInformation: Since L16B. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.

attribute.name: pdcchEnhancedLaForVolte
attribute.description: Enables CA when VoIP and enhanced PDCCH Link Adaptation on FDD PCell are both active. Not used for TDD PCells.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect when Carrier Aggregation FAJ 121 3046 and Enhanced PDCCH Link Adaptation FAJ 121 3051 are active, and a VoIP bearer exists for a UE.
attribute.takesEffect: At the next initial SCell selection during the ongoing connection

attribute.name: sCellSelectionMode
attribute.description: Selects the behavior of selecting SCell candidates beyond the first candidate. Warning: There is a risk when using UN_ACK_SIMULTANEOUS_SCELL_SELECTION that the UE may not report a bad SCell.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect when Dynamic SCell Selection for Carrier Aggregation FAJ 121 3063 and 3CC DL Carrier Aggregation Extension FAJ 121 3084 are active.

attribute.name: laaSCellActDeactDataThres
attribute.description:
If minimum time to transmit all bits is higher than laaSCellActDeactDataThres, activation of one or more secondary cells is considered.
Minimum time to transmit all bits is calculated as number of bits in all priority queues, divided by number of bits transmitted in one TTI by all active serving cells. Computed as if UE has all resources in those cells.
For FDD, the unit "number of DL subframes" is equivalent to ms, but for TDD UL/DL subframe configuration 1, there are 6 DL subframes in 10ms, and for UL/DL subframe configuration 2, there are 8 DL subframes in 10ms.
Only used if LAA is configured in RBS.
attribute.statusInformation: Since 17.Q3. Replaced by UnlicensedAccessFunction::laaSCellActDeactDataThres. Planned to be removed.
attribute.dependencies: laaSCellActDeactDataThresHyst <= laaSCellActDeactDataThres

attribute.name: laaSCellActDeactDataThresHyst
attribute.description:
If minimum time to transmit all bits is less than laaSCellActDeactDataThres minus laaSCellActDeactDataThresHyst, then deactivation of one component carrier is considered.
Minimum time to transmit all bits is calculated as number of bits in all priority queues, divided by number of bits transmitted in one TTI by all active serving cells after deactivation decision. Computed as if UE has all resources in those cells.
For FDD, the unit "number of DL subframes" is equivalent to ms.
Only used if LAA is configured in RBS.
attribute.statusInformation: Since 17.Q3. Replaced by UnlicensedAccessFunction::laaSCellActDeactDataThresHyst. Planned to be removed.
attribute.dependencies: laaSCellActDeactDataThresHyst <= laaSCellActDeactDataThres

attribute.name: laaSCellActDeactProhibitTimer
attribute.description:
Activation/deactivation prohibit timer. No new activation/deactivation of an LAA SCell is allowed while this timer is running.
Only used if LAA is configured in RBS.
attribute.statusInformation: Since 17.Q1. Replaced by laaSCellActProhibitTimer and laaSCellDeactProhibitTimer. Planned to be removed.

attribute.name: laaSCellScheduleSinrThres
attribute.description:
No data is scheduled on LAA SCell if wideband SINR is lower than laaSCellScheduleSinrThres. If SINR stays below threshold, LAA SCell eventually becomes deactivated.
Only used if LAA is configured in RBS.
attribute.statusInformation: Since 17.Q1. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.

attribute.name: sCellActProhibitTimer
attribute.description: Activation prohibit timer. No new SCell activation is allowed while this timer is running.

attribute.name: sCellDeactProhibitTimer
attribute.description: Deactivation prohibit timer. No new SCell deactivation is allowed while this timer is running.

attribute.name: sCellDeactOutOfCoverageTimer
attribute.description:
SCell is deactivated if: - wideband DL SINR remains below sCellScheduleSinrThres, or - no Channel State Information is received by the eNB for a duration of sCellDeactOutOfCoverageTimer.
Deactivation can be deferred, for example by sCellDeactProhibitTimer.
"-1" means the SCell is not deactivated due to the SINR condition.

attribute.name: sCellDeactDelayTimer
attribute.description: One SCell is deactivated if minimum time needed to transmit all bits in all priority queues of a UE is less than or equal to sCellActDeactDataThres minus sCellActDeactDataThresHyst for a duration of sCellDeactDelayTimer.
attribute.dependencies: sCellActDeactDataThresHyst <= sCellActDeactDataThres

If effective bandwidth is not changed, tie-breaking rule is governed by fourLayerMimoPreferred. attribute.name: selectionPolicyUlWeighting
