attribute.name: hysteresis
attribute.description: The hysteresis value for the event B1 and event B2, threshold2, measurement.

attribute.name: timeToTrigger
attribute.description: The time to trigger value for the event B1 or B2 measurement.

class.name: ReportConfigB2Cdma20001xRtt
class.description: This managed object contains report configuration settings for the B2 event for CDMA2000 1xRTT measurements, used when searching for a suitable target cell when SRVCC is triggered for the UE. The B2 event is used to detect when a CDMA2000 1xRTT cell becomes better than threshold2, and serving cell becomes worse than threshold1. The actual threshold values used can be adjusted by frequency relation related offsets if the feature Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility (MLSTM) is enabled.

attribute.name: reportConfigB2Cdma20001xRttId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: b2Threshold1Rsrp
attribute.description: The Reference Signal Received Power (RSRP) threshold1 value for eventB2.
attribute.dependencies: Only used if triggerQuantityB2 is set to RSRP.

attribute.name: b2Threshold1Rsrq
attribute.description: The Reference Signal Received Quality (RSRQ) threshold1 value for eventB2.
attribute.dependencies: Only used if triggerQuantityB2 is set to RSRQ.

attribute.name: b2Threshold2Cdma20001xRtt
attribute.description: The Signal Quality in the thresholdCDMA2000, threshold2 value for eventB2.

attribute.name: hysteresisB2
attribute.description: The hysteresis value for the event B2 measurement.

attribute.name: timeToTriggerB2
attribute.description: Time-to-trigger value for event B2 measurements. If timeToTriggerB2Rsrq is -1, this attribute is used for both RSRP and RSRQ. But if not set to -1, this attribute is used only for RSRP.

attribute.name: triggerQuantityB2
attribute.description: The quantity for threshold1 that is sent to the UE, and is used together with threshold2 to trigger the eventB2.

attribute.name: timeToTriggerB2Rsrq
attribute.description: Time-to-trigger value for event B2 with trigger quantity RSRQ. If set to -1, this attribute is not used for report configuration.
attribute.dependencies: Feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage must be active.

attribute.name: hysteresisB2RsrqOffset
attribute.description: Offset to obtain the Hysteresis for B2 measurement for trigger quantity RSRQ. hysteresisB2Rsrq = hysteresisB2 + hysteresisB2RsrqOffset
attribute.dependencies: Feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage must be active.

class.name: PreschedulingProfile
class.description: Contains prescheduling profiles, prescheduling parameters, to map towards the different QCIs. The RDN values for this MO type is "initial".

attribute.name: preschedulingProfileId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: preschedulingPeriod
attribute.description: Period in ms lapsed between granted prescheduling instances.

attribute.name: preschedulingDataSize
attribute.description: Granted data size during prescheduling period.

attribute.name: preschedulingDuration
attribute.description: Prescheduling is stopped if there are no UL transmissions during this time.

class.name: MimoSleepFunction
class.description: Contains all MIMO sleep mode function configuration parameters of the in the cell.

attribute.name: mimoSleepFunctionId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: sleepMode
attribute.description: MIMO sleep mode status for the cell. Value "OFF" disables both detection and switching support. Value "DETECTION" enables detection-only mode. No switching is triggered. Values "SOFT_SWITCH", "SWITCH", "ADVANCED_SWITCH" enable detection and automatic switching.
attribute.dependencies: ADVANCED_SWITCH cannot be set if sleepPowerControl is set to USE_MAX_POWER.
attribute.disturbances: Activating sleep mode can impact traffic depending on how associated thresholds are configured.

attribute.name: sleepState
attribute.description: If MIMO sleep mode takes effect and is activated. Energy saving mode starts.

attribute.name: sleepStartTime
attribute.description: RBS daily start time (UTC time) to perform antenna muting detection or switching. Format in ASCII-code: hh:mm hh = 00-23 mm = 00-59

attribute.name: sleepEndTime
attribute.description: RBS daily end time (UTC time) to stop antenna muting detection or switching. Format in ASCII-code: hh:mm hh = 00-23 mm = 00-59

attribute.name: switchDownMonitorDurTimer
attribute.description: MIMO sleep detection duration period to enter MIMO sleep state.

attribute.name: switchDownPrbThreshold
attribute.description: Maximum percentage of DL PRB usage allowed during MIMO sleep detection period to enter MIMO sleep state.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: switchDownRrcConnThreshold
attribute.description: Maximum number of user connections allowed during MIMO sleep detection period to enter MIMO sleep state.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: switchUpMonitorDurTimer
attribute.description: MIMO sleep detection duration period to exit MIMO sleep state.

attribute.name: switchUpPrbThreshold
attribute.description: Minimum percentage of DL PRB usage required during MIMO sleep detection period to exit MIMO sleep state.
attribute.dependencies: switchUpPrbThreshold >= switchDownPrbThreshold
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: switchUpRrcConnThreshold
attribute.description: Minimum number of user connections required during MIMO sleep detection period to exit MIMO sleep state.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: sleepPowerControl
attribute.description: Power allocation method on the transmit branches during MIMO sleep.
attribute.dependencies: USE_MAX_POWER cannot be set if sleepMode is set to ADVANCED_SWITCH.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

class.name: NonPlannedPciDrxProfile
class.description:
Contains DRX profiles, DRX parameters, to map with non-planned PCI, CSG cell and Hybrid CSG cell CGI reading.
RDN for this MO type is NonPlannedPciDrxProfile=1.

attribute.name: nonPlannedPciDrxProfileId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: nonPlannedPciDrxInactivityTimer
attribute.description: The number of consecutive PDCCH subframes after successfully decoding a PDCCH that indicates an initial UL or DL user data transmission for this UE. Attribute is only used to read CGI for Non-planned PCI, CSG cell or Hybrid CSG cell. TS36.331 ch. 6.3.2, RRC parameter drx-InactivityTimer.

attribute.name: nonPlannedPciLongDrxCycle
attribute.description: Value longDrxCycle indicates the number of subframes. Attribute is only used to read CGI for Non-planned PCI, CSG cell or Hybrid CSG cell.

attribute.name: nonPlannedPciOnDurationTimer
attribute.description: The number of consecutive PDCCH subframes at DRX Cycle initialization. Attribute is only used to read CGI for Non-planned PCI, CSG cell or Hybrid CSG cell. TS36.331 ch. 6.3.2, RRC parameter onDurationTimer.

class.name: PmUlInterferenceReport
class.description: Contains RF branch information used for the feature Uplink Interference Reporting. Created when the feature license is activated.

attribute.name: pmUlInterferenceReportId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: rfBranchRxRef
attribute.description: Reference to the instance of RfBranch MO used for the feature Uplink Interference Reporting.

class.name: ReportConfigA5DlComp
class.description:
This MO contains report configuration settings for the A5 event measurements that assist Downlink Coordinated Multi-Point. The A5 event is used to detect when serving cell becomes worse than threshold1, and neighbor cell becomes better than threshold2.
The RDN of this MO is ReportConfigA5DlComp=1.

attribute.name: reportConfigA5DlCompId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

class.name: DlComp
class.description:
This MO contains configuration settings for Downlink Coordinated Multi-Point.
The RDN of this MO is DlComp=1.

attribute.name: dlCompId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

class.name: IdleModePrioAtRelease
class.description: Contains distribution model data for the Pre-Distribution At Release feature that controls the priority of the frequencies in IdleModeMobilityControlInfo in the RRC Connection Release message.

attribute.name: idleModePrioAtReleaseId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: reservedBy
attribute.description: Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.

attribute.name: lowLoadThreshold
attribute.description: Threshold value for when the distribution model at low load is used.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: lowMediumLoadThreshold
attribute.description: Threshold value for when the distribution model at low-medium load is used.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: mediumLoadThreshold
attribute.description: Threshold value for when the distribution model at medium load is used.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: mediumHighLoadThreshold
attribute.description: Threshold value for when the distribution model at medium-high load is used.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: highLoadThreshold
attribute.description: Threshold value for when the distribution model at high load is used.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: lowLoadDistributionInfo
attribute.description: Contains the distribution models used at low load level in a cell.

attribute.name: lowMediumLoadDistributionInfo
attribute.description: Contains the distribution models used at low-medium load level in a cell.

attribute.name: mediumLoadDistributionInfo
attribute.description: Contains the distribution models used at medium load level in a cell.

attribute.name: mediumHighLoadDistributionInfo
attribute.description: Contains the distribution models used at medium-high load level in a cell.

attribute.name: highLoadDistributionInfo
attribute.description: Contains the distribution models used at high load level in a cell.

class.name: ImeisvProfile
class.description: Contains UE IMEISV configuration used for feature Differentiated UE Handling. Instances of this class are created on demand by the operator. The instances can be created and configured independent of the serviceState for DifferentiatedUeHandling. But the IMEISV profiles cannot be used unless the service state is OPERABLE.

attribute.name: listOfTacSvSns
attribute.description: List of quintuples {tac, minSv, maxSv, minSn, maxSn} that are configured with similar "special" handling needs.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: imeisvProfileId
attribute.description: Value component of the RDN

attribute.name: listOfFeaturesToTurnOff
attribute.description: List of features to be turned off for the list of quintuples {tac, minSv, maxSv, minSn, maxSn} specified in listOfTacSvSns
attribute.dependencies: listOfFeaturesToTurnOff and listOfFeaturesToTurnOn must be disjoint sets
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: listOfFeaturesToTurnOn
attribute.description: List of features to be turned on for the list of quintuples {tac, minSv, maxSv, minSn, maxSn} specified in listOfTacSvSns
attribute.dependencies: listOfFeaturesToTurnOff and listOfFeaturesToTurnOn must be disjoint sets
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: voiceDrxProfileRef
attribute.description: Points out the DRX profile associated with this IMEISV profile, used for UEs with voice bearers.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: nonVoiceDrxProfileRef
attribute.description: Points out the DRX profile associated with this IMEISV profile, used for UEs without voice bearers.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: elcPreHeatingLength
attribute.description: UE-dependent parameter. Defines necessary number of subframes with available CRS before a DRX onDuration. Allows the operator to configure UE behavior for each IMEISV. Only applicable when the feature Ericsson Lean Carrier is enabled.
attribute.disturbances: Can affect traffic. If incorrectly set, RSRP measurement performed by the UE can become corrupt and cause degraded NW performance.

attribute.name: elcPostHeatingLength
attribute.description: UE-dependent parameter. Defines necessary number of subframes with available CRS after a DRX onDuration. Allows the operator to configure UE behavior for each IMEISV. Only applicable when the feature Ericsson Lean Carrier is enabled.
attribute.disturbances: Can affect traffic. If incorrectly set, RSRP measurement performed by the UE can become corrupt and cause degraded NW performance.

attribute.name: elc320msDrxEnabled
attribute.description: If set to true, 320ms long DRX cycle is configured to ELC UE.
attribute.dependencies: Only relevant if license Ericsson Lean Carrier is present and feature is active.

class.name: ImeisvTable
class.description:
Contains eNB specific configuration used for feature Differentiated UE Handling.
The RDN of this MO is ImeisvTable=1.

attribute.name: imeisvTableId
attribute.description: Value component of the RDN

attribute.name: listOfFeaturesDefaultOff
attribute.description: List of features that are considered as "Default OFF" in the eNB. Features in the list are possible to turn ON per IMEISV. A feature present in the list is ON for all UEs if the feature Differentiated UE Handling is INOPERABLE. If the feature Differentiated UE Handling is OPERABLE, a feature present in the list is ON for UEs for which: - the UE's IMEISV is present in some ImeisvProfile AND - the feature is explicitly configured for this ImeisvProfile in attribute listOfFeaturesToTurnOn For all other UEs the feature is OFF.
attribute.dependencies: listOfFeaturesDefaultOff and listOfFeaturesDefaultOn must be disjoint sets
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: listOfFeaturesDefaultOn
attribute.description: List of features that are considered as "Default ON" in the eNB. Features in the list are possible to turn OFF per IMEISV. If the feature Differentiated UE Handling is OPERABLE, a feature present in the list is OFF for UEs for which: - the UE's IMEISV is present in some ImeisvProfile AND - the feature is explicitly configured for this ImeisvProfile in attribute listOfFeaturesToTurnOff For all other UEs the feature is ON.
attribute.dependencies: listOfFeaturesDefaultOff and listOfFeaturesDefaultOn must be disjoint sets
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

class.name: CellSleepFunction
class.description: Contains configuration parameters for function Cell Sleep Mode. The RDN of this MO is CellSleepFunction=1.

attribute.name: cellSleepFunctionId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: sleepMode
attribute.description: Cell sleep mode status for the cell.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute to ACTIVATED allows the cell to enter sleep state when sleep criteria is met when within the sleepStartTime and sleepEndTime interval.

attribute.name: sleepState
attribute.description: Indicates if Cell Sleep Mode takes effect. The cell is deactivated. Energy saving mode starts.

attribute.name: sleepStartTime
attribute.description: RBS daily start time (UTC time) to perform cell sleep detection or switching. Format in ASCII-code: HH:MM where HH is in range [00..23] and MM is in range [00..59].

attribute.name: sleepEndTime
attribute.description: RBS daily end time (UTC time) to stop cell sleep detection or switching. Format in ASCII-code: HH:MM where HH is in range [00..23] and MM is in range [00..59].

attribute.name: capCellSleepMonitorDurTimer
attribute.description: Minimum duration for this cell to satisfy the configured load thresholds before entering sleep state. Used in the Cell Sleep Mode feature.

attribute.name: capCellDlPrbSleepThreshold
attribute.description: DL PRB Usage percentage threshold. The capacity cell must be below this to enter sleep state.
attribute.disturbances: Low values can cause cells with traffic to go into sleep mode.

attribute.name: capCellRrcConnSleepThreshold
attribute.description: Number of active RRC connections. The capacity cell must be below this to enter sleep state.
attribute.disturbances: Low values can cause cells with traffic to go into sleep mode.

attribute.name: covCellWakeUpMonitorDurTimer
attribute.description: Minimum duration for coverage cell to satisfy the configured load thresholds before the capacity cell can wake-up. Used in feature Cell sleep mode.

attribute.name: covCellDlPrbWakeUpThreshold
attribute.description: DL PRB usage percentage threshold. At least one of the coverage cells must exceed this threshold to wake-up the capacity cell.
attribute.disturbances: High values can cause cells not to wake up from sleep mode.

attribute.name: covCellRrcConnWakeUpThreshold
attribute.description: Active RRC connections threshold. At least one of the coverage cells must exceed this number of active RRC connections to wake-up this capacity cell.
attribute.disturbances: High values can cause cells not to wake up from sleep mode.

attribute.name: coverageCellDiscovery
attribute.description:
Indicates if automatic coverage cells detection is enabled.
If true, EUtranCellRelations with sleepModeCovCellCandidate=AUTO are evaluated as coverage cell for sleep mode support. EUtranCellRelations found applicable as coverage cells have sleepModeCoverageCell=true. EUtranCellRelations with sleepModeCovCellCandidate =ALLOWED are always evaluated.
If false, only EUtranCellRelations with sleepModeCovCellCandidate =ALLOWED are included as coverage cells for sleep mode support.

attribute.name: capCellMobReasNotSleepThr
attribute.description: Threshold value for number of incoming X2 inter-frequency handovers with cause "Handover Desirable for Radio Reasons" from neighbor cells with coverage frequency. If incoming X2 inter-frequency handovers exceeds threshold, it is considered related capacity cell is providing basic coverage support and entering sleep state is prevented.

attribute.name: capCellSleepProhibitInterval
attribute.description: Time interval when sleep state is prohibited for capacity cell. If 0, prohibition is disabled for related cell. When related cell is in prohibition state, only value 0 can be set.

attribute.name: sleepProhibitStartTime
attribute.description: Start time for sleep state prohibition. Format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS. If empty, related capacity cell is not prohibited from entering sleep state. Otherwise, sleep state is prohibited till capCellSleepProhibitInterval expires or prohibition is disabled.

attribute.name: isCleanupHitRateTable
attribute.description: Indicates if hit rate table is cleaned up when related capacity cell wakes up due to suspected coverage hole and automatic coverage cell discovery is enabled.

attribute.name: covCellUeLostWakeUpThr
attribute.description: Difference threshold for UE Lost rate between normal and sleep statistics. If threshold is exceeded coverage cell wakes up all capacity cells. Value 100 means monitoring for UE Lost is disabled.

attribute.name: covCellRrcReestWakeUpThr
attribute.description: Difference threshold for RRC Connection Re-establishment rate between normal and sleep statistics. If threshold is exceeded coverage cell wakes up all capacity cells. Value 100 means monitoring for RRC Connection Re-establishment is disabled.

attribute.name: covCellUeCtxtRelMin
attribute.description: Minimum required samples of UE Context Release to calculate UE Lost rate for normal and sleep statistics.

attribute.name: covCellRrcConnEstAttMin
attribute.description: Minimum required samples of RRC Connection Establishment Attempt to calculate RRC Connection Re-establishment rate for normal and sleep statistics.

attribute.name: covCellLatestStatsAdaRatio
attribute.description: Ratio indicating weight of latest data for normal statistics calculation.

attribute.name: isAllowedMsmOnCovCell
attribute.description: Defines if MIMO sleep with "SWITCH" or "SOFT_SWITCH" mode is allowed in the coverage cell. The "ADVANCED_SWITCH" mode is not dependent on this attribute.

attribute.name: wakeUpLastHoTime
attribute.description: Maximum time for last handover attempt before eNodeB wakes up capacity cells.

attribute.name: wakeUpWaitTimer
attribute.description: Time before eNodeB wakes up remaining capacity cells. Value 0 disables wake-up attempt.

class.name: CellPortion
class.description: This MO represents the area within a Cell, which can be used for feature, e.g. UE Positioning.

attribute.name: altitude
attribute.description: The altitude of the transmitter antenna in meters. Use +/- values to denote height/depth.

attribute.name: cellPortionCoverage
attribute.description: Models the cell portion coverage area used for UE positioning. The cell portion coverage area is defined by the bearing, opening angle and radius.

attribute.name: cellPortionId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: cellPortionPolygon
attribute.description: Models the manageable characteristics for the cell portion polygon used for UE. positioning. Each polygon corner is described by a latitude and longitude pair. Each polygon corner is represented with one position in the sequence. The other configured polygon corners follow in sequence.
attribute.dependencies: There must at least be three corners configured in a polygon when the function is active/used. The points shall be connected in the order that they are given. The last point is connected to the first point.

attribute.name: latitude
attribute.description: The degree of latitude of the transmitter antenna position.

attribute.name: longitude
attribute.description: The degree of longitude of the transmitter antenna position.

attribute.name: lppaCellPortionId
attribute.description: The LPPa Cell Portion ID IE defined in 3GPP TS 36.455.

attribute.name: sectorCarrierRef
attribute.description: Reference to an instance of SectorCarrier MO.

class.name: MdtConfiguration
class.description: Contains the parameters for the Minimization of Drive Tests (MDT). The RDN for this MO type is MdtConfiguration=1.

attribute.name: mdtConfigurationId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: reportingTrigger
attribute.description: Reporting trigger used for UE side MDT measurement.

attribute.name: reportIntervalMdt
attribute.description: Report interval between the periodical measurements used for UE side MDT measurement.

attribute.name: reportAmountMdt
attribute.description: Number of MDT measurements to be taken for periodical reporting. Value 0 means that reports are sent as long as the event is fulfilled.

attribute.name: a2ThresholdRsrpMdt
attribute.description: RSRP threshold value for eventA2 that triggers the MDT UE measurement.

attribute.name: a2ThresholdRsrqMdt
attribute.description: RSRQ threshold value for eventA2 that triggers the MDT UE measurement.

attribute.name: positioningMethod
attribute.description: Positioning method used to obtain UE location information.

attribute.name: hysteresisA2Mdt
attribute.description: The hysteresis value for the MDT eventA2 measurement.

attribute.name: timeToTriggerA2Mdt
attribute.description: The time-to-trigger value for the MDT eventA2 measurement.

attribute.name: maxReportCellsA2Mdt
attribute.description: Maximum number of cells to include in the measurement report for the eventA2 measurement.

attribute.name: reportQuantityA2Mdt
attribute.description: The quantities to include in the measurement report for the MDT eventA2 measurement. The value 0 - SAME_AS_TRIGGER_QUANTITY means that the same quantity as triggerQuantityA2Mdt is included in the measurement report. The value 1 - BOTH means that both Reference Symbol Received Power (RSRP) and Reference Symbol Received Quality (RSRQ) quantities are included in the measurement report.

attribute.name: triggerQuantityA2Mdt
attribute.description: The Reference Signal Received Power (RSRP) or Reference Signal Received Quality (RSRQ) quantity that triggers the MDT eventA2.

attribute.name: measGapAllowedMdt
attribute.description: Whether or not measurement gap configuration is allowed for EUTRAN inter-frequency measurements.

class.name: ReportConfigA5SoftLock
class.description: Contains the Report Configuration settings for the A5 event measurements initiated for Soft-Lock of Cell. The RDN for this MO type is "ReportConfigA5SoftLock=1".

attribute.name: reportConfigA5SoftLockId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: a5Threshold2Rsrp
attribute.description: RSRP threshold2 value for eventA5.

class.name: CellSleepNodeFunction
class.description: Contains parameters for Cell Sleep Mode support in the node that are common for all cells. The RDN of this MO is CellSleepNodeFunction=1.

attribute.name: cellSleepNodeFunctionId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: csmEutranInterFMeasReportMax
attribute.description: Maximum target number of cell sleep mode measurement reports each hour for each EUtranFreqRelation. The number of measurement reports can deviate from the target. Note that the unit is decMeasurementReport. Thus, the given number of measurement reports is divided by 10.
attribute.dependencies: csmEutranInterFMeasReportMax > csmEutranInterFMeasReportMin
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: csmEutranInterFMeasReportMin
attribute.description: Minimum target number of cell sleep mode measurement reports each hour for each EUtranFreqRelation. The number of measurement reports can deviate from the target. Note that the unit is decMeasurementReport. Thus, the given number of measurement reports is divided by 10.
attribute.dependencies: csmEutranInterFMeasReportMin < csmEutranInterFMeasReportMax
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: csmEutranInterFMeasReportIncr
attribute.description: Increase in the target number of periodic measurement reports for each EUtranFreqRelation when the required hit rate to identify cell sleep mode coverage cells is not yet achieved. Note that the unit is decMeasurementReport. Thus, the given number of measurement reports is divided by 10.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: csmEutranInterFMeasReportDecr
attribute.description: Decrease in the target number of periodic measurement reports for each EUtranFreqRelation when the required hit rate to identify cell sleep mode coverage cells is achieved. Note that the unit is decMeasurementReport. Thus, the given number of measurement reports is divided by 10.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: csmMinHitRateForCovCell
attribute.description: Minimum required hit rate value for related cell to be assigned as coverage cell. When hit rate of given cell is higher than value, cell can be selected as coverage cell for capacity cell.

class.name: ReportConfigEUtraIFA3UlTrig

attribute.name: hysteresisA3

attribute.name: reportIntervalA3

attribute.name: reportIntervalA5

attribute.name: timeToTriggerA5

class.description:

Ratio of energy per modulation bit to noise spectral density in the ThresholdUTRA, threshold2 value for eventB2.

attribute.name: hysteresisB2

attribute.name: reportIntervalB2

class.name: ReportConfigB2GeranUlTrig

attribute.name: reportConfigB2GeranUlTrigId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: b2Threshold2Geran
attribute.description: The Signal Quality in the ThresholdGERAN, threshold2 value for eventB2.

attribute.name: hysteresisB2
attribute.description: The hysteresis value for the event B2.

attribute.name: reportIntervalB2
attribute.description: The interval for event triggered periodical reporting for B2 event.

attribute.name: timeToTriggerB2
attribute.description: Time-to-trigger value for event B2.

class.name: ReportConfigB2CdmaUlTrig
class.description:
Contains report configuration settings for the B2 event for CDMA2000 measurements initiated by Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility. The actual threshold values used can be adjusted by frequency relation or QCI related offsets if the feature Multi-Layer Service-Triggered Mobility (MLSTM) is enabled.
The RDN of this MO is ReportConfigB2CdmaUlTrig=1.
class.statusInformation: Since 17.Q4. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.

attribute.name: reportConfigB2CdmaUlTrigId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.
attribute.statusInformation: Since 17.Q4. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.

attribute.description: When timer expires, channel evaluation is performed to find better carrier. Only applicable for Dynamic Channel Selection.

attribute.description: When timer expires, LBT success rate is evaluated. If less than threshold, new channel evaluation is performed to find better carrier. Only applicable for Dynamic Channel Selection.

attribute.description: Selects channel selection type: - Static channel selection configures carriers according to UnlicensedBandProfile. - Dynamic channel selection dynamically chooses best available channels.

attribute.name: laaSCellActDeactDataThres
attribute.description:
SCells can be activated if minimum time needed to transmit all bits in all priority queues of UE is higher than laaSCellActDeactDataThres.
Minimum time is calculated as number of bits in all priority queues, divided by number of bits that can be transmitted in one TTI by all active serving cells (prior to activation decision). Computed as if UE is given all resources in those cells. If condition for activating one SCell is satisfied, a second SCell is also considered for activation. Minimum time needed to transmit all bits is now re-calculated with added capacity of new SCell. Another SCell is added if still over threshhold.
"-1" means data-triggered activation condition is always satisfied even with no data in buffer, and also that data-triggered deactivation condition is never satisfied
Only used if LAA is configured in RBS.
attribute.dependencies: laaSCellActDeactDataThresHyst <= laaSCellActDeactDataThres when sCellActDeactDataThres is not equal to -1.

attribute.name: laaSCellActDeactDataThresHyst
attribute.description:
Deactivation of one component carrier is considered if: minimum time to transmit all bits in all priority queues of a UE is less than or equal to laaSCellActDeactDataThres minus laaSCellActDeactDataThresHyst.
Minimum time is calculated as number of bits in all priority queues, divided by number of bits that can be transmitted in one TTI by all active serving cells (after deactivation decision). Computed as if UE is given all resources in those cells.
If laaSCellActDeactDataThres is set to "-1", data-triggered deactivation condition is never satisfied and value of laaSCellActDeactDataThresHyst is ignored.
attribute.dependencies: laaSCellActDeactDataThresHyst <= laaSCellActDeactDataThres when sCellActDeactDataThres is not equal to -1.

class.name: NbIotCell
class.description: This MO represents a Nb-Iot cell and contains parameters needed by the cell.

attribute.name: nbIotCellType
attribute.description: The Nb-Iot cell type determines the cell deployment, i.e. the allocation of PRBs. A Nb-Iot Cell with inband deployment allocated its PRBs from an EUtranCellFDD. A guard band cell gets its PRBs from the guard bands of an EUtranCellFDD. The standalone Nb-Iot cell is deployed independently of EUtranCellFDD:s.

attribute.name: eutranCellRef
attribute.description: Reference to an EUtranCellFDD MO.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute will affect the resource allocation of the cell.
attribute.precondition: Only applicable for inband or guardband deployment. The NbIotCell Mo must be locked.

attribute.name: sectorCarrierRef
attribute.description: A list of references to instances of SectorCarrier MOs. Only applicable in standalone deployment.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute will affect the resource allocation of the cell.

attribute.name: prbNumber
attribute.description: PRB numbers used by the Nb-Iot Cell (inband or guardband deployment) The six PRBs in the middle of the EUtranCellFDD may not be reserved. Negative numbers may be used for guardband PRBs in the lower frequency range.
attribute.statusInformation: Since L17A. Planned to be removed.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute will affect the resource allocation of the cell.
attribute.precondition: Only applicable for inband or guardband deployment. The NbIotCell Mo must be locked.

attribute.name: administrativeState
attribute.description:
The administrative state.
Note: Only LOCKED or UNLOCKED is permitted to this attribute since Soft Lock is not supported in NbIotCell.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute to LOCKED causes loss of traffic.

attribute.name: availabilityStatus
attribute.description: The availability status. It contains details about operationalState.

attribute.name: cellBarred
attribute.description: Indicates if the cell is barred and should not be accessible to random UEs.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute to BARRED blocks all traffic in the cell.

attribute.name: cellId
attribute.description: RBS internal ID attribute for NB-IoT cell. Must be unique across all cell types in RBS. Together with Node ID and PLMN, this is a universally unique cell ID.

attribute.name: nbIotCellId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: operationalState
attribute.description: The operational state. This attribute is set by the application in the RBS.

attribute.name: pciConflict
attribute.description: A PCI confusion exists if a source cell has relations to two neighbor cells where both neighbor cells have the same PCI and frequency. A PCI collision exists if a source cell has a relation to a neighbor cell where both the source cell and neighbor cell have the same PCI and frequency.
attribute.statusInformation: Since L17A. Planned to be removed.

attribute.name: pciConflictCell
attribute.description: Indicates the CGI of the other cell that is involved in the PCI collision/confusion. This value is only valid if the attribute pciConflict is "YES" or "YES_CONFLICTING_CELL".
attribute.statusInformation: Since L17A. Planned to be removed.

attribute.name: physicalLayerCellIdGroup
attribute.description:
The physical layer cell ID group. Physical-layer cell IDs are grouped into 168 unique physical-layer cell-identity groups, each group containing 3 unique subidentities.
This attribute together with physicalLayerSubCellId is used to calculate physical layer cell ID (see 3GPP TS 36.211) that is sent as part of the system information (see 3GPP TS 36.331).
attribute.statusInformation: Since L17A. Planned to be removed.
attribute.disturbances: Changes may affect traffic.

attribute.name: prbIndex
attribute.description: Downlink PRB index used by the Nb-Iot Cell (inband or guardband deployment). For guardband deployment, the PRB index is outside of the PRB value range of the EUtranCellFDD (below 0 or above the cell's highest PRB index).
attribute.statusInformation: Since 17.Q3. Planned to be removed.
attribute.precondition: Only applicable for inband or guardband deployment. The NbIotCell MO must be locked.

attribute.name: plmnIdentityList
attribute.description: Lists the PLMN IDs served by at least one MME. The PLMN ID is defined in the attribute eNodeBPlmnId in the parent ENodeBFunction. Information item included in SIB1.
attribute.statusInformation: Since L17A. Replaced by plmnIdList. Planned to be removed.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute will impact the PLMN configuration for NB-IOT.

attribute.name: tac
attribute.description: Tracking Area Code for the Nb-Iot cell. Information item included in SIB1.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute may affect traffic.

attribute.name: physicalLayerCellId
attribute.description: The physical layer cell ID (see 3GPP TS 36.211). Provided as part of the system information (see 3GPP TS 36.331). If the NbIot PCI is different from the host cell PCI, the NbIot PCI shall follow NBPCI mod 6 = WBPCI mod 6, or the position of the CRS of the host cell will not be known to the UEs.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute may affect traffic.

attribute.name: earfcndl
attribute.description: The channel number for central DL frequency. Mapping from channel number to physical frequency for specified EUTRA bands is described in 3GPP TS 36.104. The values that can be used depend on national, operator-specific frequency allocation as well as on the supported frequency bands in the RBS. The value is applicable for all NB-IoT cell deployment types, if earfcndl is undefined the host cell value will be used for inband and guard band deployments. For standalone deployments it is mandatory to set earfcndl.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute may affect traffic.

attribute.name: pZeroNominalNPusch
attribute.description: The nominal component of the UE transmit power for Physical Uplink Shared Channel (N-PUSCH).

attribute.name: earfcnul
attribute.description: Channel number for the central UL frequency. The mapping from channel number to physical frequency for specified EUTRA bands is described in 3GPP TS 36.104. Values that can be used depend on national, operator-specific frequency allocation, as well as on the supported frequency bands of the RBS.
attribute.dependencies: earfcnul is calculated as an offset of earfcndl, as described in 3GPP TS36.104. If the calculated offset shall be used, this parameter shall be undefined. If the calculated offset value shall be overridden, this parameter shall be set.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute will affect the cell frequency handling.

attribute.name: qRxLevMin
attribute.description: The required minimum received Reference Symbol Received Power (RSRP) level in the E-UTRA frequency for cell reselection. Included in NB-SIB1.

attribute.name: qQualMin
attribute.description: The minimum required quality level (RSRQ) in the cell in dB. Corresponds to Qqualmin in TS 36.304, sent in NB-SIB1. Value 0 means that the lowest possible value is used for Qqualmin.

attribute.name: pMax
attribute.description: Limits UE uplink transmission power in the serving cell and calculates the parameter Pcompensation (defined in 3GPP TS 36.304) for cell selection. Included in NB-SIB1. Value 1000 means the parameter is not included in system information.

attribute.name: qHyst
attribute.description: Hysteresis value for ranking criteria. Included in NB-SIB3.

attribute.name: mappingInfo
attribute.description: SI message to which each NB-SIB is mapped.

attribute.name: siWindowLength
attribute.description: Length of SI window during which each SI message is transmitted. Applies to all SI messages.

attribute.name: siPeriodicity
attribute.description: SI message periodicity. SI message is not transmitted unless SIB is mapped to it.
attribute.statusInformation: Since 17.Q2. Planned to be removed.

attribute.name: siRepetition
attribute.description: Radio frames in SI window used for SI message transmission. Values range from every second radio frame up to every 16th radio frame. They start from first radio frame of SI window used for SI transmission. Applicable to all SI messages.
attribute.statusInformation: Since 17.Q2. Planned to be removed.

attribute.name: frequencyInfo
attribute.description: Array of inter frequency related information.

attribute.name: allocatedPrbIndex
attribute.description: Which downlink PRB index is allocated to NB-IOT cell.
attribute.dependencies: Only applicable for inband and guardband deployment.

attribute.name: plmnList
attribute.description: Lists the PLMN IDs configured for the cell. If shared NW is disabled only the first PLMN in the list is considered.
attribute.statusInformation: Since 17.Q2. Replaced by plmnIdList. Planned to be removed.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.dependencies: The list must have the same number of entries as plmnIdList.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.dependencies: The list must have the same number of entries as plmnIdList.

attribute.name: freqBand
attribute.description: The primary frequency band the cell belongs to.

attribute.name: modificationPeriodCoeff
attribute.description: Actual modification period, expressed in number of radio frames= modificationPeriodCoeff * defaultPagingCycleNbIot. See MO Paging for more info on defaultPagingCycleNbIot. Provided in NB-SIB2.
attribute.statusInformation: Since 17.Q2. Planned to be removed.

attribute.description: Cell Reselection Threshold (intra-frequency measurements). Provided in NB-SIB3.

attribute.name: sInterSearchThreshold
attribute.description: Cell Reselection Threshold (inter-frequency measurements). Provided in NB-SIB3.

attribute.name: allocatedUlPrb
attribute.description: Which uplink PRB index is allocated to NB-IOT cell.
attribute.dependencies: Only applicable in inband and guardband deployment.

attribute.description: Nb-Iot Coverage Enhancement level.

attribute.name: gbPrbIndexDl
attribute.description: Downlink PRB index used by the Nb-IoT Cell guard band deployment. For guardband deployment, the PRB index is outside of the PRB value range of the EUtranCellFDD host cell (below 0 or above the cell's highest PRB index). For above 0, the real prbindex is dependent on the LTE carrier BW, e.g. for 10Mhz BW 1 means PRB 49+1=50. There are 3 vacant sub-carriers in-between the edge LTE PRB and the guardband NB-IoT PRB for 5MHz and 15 MHz host cells on each side to guarantee that the center frequency of the guardband cell is on a 100Khz raster (in this release 5 MHz is not supported).
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect when NbIoTCell::nbIotCellType = NBIOT_GUARDBAND
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. Affects the resource allocation of the GB cell.

attribute.name: gbPrbIndexUl
attribute.description: Uplink PRB index used by the Nb-IoT Cell guardband deployment. For guardband deployment, the PRB index is outside of the PRB value range of the EUtranCellFDD host cell (below 0 or above the cell's highest PRB index). For above 0, the real prbindex is dependent on the LTE carrier BW, e.g. for 10Mhz BW 1 means PRB 49+1=50.
attribute.dependencies: Only takes effect when NbIoTCell::nbIotCellType = NBIOT_GUARDBAND
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. Affects the resource allocation of the GB cell.

attribute.name: additionalFreqBandList
attribute.description: A list of additional frequency bands the cell belongs to, not including the frequency band indicated by the EARFCN value of the cell (primary frequency band). The list is automatically set by the eNB. These additional frequency bands are broadcasted to the UEs in NB-SIB1.

attribute.name: additionalSpectrumEmissionValues
attribute.description: A list of network signaling values, where each value corresponds to the frequency band on the same position in additionalFreqBandList. Enables additional spectrum emission requirements according to 3GPP TS 36.101, table 6.2.4-1. The content of this list is based on spectrumEmissionReqMapping. This list will be broadcasted in NB-SIB2 as multiBandInfoList.

attribute.name: spectrumEmissionReqMapping
attribute.description: A list which maps frequency bands to network signaling values specifying additional spectrum emissions, as described by 3GPP TS 36.101, table 6.2.4-1. A band which is not explicitly mapped to a network signaling value by this list, will use the value NS_01. This list is used to generate the value of additionalSpectrumEmissionValues.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: networkSignallingValue
attribute.description: Enables additional spectrum emission requirements according to 3GPP TS 36.101, table 6.2.4-1.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

class.name: EUtranFreqRelationUnlicensed
class.description: MO represents mobility relation between EUtranCellFDD (or-TDD) and EUtranFrequencyUnlicensed. Contains parameters specific for this relation. One instance of this MO must refer to Band46UnlicensedProfile MO.

attribute.name: eUtranFreqRelationUnlicensedId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: allowedMeasBandwidth
attribute.description: The maximum allowed measurement bandwidth on a carrier frequency. Note: The values indicate the number of resource blocks and correspond to the channel bandwidth 1,4MHz, 3MHz, 5MHz, 10MHz, 15MHz, 20MHz respectively specified in 3GPP TS 36.104.

attribute.name: allowedPlmnList
attribute.description: Lists all Public Land Mobile Network (PLMN) IDs allowed for this frequency relation. A UE that does not support a PLMN included in allowedPlmnList does not measure on this frequency according to the UE Handover Restriction List. No values in allowedPlmnList imply that the frequency has no restrictions for PLMN. The PLMN identity consists of the following parts: 1. MobileCountryCode, MCC, 3 digits 2. MobileNetworkCode, MNC, 2 or 3 digits (the correct number of digits is set in the mncLength member of this Struct) For example, if MCC=125 and MNC=46, then plmnId=12546.
attribute.statusInformation: Since 17.Q2. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.

attribute.name: caFreqPriority
attribute.description: Prioritizes EUTRAN frequency carriers from which to pick SCells for carrier aggregation. 0 means lowest priority. -1 means the frequency is excluded from SCell selection.
attribute.dependencies: Only applicable when CarrierAggregationFunction::dynamicSCellSelectionMethod == PRIORITIZED.

attribute.name: caFreqProportion
attribute.description: In conjunction with caFreqPriority the value sets a threshold for the number of SCells on this frequency carrier that can be configured using prioritized SCell selection. A normalized value is applied. When frequency carriers have same priority, SCells are selected on the carrier with the lowest proportional SCell utilization.
attribute.dependencies: Only applicable when CarrierAggregationFunction::dynamicSCellSelectionMethod == PRIORITIZED.

attribute.name: inhibitSpidList

attribute.name: sendInhibitIMPrioritizationEnabled
attribute.description: Enable function to send load state Inhibit Idle Mode Prioritization when subscription ratio level in cell is above threshold.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: lbStopIncomingIflbThreshold
attribute.description: Threshold for subscription ratio in cell. If exceeded, IFLB towards cell must be stopped.

attribute.name: sendStopIncomingIflbEnabled
attribute.description: Enable function to send load state Stop Incoming IFLB when subscription ratio level in cell is above threshold.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: stopOutgoingIflbEnabled
attribute.description: Enable function to stop IFLB from source cell to target cell, where the target cell previously signaled load state Stop Incoming IFLB.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: plmnsToReserveAtHighLoad
attribute.description: List of PLMN IDs; broadcasted as "reserved for operator use" when total subscription ratio or total usage of any monitored system resource exceeds threshold.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: plmnResOpUseSRatioThreshold
attribute.description: Upper threshold for total subscription ratio. If total subscription ratio is above the threshold, triggers a broadcast of PLMN IDs configured in plmnsToReserveAtHighLoad as "reserved for operator use".
attribute.dependencies: plmnResOpUseSRatioThreshold>plmnUnresOpUseSRatioThreshold
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: plmnUnresOpUseSRatioThreshold
attribute.description: Lower threshold for total subscription ratio. If the total subscription ratio is below the threshold and usage of all Monitored System Resources is below plmnUnresOpUseMsrUsageThreshold, then broadcast PLMN IDs configured in plmnsToReserveAtHighLoad as "unreserved", if previously broadcasted as "reserved for operator use".
attribute.dependencies: plmnResOpUseSRatioThreshold>plmnUnresOpUseSRatioThreshold
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: plmnResOpUseMsrUsageThreshold
attribute.description: Upper threshold for monitored system resource usage. If usage of some monitored system resource is above the threshold, triggers a broadcast of PLMN IDs configured in plmnsToReserveAtHighLoad as "reserved for operator use".
attribute.dependencies: plmnResOpUseMSRUsageThreshold>plmnUnresOpUseMSRUsageThreshold
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: plmnUnresOpUseMsrUsageThreshold
attribute.description: Lower threshold for monitored system resource usage. If usage of all Monitored System Resources is below the threshold and the total subscription ratio is below plmnUnresOpUseSRatioThreshold, then broadcast PLMN IDs configured in plmnsToReserveAtHighLoad as "unreserved", if previously broadcasted as "reserved for operator use".
attribute.dependencies: plmnResOpUseMSRUsageThreshold>plmnUnresOpUseMSRUsageThreshold
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

attribute.name: spidBlacklistHo

If set to -1, UEs with no SPID value allocated are also affected by the sub-routine to block incoming handover when PLMN ID is broadcasted as "reserved for operator use".
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

class.name: TermPointToENB
class.description: Models the local eNB termination point of an X2 link between the eNB and a neighbour eNB.

attribute.name: termPointToENBId
attribute.description: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).

attribute.name: ipAddress
attribute.description: The IP address of the neighboring RBS. The input format is four fields of digits, separated by dots. Each field may consist of three digits. The value of each field is in the range 0-255.
attribute.dependencies: To set this attribute, administrativeState must be LOCKED.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of X2 connectivity.

attribute.name: administrativeState
attribute.description: The administrative state. Note: If this attribute is set to SHUTTING_DOWN, it will immediately go into the state LOCKED.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute to LOCKED or SHUTTINGDOWN causes loss of X2 connectivity.

attribute.name: availabilityStatus
attribute.description: The availability status. It contains details about operational state. This attribute is set by the application in the RBS.

attribute.name: operationalState
attribute.description: The operational state. This attribute is set by the application in the RBS.

attribute.name: domainName
attribute.description:
The fully-qualified domain name of the RBS.
A valid domain name consists of 1 or more labels separated by dots (.). Valid characters for a label are limited to letters a-z, A-Z, digits 0-9, and the character - (dash).
The following format is used for automatically created domain names:
x2.enbidDDDDD.enb.tac-lbEE.tac-hbFF.tac.eutran.mncBBB.mccCCC.3gppnetwork.org.
The D's (five or seven) represent hexadecimal coding of ENBID (enodeB Identity) without padding.
B & C represent BCD (binary coded decimal) coding of MNC (mobile network code) and MCC (mobile country code) respectively.
E & F represent hexadecimal coding of the least and most significant bytes (low & high byte) of the tracking area code.
B, C, E & F are always padded with leading zeros to match the number of characters in the format above.

attribute.name: usedIpAddress
attribute.description: The destination address used for initialization of the underlying SCTP association of the latest successful X2-Setup. The IP address can be an IPv4 or an IPv6 address. Note: usedIpAddress never changes during the lifetime of the SCTP association.

attribute.name: ipv6Address
attribute.description:
The IP address of the neighboring RBS. The format is eight fields, separated by colons.
Each field consists of four hexadecimal characters. The value of each field is in the range 0-FFFF.
Leading zeroes can be omitted in a field, and multiple groups of 16 bits of zeroes can be compressed to ::
The :: can appear only once in an address.
To set this attribute, administrativeState must be LOCKED.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of X2 connectivity.

attribute.name: createdBy
attribute.description: Indicates whether the MO has been created by the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function or operator or X2

attribute.name: timeOfCreation
attribute.description: Indicates the time and date when the MO was created. Format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS

attribute.name: lastModification

attribute.name: timeOfLastModification
attribute.description: Indicates the time and date when the MO was last modified. Format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS

class.name: TermPointToMme
class.description: Models the MME termination point of an S1 link between the RBS and the MME node.

attribute.name: termPointToMmeId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: mmeName
attribute.description: Used by OSS-RC to identify an MME. The attribute is set by the RBS at S1-SETUP.

attribute.name: domainName
attribute.description:
The fully-qualified domain name of the MME.
A valid domain name consists of 1 or more labels separated by dots (.).
Valid characters for a label are limited to letters a - z, A - Z, digits 0 - 9, and the character - (dash). Character case is preserved. Length of a label may not exceed 255 characters.
NOTE: The first and last character in the domain name must be one of the following: alphanumerical a - z, A - Z and digits 0 - 9. For more information refer to RFC 952, 1101 and 1123.
To set this attribute, administrativeState must be LOCKED.

attribute.name: ipAddress1
attribute.description:
The primary IP address of the MME. A unique IP address is required for each MME.
The input format is four fields of digits, separated by dots. Each field consists of three digits. The value of each field must be in the range 0-255.
To set this attribute, administrativeState must be LOCKED.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of S1 connectivity.

attribute.name: administrativeState
attribute.description: The administrative state. Note: If this attribute is set to SHUTTING_DOWN, it will immediately go into the state LOCKED.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute to LOCKED or SHUTTINGDOWN causes loss of traffic.

attribute.name: availabilityStatus
attribute.description: The availability status. It contains details about operationalState. This attribute is set by the application in the RBS.

attribute.name: operationalState
attribute.description: The operational state. This attribute is set by the application in the RBS.

attribute.name: ipAddress2
attribute.description:
The secondary IP address of the MME. A unique IP address is required for each MME.
The input format is four fields of digits, separated by dots. Each field consists of three digits. The value of each field must be in the range 0-255.
To set this attribute, administrativeState must be LOCKED.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of S1 connectivity.

attribute.name: usedIpAddress
attribute.description: The destination address used for initialization of the underlying SCTP association of the latest successful S1-Setup. The IP address can be an IPv4 or an IPv6 address. Note: usedIpAddress never changes during the lifetime of the SCTP association.

attribute.name: relativeMmeCapacity
attribute.description: Relative processing capacity of an MME to the other MMEs in the pool. The capacity is used to balance the load between MMEs in a pool.

attribute.name: ipv6Address1
attribute.description:
The primary IPv6 address of the MME. The input format is eight fields, separated by colons. Each field consists of four hexadecimal characters. The value of each field must be in the range 0-FFFF. Leading zeroes can be omitted in a field, and multiple groups of 16 bits of zeroes can be compressed to ::. The :: can be used only once in an address.
To set this attribute, administrativeState must be LOCKED.

attribute.name: ipv6Address2
attribute.description:
The secondary IPv6 address of the MME. The input format is eight fields, separated by colons. Each field consists of four hexadecimal characters. The value of each field must be in the range 0-FFFF. Leading zeroes can be omitted in a field and multiple groups of 16 bits of zeroes can be compressed to ::. The :: can be used only once in an address.
To set this attribute, administrativeState must be LOCKED.

attribute.name: servedPlmnListLTERelated
attribute.description:
Lists the PLMN IDs served by the MME. The attribute is set by the RBS at S1-SETUP. The PLMN ID consists of:
1. MobileCountryCode, MCC, 3 digits 2. MobileNetworkCode, MNC, 2 or 3 digits (the correct number of digits is set in the mncLength member of this Struct)
Example: If MCC=125 and MNC=46, then plmnId=12546.

attribute.name: servedPlmnListOtherRATs
attribute.description:
Lists PLMN IDs served by the MME for radio technologies other than LTE. The attribute is set by the RBS at S1-SETUP. The PLMN ID consists of:
1. MobileCountryCode, MCC, 3 digits 2. MobileNetworkCode, MNC, 2 or 3 digits (the correct number of digits is set in the mncLength member of this Struct)
Example: If MCC=125 and MNC=46, then plmnId=12546.

attribute.name: mmeCodeListLTERelated
attribute.description: MME code for LTE.

attribute.name: mmeCodeListOtherRATs

attribute.name: dcnType

attribute.name: mmeSupportLegacyLte

attribute.name: mmeSupportNbIoT
attribute.description: Enable/disable MME to serve NbIot traffic.

attribute.name: additionalCnRef

attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

Models SGW termination point of S1 link between RBS and SGW node.
The RDNs for this MO type are TermPointToSGW=1 to TermPointToSGW=64.

attribute.name: usedIpAddress
attribute.description: Remote address used for SGW termination point. Can be IPv4 or IPv6 address.

attribute.name: timeOfCreation
attribute.description: Time and date when MO was created. Format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS

attribute.name: termPointToSGWId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

class.name: GtpPath
class.description:
Models GTP-U path between RBS and another node, either SGW or neighbor RBS.
The RDN of this MO is GtpPath=1.

attribute.name: remoteIpAddress
attribute.description: Remote address used for path termination point. Can be IPv4 or IPv6 address.

attribute.name: localIpAddress
attribute.description: Local address used for path termination point. Can be IPv4 or IPv6 address.

attribute.name: samplingInterval
attribute.description: Sampling interval used for path. No delay measurements are performed and a 60-second interval is used when sampling interval is set to 0.

attribute.name: echoPeerStatus
attribute.description: Peer reachability status for path.

attribute.name: operationalState
attribute.description: The operational state. This attribute is set by the application in the RBS.

attribute.name: gtpPathId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

class.name: AdditionalCoreNetwork
class.description: MO contains information of additional core network configuration.

attribute.name: plmnList
attribute.description: Lists PLMN IDs served by additional CN. Attribute is used to identify local S1 and X2 IP interfaces for an additional core network. Additional CN can contain up to 5 PLMNs other than primary PLMN.
attribute.dependencies: 1) Make each PLMN in plmnLists unique. 2) Make each PLMN in plmnLists in each additionalCN unique.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic

attribute.name: sctpS1Ref
attribute.description: Refers to the SCTP instance that is used to configure the SCTP host for S1 connections of the PLMNs in plmnList.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic

attribute.name: upS1IpAddressRef
attribute.description: Refers to the IpAccessHostEt or AddressIPv4/AddressIPv6 instance to use for configuring the IP address for S1 plane connections of the PLMNs in plmnList.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic

attribute.name: upX2IpAddressRef
attribute.description: Refers to the IpAccessHostEt or AddressIPv4/AddressIPv6 instance to use for configuring the IP address for X2 user plane connections of the PLMNs in plmnList.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic

attribute.name: dnsSelectionS1Ref
attribute.description: Controls DNS selection for S1 lookup for PLMNs in plmnList. If not set, DNS queries use DNS servers located in OAM network. It can be set to reference a DnsClient, and DNS queries are resolved using referenced DnsClient (typically using DNS server on transport network).
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect start(restart) duration
attribute.precondition: To enable this attribute DNS servers must support EDNS0.

attribute.name: additionalCoreNetworkId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: reservedBy
attribute.description: List of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.
attribute.dependencies: MO can not be deleted if it is reserved.

class.name: TermPointToGNB
class.description: Models the local eNB termination point of an X2 link between the gNB and an eNB.

attribute.name: termPointToGNBId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: administrativeState
attribute.description: The administrative state. Note: If this attribute is set to SHUTTING_DOWN, it will immediately go into the state LOCKED.

attribute.name: availabilityStatus
attribute.description: The availability status. It contains details about operational state. This attribute is set by the application in the RBS.

attribute.name: operationalState
attribute.description: The operational state. This attribute is set by the application in the RBS.

attribute.name: ipAddress
attribute.description: The IP address of the neighboring RBS. The input format is four fields of digits, separated by dots. Each field may consist of three digits. The value of each field is in the range 0-255.
attribute.dependencies: To set this attribute, administrativeState must be LOCKED.

attribute.name: ipv6Address
attribute.description:
The IP address of the neighboring RBS. The format is eight fields, separated by colons.
Each field consists of four hexadecimal characters. The value of each field is in the range 0-FFFF.
Leading zeroes can be omitted in a field, and multiple groups of 16 bits of zeroes can be compressed to ::
The :: can appear only once in an address.
attribute.dependencies: To set this attribute, administrativeState must be LOCKED.

attribute.name: domainName
attribute.description:
The fully-qualified domain name of the RBS.
A valid domain name consists of 1 or more labels separated by dots (.). Valid characters for a label are limited to letters a-z, A-Z, digits 0-9, and the character - (dash).
The following format is used for automatically created domain names:
x2.enbidDDDDD.enb.tac-lbEE.tac-hbFF.tac.eutran.mncBBB.mccCCC.3gppnetwork.org.
The D's (five or seven) represent hexadecimal coding of ENBID (enodeB Identity) without padding.
B & C represent BCD (binary coded decimal) coding of MNC (mobile network code) and MCC (mobile country code) respectively.
E & F represent hexadecimal coding of the least and most significant bytes (low & high byte) of the tracking area code.
B, C, E & F are always padded with leading zeros to match the number of characters in the format above.

attribute.name: usedIpAddress
attribute.description: The destination address used for initialization of the underlying SCTP association of the latest successful X2-Setup. The IP address can be an IPv4 or an IPv6 address. Note: usedIpAddress never changes during the lifetime of the SCTP association.
